9658 return EI.UserTE == E && EI.EdgeIdx == NodeIdx;
9659 }) ||
9660 any_of(VectorizableTree,
9661 [E, NodeIdx, VE](const std::unique_ptr<TreeEntry> &TE) {
9662 return TE->isOperandGatherNode({E, NodeIdx}) &&
9663 VE->isSame(TE->Scalars);
9664 }))) {
9665 auto FinalShuffle = [&](Value *V, ArrayRef<int> Mask) {
9666 ShuffleInstructionBuilder ShuffleBuilder(Builder, *this);
9667 ShuffleBuilder.add(V, Mask);
9668 return ShuffleBuilder.finalize(std::nullopt);
9669 };
9670 Value *V = vectorizeTree(VE);
9671 if (VF != cast<FixedVectorType>(V->getType())->getNumElements()) {
9672 if (!VE->ReuseShuffleIndices.empty()) {
9673 // Reshuffle to get only unique values.
9674 // If some of the scalars are duplicated in the vectorization
9675 // tree entry, we do not vectorize them but instead generate a
9676 // mask for the reuses. But if there are several users of the
9677 // same entry, they may have different vectorization factors.
9678 // This is especially important for PHI nodes. In this case, we
9679 // need to adapt the resulting instruction for the user
9680 // vectorization factor and have to reshuffle it again to take
9681 // only unique elements of the vector. Without this code the
9682 // function incorrectly returns reduced vector instruction with
9683 // the same elements, not with the unique ones.
9684
9685 // block:
9686 // %phi = phi <2 x > { .., %entry} {%shuffle, %block}
9687 // %2 = shuffle <2 x > %phi, poison, <4 x > <1, 1, 0, 0>
9688 // ... (use %2)
9689 // %shuffle = shuffle <2 x> %2, poison, <2 x> {2, 0}
9690 // br %block
9691 SmallVector<int> UniqueIdxs(VF, PoisonMaskElem);
9692 SmallSet<int, 4> UsedIdxs;
9693 int Pos = 0;
9694 for (int Idx : VE->ReuseShuffleIndices) {
9695 if (Idx != static_cast<int>(VF) && Idx != PoisonMaskElem &&
9696 UsedIdxs.insert(Idx).second)
9697 UniqueIdxs[Idx] = Pos;
9698 ++Pos;
9699 }
9700 assert(VF >= UsedIdxs.size() && "Expected vectorization factor "
9701 "less than original vector size.");
9702 UniqueIdxs.append(VF - UsedIdxs.size(), PoisonMaskElem);
9703 V = FinalShuffle(V, UniqueIdxs);
9704 } else {
9705 assert(VF < cast<FixedVectorType>(V->getType())->getNumElements() &&
9706 "Expected vectorization factor less "
9707 "than original vector size.");
9708 SmallVector<int> UniformMask(VF, 0);
9709 std::iota(UniformMask.begin(), UniformMask.end(), 0);
9710 V = FinalShuffle(V, UniformMask);
9711 }
9712 }
9713 // Need to update the operand gather node, if actually the operand is not a
9714 // vectorized node, but the buildvector/gather node, which matches one of
9715 // the vectorized nodes.
9716 if (find_if(VE->UserTreeIndices, [&](const EdgeInfo &EI) {
9717 return EI.UserTE == E && EI.EdgeIdx == NodeIdx;
9718 }) == VE->UserTreeIndices.end()) {
9719 auto *It = find_if(
9720 VectorizableTree, [&](const std::unique_ptr<TreeEntry> &TE) {
9721 return TE->State == TreeEntry::NeedToGather &&
9722 TE->UserTreeIndices.front().UserTE == E &&
9723 TE->UserTreeIndices.front().EdgeIdx == NodeIdx;
9724 });
9725 assert(It != VectorizableTree.end() && "Expected gather node operand.");
9726 (*It)->VectorizedValue = V;
9727 }
9728 return V;
9729 }
9730 }
9731
9732 // Find the corresponding gather entry and vectorize it.
9733 // Allows to be more accurate with tree/graph transformations, checks for the
9734 // correctness of the transformations in many cases.
9735 auto *I = find_if(VectorizableTree,
9736 [E, NodeIdx](const std::unique_ptr<TreeEntry> &TE) {
9737 return TE->isOperandGatherNode({E, NodeIdx});
9738 });
9739 assert(I != VectorizableTree.end() && "Gather node is not in the graph.");
9740 assert(I->get()->UserTreeIndices.size() == 1 &&
9741 "Expected only single user for the gather node.");
9742 assert(I->get()->isSame(VL) && "Expected same list of scalars.");
9743 IRBuilder<>::InsertPointGuard Guard(Builder);
9744 if (E->getOpcode() != Instruction::InsertElement &&
9745 E->getOpcode() != Instruction::PHI) {
9746 Instruction *LastInst = &getLastInstructionInBundle(E);
9747 assert(LastInst && "Failed to find last instruction in bundle");
9748 Builder.SetInsertPoint(LastInst);
9749 }
9750 return vectorizeTree(I->get());
9751}
9752
9753template <typename BVTy, typename ResTy, typename... Args>
9754ResTy BoUpSLP::processBuildVector(const TreeEntry *E, Args &...Params) {
9755 assert(E->State == TreeEntry::NeedToGather && "Expected gather node.");
9756 unsigned VF = E->getVectorFactor();
9757
9758 bool NeedFreeze = false;
9759 SmallVector<int> ReuseShuffleIndicies(E->ReuseShuffleIndices.begin(),
9760 E->ReuseShuffleIndices.end());
9761 SmallVector<Value *> GatheredScalars(E->Scalars.begin(), E->Scalars.end());
9762 // Build a mask out of the reorder indices and reorder scalars per this
9763 // mask.
9764 SmallVector<int> ReorderMask;
9765 inversePermutation(E->ReorderIndices, ReorderMask);
9766 if (!ReorderMask.empty())
9767 reorderScalars(GatheredScalars, ReorderMask);
9768 auto FindReusedSplat = [&](SmallVectorImpl<int> &Mask) {
9769 if (!isSplat(E->Scalars) || none_of(E->Scalars, [](Value *V) {
9770 return isa<UndefValue>(V) && !isa<PoisonValue>(V);
9771 }))
9772 return false;
9773 TreeEntry *UserTE = E->UserTreeIndices.back().UserTE;
9774 unsigned EdgeIdx = E->UserTreeIndices.back().EdgeIdx;
9775 if (UserTE->getNumOperands() != 2)
9776 return false;
9777 auto *It =
9778 find_if(VectorizableTree, [=](const std::unique_ptr<TreeEntry> &TE) {
9779 return find_if(TE->UserTreeIndices, [=](const EdgeInfo &EI) {
9780 return EI.UserTE == UserTE && EI.EdgeIdx != EdgeIdx;
9781 }) != TE->UserTreeIndices.end();
9782 });
9783 if (It == VectorizableTree.end())
9784 return false;
9785 unsigned I =
9786 *find_if_not(Mask, [](int Idx) { return Idx == PoisonMaskElem; });
9787 int Sz = Mask.size();
9788 if (all_of(Mask, [Sz](int Idx) { return Idx < 2 * Sz; }) &&
9789 ShuffleVectorInst::isIdentityMask(Mask))
9790 std::iota(Mask.begin(), Mask.end(), 0);
9791 else
9792 std::fill(Mask.begin(), Mask.end(), I);
9793 return true;
9794 };
9795 BVTy ShuffleBuilder(Params...);
9796 ResTy Res = ResTy();
9797 SmallVector<int> Mask;
9798 SmallVector<int> ExtractMask;
9799 std::optional<TargetTransformInfo::ShuffleKind> ExtractShuffle;
9800 std::optional<TargetTransformInfo::ShuffleKind> GatherShuffle;
9801 SmallVector<const TreeEntry *> Entries;
9802 Type *ScalarTy = GatheredScalars.front()->getType();
9803 if (!all_of(GatheredScalars, UndefValue::classof)) {
9804 // Check for gathered extracts.
9805 ExtractShuffle = tryToGatherExtractElements(GatheredScalars, ExtractMask);
9806 SmallVector<Value *> IgnoredVals;
9807 if (UserIgnoreList)
9808 IgnoredVals.assign(UserIgnoreList->begin(), UserIgnoreList->end());
9809 bool Resized = false;
9810 if (Value *VecBase = ShuffleBuilder.adjustExtracts(E, ExtractMask))
9811 if (auto *VecBaseTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(VecBase->getType()))
9812 if (VF == VecBaseTy->getNumElements() && GatheredScalars.size() != VF) {
9813 Resized = true;
9814 GatheredScalars.append(VF - GatheredScalars.size(),
9815 PoisonValue::get(ScalarTy));
9816 }
9817 // Gather extracts after we check for full matched gathers only.
9818 if (ExtractShuffle || E->getOpcode() != Instruction::Load ||
9819 E->isAltShuffle() ||
9820 all_of(E->Scalars, [this](Value *V) { return getTreeEntry(V); }) ||
9821 isSplat(E->Scalars) ||
9822 (E->Scalars != GatheredScalars && GatheredScalars.size() <= 2)) {
9823 GatherShuffle = isGatherShuffledEntry(E, GatheredScalars, Mask, Entries);
9824 }
9825 if (GatherShuffle) {
9826 if (Value *Delayed = ShuffleBuilder.needToDelay(E, Entries)) {
9827 // Delay emission of gathers which are not ready yet.
9828 PostponedGathers.insert(E);
9829 // Postpone gather emission, will be emitted after the end of the
9830 // process to keep correct order.
9831 return Delayed;
9832 }
9833 assert((Entries.size() == 1 || Entries.size() == 2) &&
9834 "Expected shuffle of 1 or 2 entries.");
9835 if (*GatherShuffle == TTI::SK_PermuteSingleSrc &&
9836 Entries.front()->isSame(E->Scalars)) {
9837 // Perfect match in the graph, will reuse the previously vectorized
9838 // node. Cost is 0.
9839 LLVM_DEBUG(
9840 dbgs()
9841 << "SLP: perfect diamond match for gather bundle that starts with "
9842 << *E->Scalars.front() << ".\n");
9843 // Restore the mask for previous partially matched values.
9844 if (Entries.front()->ReorderIndices.empty() &&
9845 ((Entries.front()->ReuseShuffleIndices.empty() &&
9846 E->Scalars.size() == Entries.front()->Scalars.size()) ||
9847 (E->Scalars.size() ==
9848 Entries.front()->ReuseShuffleIndices.size()))) {
9849 std::iota(Mask.begin(), Mask.end(), 0);
9850 } else {
9851 for (auto [I, V] : enumerate(E->Scalars)) {
9852 if (isa<PoisonValue>(V)) {
9853 Mask[I] = PoisonMaskElem;
9854 continue;
9855 }
9856 Mask[I] = Entries.front()->findLaneForValue(V);
9857 }
9858 }
9859 ShuffleBuilder.add(Entries.front()->VectorizedValue, Mask);
9860 Res = ShuffleBuilder.finalize(E->getCommonMask());
9861 return Res;
9862 }
9863 if (!Resized) {
9864 unsigned VF1 = Entries.front()->getVectorFactor();
9865 unsigned VF2 = Entries.back()->getVectorFactor();
9866 if ((VF == VF1 || VF == VF2) && GatheredScalars.size() != VF)
9867 GatheredScalars.append(VF - GatheredScalars.size(),
9868 PoisonValue::get(ScalarTy));
9869 }
9870 // Remove shuffled elements from list of gathers.
9871 for (int I = 0, Sz = Mask.size(); I < Sz; ++I) {
9872 if (Mask[I] != PoisonMaskElem)
9873 GatheredScalars[I] = PoisonValue::get(ScalarTy);
9874 }
9875 }
9876 }
9877 auto TryPackScalars = [&](SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Scalars,
9878 SmallVectorImpl<int> &ReuseMask,
9879 bool IsRootPoison) {
9880 // For splats with can emit broadcasts instead of gathers, so try to find
9881 // such sequences.
9882 bool IsSplat = IsRootPoison && isSplat(Scalars) &&
9883 (Scalars.size() > 2 || Scalars.front() == Scalars.back());
9884 Scalars.append(VF - Scalars.size(), PoisonValue::get(ScalarTy));
9885 SmallVector<int> UndefPos;
9886 DenseMap<Value *, unsigned> UniquePositions;
9887 // Gather unique non-const values and all constant values.
9888 // For repeated values, just shuffle them.
9889 int NumNonConsts = 0;
9890 int SinglePos = 0;
9891 for (auto [I, V] : enumerate(Scalars)) {
9892 if (isa<UndefValue>(V)) {
9893 if (!isa<PoisonValue>(V)) {
9894 ReuseMask[I] = I;
9895 UndefPos.push_back(I);
9896 }
9897 continue;
9898 }
9899 if (isConstant(V)) {
9900 ReuseMask[I] = I;
9901 continue;
9902 }
9903 ++NumNonConsts;
9904 SinglePos = I;
9905 Value *OrigV = V;
9906 Scalars[I] = PoisonValue::get(ScalarTy);
9907 if (IsSplat) {
9908 Scalars.front() = OrigV;
9909 ReuseMask[I] = 0;
9910 } else {
9911 const auto Res = UniquePositions.try_emplace(OrigV, I);
9912 Scalars[Res.first->second] = OrigV;
9913 ReuseMask[I] = Res.first->second;
9914 }
9915 }
9916 if (NumNonConsts == 1) {
9917 // Restore single insert element.
9918 if (IsSplat) {
9919 ReuseMask.assign(VF, PoisonMaskElem);
9920 std::swap(Scalars.front(), Scalars[SinglePos]);
9921 if (!UndefPos.empty() && UndefPos.front() == 0)
9922 Scalars.front() = UndefValue::get(ScalarTy);
9923 }
9924 ReuseMask[SinglePos] = SinglePos;
9925 } else if (!UndefPos.empty() && IsSplat) {
9926 // For undef values, try to replace them with the simple broadcast.
9927 // We can do it if the broadcasted value is guaranteed to be
9928 // non-poisonous, or by freezing the incoming scalar value first.
9929 auto *It = find_if(Scalars, [this, E](Value *V) {
9930 return !isa<UndefValue>(V) &&
9931 (getTreeEntry(V) || isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(V) ||
9932 (E->UserTreeIndices.size() == 1 &&
9933 any_of(V->uses(), [E](const Use &U) {
9934 // Check if the value already used in the same operation in
9935 // one of the nodes already.
9936 return E->UserTreeIndices.front().EdgeIdx !=
9937 U.getOperandNo() &&
9938 is_contained(
9939 E->UserTreeIndices.front().UserTE->Scalars,
9940 U.getUser());
9941 })));
9942 });
9943 if (It != Scalars.end()) {
9944 // Replace undefs by the non-poisoned scalars and emit broadcast.
9945 int Pos = std::distance(Scalars.begin(), It);
9946 for_each(UndefPos, [&](int I) {
9947 // Set the undef position to the non-poisoned scalar.
9948 ReuseMask[I] = Pos;
9949 // Replace the undef by the poison, in the mask it is replaced by
9950 // non-poisoned scalar already.
9951 if (I != Pos)
9952 Scalars[I] = PoisonValue::get(ScalarTy);
9953 });
9954 } else {
9955 // Replace undefs by the poisons, emit broadcast and then emit
9956 // freeze.
9957 for_each(UndefPos, [&](int I) {
9958 ReuseMask[I] = PoisonMaskElem;
9959 if (isa<UndefValue>(Scalars[I]))
9960 Scalars[I] = PoisonValue::get(ScalarTy);
9961 });
9962 NeedFreeze = true;
9963 }
9964 }
9965 };
9966 if (ExtractShuffle || GatherShuffle) {
9967 bool IsNonPoisoned = true;
9968 bool IsUsedInExpr = false;
9969 Value *Vec1 = nullptr;
9970 if (ExtractShuffle) {
9971 // Gather of extractelements can be represented as just a shuffle of
9972 // a single/two vectors the scalars are extracted from.
9973 // Find input vectors.
9974 Value *Vec2 = nullptr;
9975 for (unsigned I = 0, Sz = ExtractMask.size(); I < Sz; ++I) {
9976 if (ExtractMask[I] == PoisonMaskElem ||
9977 (!Mask.empty() && Mask[I] != PoisonMaskElem)) {
9978 ExtractMask[I] = PoisonMaskElem;
9979 continue;
9980 }
9981 if (isa<UndefValue>(E->Scalars[I]))
9982 continue;
9983 auto *EI = cast<ExtractElementInst>(E->Scalars[I]);
9984 if (!Vec1) {
9985 Vec1 = EI->getVectorOperand();
9986 } else if (Vec1 != EI->getVectorOperand()) {
9987 assert((!Vec2 || Vec2 == EI->getVectorOperand()) &&
9988 "Expected only 1 or 2 vectors shuffle.");
9989 Vec2 = EI->getVectorOperand();
9990 }
9991 }
9992 if (Vec2) {
9993 IsNonPoisoned &=
9994 isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(Vec1) && isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(Vec2);
9995 ShuffleBuilder.add(Vec1, Vec2, ExtractMask);
9996 } else if (Vec1) {
9997 IsUsedInExpr = FindReusedSplat(ExtractMask);
9998 ShuffleBuilder.add(Vec1, ExtractMask);
9999 IsNonPoisoned &= isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(Vec1);
10000 } else {
10001 ShuffleBuilder.add(PoisonValue::get(FixedVectorType::get(
10002 ScalarTy, GatheredScalars.size())),
10003 ExtractMask);
10004 }
10005 }
10006 if (GatherShuffle) {
10007 if (Entries.size() == 1) {
10008 IsUsedInExpr = FindReusedSplat(Mask);
10009 ShuffleBuilder.add(Entries.front()->VectorizedValue, Mask);
10010 IsNonPoisoned &=
10011 isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(Entries.front()->VectorizedValue);
10012 } else {
10013 ShuffleBuilder.add(Entries.front()->VectorizedValue,
10014 Entries.back()->VectorizedValue, Mask);
10015 IsNonPoisoned &=
10016 isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(Entries.front()->VectorizedValue) &&
10017 isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(Entries.back()->VectorizedValue);
10018 }
10019 }
10020 // Try to figure out best way to combine values: build a shuffle and insert
10021 // elements or just build several shuffles.
10022 // Insert non-constant scalars.
10023 SmallVector<Value *> NonConstants(GatheredScalars);
10024 int EMSz = ExtractMask.size();
10025 int MSz = Mask.size();
10026 // Try to build constant vector and shuffle with it only if currently we
10027 // have a single permutation and more than 1 scalar constants.
10028 bool IsSingleShuffle = !ExtractShuffle || !GatherShuffle;
10029 bool IsIdentityShuffle =
10030 (ExtractShuffle.value_or(TTI::SK_PermuteTwoSrc) ==
10031 TTI::SK_PermuteSingleSrc &&
10032 none_of(ExtractMask, [&](int I) { return I >= EMSz; }) &&
10033 ShuffleVectorInst::isIdentityMask(ExtractMask)) ||
10034 (GatherShuffle.value_or(TTI::SK_PermuteTwoSrc) ==
10035 TTI::SK_PermuteSingleSrc &&
10036 none_of(Mask, [&](int I) { return I >= MSz; }) &&
10037 ShuffleVectorInst::isIdentityMask(Mask));
10038 bool EnoughConstsForShuffle =
10039 IsSingleShuffle &&
10040 (none_of(GatheredScalars,
10041 [](Value *V) {
10042 return isa<UndefValue>(V) && !isa<PoisonValue>(V);
10043 }) ||
10044 any_of(GatheredScalars,
10045 [](Value *V) {
10046 return isa<Constant>(V) && !isa<UndefValue>(V);
10047 })) &&
10048 (!IsIdentityShuffle ||
10049 (GatheredScalars.size() == 2 &&
10050 any_of(GatheredScalars,
10051 [](Value *V) { return !isa<UndefValue>(V); })) ||
10052 count_if(GatheredScalars, [](Value *V) {
10053 return isa<Constant>(V) && !isa<PoisonValue>(V);
10054 }) > 1);
10055 // NonConstants array contains just non-constant values, GatheredScalars
10056 // contains only constant to build final vector and then shuffle.
10057 for (int I = 0, Sz = GatheredScalars.size(); I < Sz; ++I) {
10058 if (EnoughConstsForShuffle && isa<Constant>(GatheredScalars[I]))
10059 NonConstants[I] = PoisonValue::get(ScalarTy);
10060 else
10061 GatheredScalars[I] = PoisonValue::get(ScalarTy);
10062 }
10063 // Generate constants for final shuffle and build a mask for them.
10064 if (!all_of(GatheredScalars, PoisonValue::classof)) {
10065 SmallVector<int> BVMask(GatheredScalars.size(), PoisonMaskElem);
10066 TryPackScalars(GatheredScalars, BVMask, /*IsRootPoison=*/true);
10067 Value *BV = ShuffleBuilder.gather(GatheredScalars);
10068 ShuffleBuilder.add(BV, BVMask);
10069 }
10070 if (all_of(NonConstants, [=](Value *V) {
10071 return isa<PoisonValue>(V) ||
10072 (IsSingleShuffle && ((IsIdentityShuffle &&
10073 IsNonPoisoned) || IsUsedInExpr) && isa<UndefValue>(V));
10074 }))
10075 Res = ShuffleBuilder.finalize(E->ReuseShuffleIndices);
10076 else
10077 Res = ShuffleBuilder.finalize(
10078 E->ReuseShuffleIndices, E->Scalars.size(),
10079 [&](Value *&Vec, SmallVectorImpl<int> &Mask) {
10080 TryPackScalars(NonConstants, Mask, /*IsRootPoison=*/false);
10081 Vec = ShuffleBuilder.gather(NonConstants, Vec);
10082 });
10083 } else if (!allConstant(GatheredScalars)) {
10084 // Gather unique scalars and all constants.
10085 SmallVector<int> ReuseMask(GatheredScalars.size(), PoisonMaskElem);
10086 TryPackScalars(GatheredScalars, ReuseMask, /*IsRootPoison=*/true);
10087 Value *BV = ShuffleBuilder.gather(GatheredScalars);
10088 ShuffleBuilder.add(BV, ReuseMask);
10089 Res = ShuffleBuilder.finalize(E->ReuseShuffleIndices);
10090 } else {
10091 // Gather all constants.
10092 SmallVector<int> Mask(E->Scalars.size(), PoisonMaskElem);
10093 for (auto [I, V] : enumerate(E->Scalars)) {
10094 if (!isa<PoisonValue>(V))
10095 Mask[I] = I;
10096 }
10097 Value *BV = ShuffleBuilder.gather(E->Scalars);
10098 ShuffleBuilder.add(BV, Mask);
10099 Res = ShuffleBuilder.finalize(E->ReuseShuffleIndices);
10100 }
10101
10102 if (NeedFreeze)
10103 Res = ShuffleBuilder.createFreeze(Res);
10104 return Res;
10105}
10106
10107Value *BoUpSLP::createBuildVector(const TreeEntry *E) {
10108 return processBuildVector<ShuffleInstructionBuilder, Value *>(E, Builder,
10109 *this);
10110}
10111
10112Value *BoUpSLP::vectorizeTree(TreeEntry *E) {
10113 IRBuilder<>::InsertPointGuard Guard(Builder);
10114
10115 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10116 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *E->Scalars[0] << ".\n");
10117 return E->VectorizedValue;
10118 }
10119
10120 if (E->State == TreeEntry::NeedToGather) {
10121 if (E->getMainOp() && E->Idx == 0)
10122 setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);
10123 Value *Vec = createBuildVector(E);
10124 E->VectorizedValue = Vec;
10125 return Vec;
10126 }
10127
10128 auto FinalShuffle = [&](Value *V, const TreeEntry *E) {
10129 ShuffleInstructionBuilder ShuffleBuilder(Builder, *this);
10130 if (E->getOpcode() == Instruction::Store) {
10131 ArrayRef<int> Mask =
10132 ArrayRef(reinterpret_cast<const int *>(E->ReorderIndices.begin()),
10133 E->ReorderIndices.size());
10134 ShuffleBuilder.add(V, Mask);
10135 } else {
10136 ShuffleBuilder.addOrdered(V, E->ReorderIndices);
10137 }
10138 return ShuffleBuilder.finalize(E->ReuseShuffleIndices);
10139 };
10140
10141 assert((E->State == TreeEntry::Vectorize ||
10142 E->State == TreeEntry::ScatterVectorize) &&
10143 "Unhandled state");
10144 unsigned ShuffleOrOp =
10145 E->isAltShuffle() ? (unsigned)Instruction::ShuffleVector : E->getOpcode();
10146 Instruction *VL0 = E->getMainOp();
10147 Type *ScalarTy = VL0->getType();
10148 if (auto *Store = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(VL0))
10149 ScalarTy = Store->getValueOperand()->getType();
10150 else if (auto *IE = dyn_cast<InsertElementInst>(VL0))
10151 ScalarTy = IE->getOperand(1)->getType();
10152 auto *VecTy = FixedVectorType::get(ScalarTy, E->Scalars.size());
10153 switch (ShuffleOrOp) {
10154 case Instruction::PHI: {
10155 assert((E->ReorderIndices.empty() ||
10156 E != VectorizableTree.front().get() ||
10157 !E->UserTreeIndices.empty()) &&
10158 "PHI reordering is free.");
10159 auto *PH = cast<PHINode>(VL0);
10160 Builder.SetInsertPoint(PH->getParent()->getFirstNonPHI());
10161 Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(PH->getDebugLoc());
10162 PHINode *NewPhi = Builder.CreatePHI(VecTy, PH->getNumIncomingValues());
10163 Value *V = NewPhi;
10164
10165 // Adjust insertion point once all PHI's have been generated.
10166 Builder.SetInsertPoint(&*PH->getParent()->getFirstInsertionPt());
10167 Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(PH->getDebugLoc());
10168
10169 V = FinalShuffle(V, E);
10170
10171 E->VectorizedValue = V;
10172
10173 // PHINodes may have multiple entries from the same block. We want to
10174 // visit every block once.
10175 SmallPtrSet<BasicBlock *, 4> VisitedBBs;
10176
10177 for (unsigned i = 0, e = PH->getNumIncomingValues(); i < e; ++i) {
10178 ValueList Operands;
10179 BasicBlock *IBB = PH->getIncomingBlock(i);
10180
10181 // Stop emission if all incoming values are generated.
10182 if (NewPhi->getNumIncomingValues() == PH->getNumIncomingValues()) {
10183 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10184 return V;
10185 }
10186
10187 if (!VisitedBBs.insert(IBB).second) {
10188 NewPhi->addIncoming(NewPhi->getIncomingValueForBlock(IBB), IBB);
10189 continue;
10190 }
10191
10192 Builder.SetInsertPoint(IBB->getTerminator());
10193 Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(PH->getDebugLoc());
10194 Value *Vec = vectorizeOperand(E, i);
10195 NewPhi->addIncoming(Vec, IBB);
10196 }
10197
10198 assert(NewPhi->getNumIncomingValues() == PH->getNumIncomingValues() &&
10199 "Invalid number of incoming values");
10200 return V;
10201 }
10202
10203 case Instruction::ExtractElement: {
10204 Value *V = E->getSingleOperand(0);
10205 setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);
10206 V = FinalShuffle(V, E);
10207 E->VectorizedValue = V;
10208 return V;
10209 }
10210 case Instruction::ExtractValue: {
10211 auto *LI = cast<LoadInst>(E->getSingleOperand(0));
10212 Builder.SetInsertPoint(LI);
10213 auto *PtrTy = PointerType::get(VecTy, LI->getPointerAddressSpace());
10214 Value *Ptr = Builder.CreateBitCast(LI->getOperand(0), PtrTy);
10215 LoadInst *V = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(VecTy, Ptr, LI->getAlign());
10216 Value *NewV = propagateMetadata(V, E->Scalars);
10217 NewV = FinalShuffle(NewV, E);
10218 E->VectorizedValue = NewV;
10219 return NewV;
10220 }
10221 case Instruction::InsertElement: {
10222 assert(E->ReuseShuffleIndices.empty() && "All inserts should be unique");
10223 Builder.SetInsertPoint(cast<Instruction>(E->Scalars.back()));
10224 Value *V = vectorizeOperand(E, 1);
10225
10226 // Create InsertVector shuffle if necessary
10227 auto *FirstInsert = cast<Instruction>(*find_if(E->Scalars, [E](Value *V) {
10228 return !is_contained(E->Scalars, cast<Instruction>(V)->getOperand(0));
10229 }));
10230 const unsigned NumElts =
10231 cast<FixedVectorType>(FirstInsert->getType())->getNumElements();
10232 const unsigned NumScalars = E->Scalars.size();
10233
10234 unsigned Offset = *getInsertIndex(VL0);
10235 assert(Offset < NumElts && "Failed to find vector index offset");
10236
10237 // Create shuffle to resize vector
10238 SmallVector<int> Mask;
10239 if (!E->ReorderIndices.empty()) {
10240 inversePermutation(E->ReorderIndices, Mask);
10241 Mask.append(NumElts - NumScalars, PoisonMaskElem);
10242 } else {
10243 Mask.assign(NumElts, PoisonMaskElem);
10244 std::iota(Mask.begin(), std::next(Mask.begin(), NumScalars), 0);
10245 }
10246 // Create InsertVector shuffle if necessary
10247 bool IsIdentity = true;
10248 SmallVector<int> PrevMask(NumElts, PoisonMaskElem);
10249 Mask.swap(PrevMask);
10250 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumScalars; ++I) {
10251 Value *Scalar = E->Scalars[PrevMask[I]];
10252 unsigned InsertIdx = *getInsertIndex(Scalar);
10253 IsIdentity &= InsertIdx - Offset == I;
10254 Mask[InsertIdx - Offset] = I;
10255 }
10256 if (!IsIdentity || NumElts != NumScalars) {
10257 V = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(V, Mask);
10258 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {
10259 GatherShuffleExtractSeq.insert(I);
10260 CSEBlocks.insert(I->getParent());
10261 }
10262 }
10263
10264 SmallVector<int> InsertMask(NumElts, PoisonMaskElem);
10265 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumElts; I++) {
10266 if (Mask[I] != PoisonMaskElem)
10267 InsertMask[Offset + I] = I;
10268 }
10269 SmallBitVector UseMask =
10270 buildUseMask(NumElts, InsertMask, UseMask::UndefsAsMask);
10271 SmallBitVector IsFirstUndef =
10272 isUndefVector(FirstInsert->getOperand(0), UseMask);
10273 if ((!IsIdentity || Offset != 0 || !IsFirstUndef.all()) &&
10274 NumElts != NumScalars) {
10275 if (IsFirstUndef.all()) {
10276 if (!ShuffleVectorInst::isIdentityMask(InsertMask)) {
10277 SmallBitVector IsFirstPoison =
10278 isUndefVector<true>(FirstInsert->getOperand(0), UseMask);
10279 if (!IsFirstPoison.all()) {
10280 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumElts; I++) {
10281 if (InsertMask[I] == PoisonMaskElem && !IsFirstPoison.test(I))
10282 InsertMask[I] = I + NumElts;
10283 }
10284 }
10285 V = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(
10286 V,
10287 IsFirstPoison.all() ? PoisonValue::get(V->getType())
10288 : FirstInsert->getOperand(0),
10289 InsertMask, cast<Instruction>(E->Scalars.back())->getName());
10290 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {
10291 GatherShuffleExtractSeq.insert(I);
10292 CSEBlocks.insert(I->getParent());
10293 }
10294 }
10295 } else {
10296 SmallBitVector IsFirstPoison =
10297 isUndefVector<true>(FirstInsert->getOperand(0), UseMask);
10298 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumElts; I++) {
10299 if (InsertMask[I] == PoisonMaskElem)
10300 InsertMask[I] = IsFirstPoison.test(I) ? PoisonMaskElem : I;
10301 else
10302 InsertMask[I] += NumElts;
10303 }
10304 V = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(
10305 FirstInsert->getOperand(0), V, InsertMask,
10306 cast<Instruction>(E->Scalars.back())->getName());
10307 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {
10308 GatherShuffleExtractSeq.insert(I);
10309 CSEBlocks.insert(I->getParent());
10310 }
10311 }
10312 }
10313
10314 ++NumVectorInstructions;
10315 E->VectorizedValue = V;
10316 return V;
10317 }
10318 case Instruction::ZExt:
10319 case Instruction::SExt:
10320 case Instruction::FPToUI:
10321 case Instruction::FPToSI:
10322 case Instruction::FPExt:
10323 case Instruction::PtrToInt:
10324 case Instruction::IntToPtr:
10325 case Instruction::SIToFP:
10326 case Instruction::UIToFP:
10327 case Instruction::Trunc:
10328 case Instruction::FPTrunc:
10329 case Instruction::BitCast: {
10330 setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);
10331
10332 Value *InVec = vectorizeOperand(E, 0);
10333 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10334 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10335 return E->VectorizedValue;
10336 }
10337
10338 auto *CI = cast<CastInst>(VL0);
10339 Value *V = Builder.CreateCast(CI->getOpcode(), InVec, VecTy);
10340 V = FinalShuffle(V, E);
10341
10342 E->VectorizedValue = V;
10343 ++NumVectorInstructions;
10344 return V;
10345 }
10346 case Instruction::FCmp:
10347 case Instruction::ICmp: {
10348 setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);
10349
10350 Value *L = vectorizeOperand(E, 0);
10351 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10352 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10353 return E->VectorizedValue;
10354 }
10355 Value *R = vectorizeOperand(E, 1);
10356 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10357 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10358 return E->VectorizedValue;
10359 }
10360
10361 CmpInst::Predicate P0 = cast<CmpInst>(VL0)->getPredicate();
10362 Value *V = Builder.CreateCmp(P0, L, R);
10363 propagateIRFlags(V, E->Scalars, VL0);
10364 V = FinalShuffle(V, E);
10365
10366 E->VectorizedValue = V;
10367 ++NumVectorInstructions;
10368 return V;
10369 }
10370 case Instruction::Select: {
10371 setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);
10372
10373 Value *Cond = vectorizeOperand(E, 0);
10374 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10375 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10376 return E->VectorizedValue;
10377 }
10378 Value *True = vectorizeOperand(E, 1);
10379 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10380 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10381 return E->VectorizedValue;
10382 }
10383 Value *False = vectorizeOperand(E, 2);
10384 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10385 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10386 return E->VectorizedValue;
10387 }
10388
10389 Value *V = Builder.CreateSelect(Cond, True, False);
10390 V = FinalShuffle(V, E);
10391
10392 E->VectorizedValue = V;
10393 ++NumVectorInstructions;
10394 return V;
10395 }
10396 case Instruction::FNeg: {
10397 setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);
10398
10399 Value *Op = vectorizeOperand(E, 0);
10400
10401 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10402 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10403 return E->VectorizedValue;
10404 }
10405
10406 Value *V = Builder.CreateUnOp(
10407 static_cast<Instruction::UnaryOps>(E->getOpcode()), Op);
10408 propagateIRFlags(V, E->Scalars, VL0);
10409 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V))
10410 V = propagateMetadata(I, E->Scalars);
10411
10412 V = FinalShuffle(V, E);
10413
10414 E->VectorizedValue = V;
10415 ++NumVectorInstructions;
10416
10417 return V;
10418 }
10419 case Instruction::Add:
10420 case Instruction::FAdd:
10421 case Instruction::Sub:
10422 case Instruction::FSub:
10423 case Instruction::Mul:
10424 case Instruction::FMul:
10425 case Instruction::UDiv:
10426 case Instruction::SDiv:
10427 case Instruction::FDiv:
10428 case Instruction::URem:
10429 case Instruction::SRem:
10430 case Instruction::FRem:
10431 case Instruction::Shl:
10432 case Instruction::LShr:
10433 case Instruction::AShr:
10434 case Instruction::And:
10435 case Instruction::Or:
10436 case Instruction::Xor: {
10437 setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);
10438
10439 Value *LHS = vectorizeOperand(E, 0);
10440 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10441 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10442 return E->VectorizedValue;
10443 }
10444 Value *RHS = vectorizeOperand(E, 1);
10445 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10446 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10447 return E->VectorizedValue;
10448 }
10449
10450 Value *V = Builder.CreateBinOp(
10451 static_cast<Instruction::BinaryOps>(E->getOpcode()), LHS,
10452 RHS);
10453 propagateIRFlags(V, E->Scalars, VL0);
10454 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V))
10455 V = propagateMetadata(I, E->Scalars);
10456
10457 V = FinalShuffle(V, E);
10458
10459 E->VectorizedValue = V;
10460 ++NumVectorInstructions;
10461
10462 return V;
10463 }
10464 case Instruction::Load: {
10465 // Loads are inserted at the head of the tree because we don't want to
10466 // sink them all the way down past store instructions.
10467 setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);
10468
10469 LoadInst *LI = cast<LoadInst>(VL0);
10470 Instruction *NewLI;
10471 Value *PO = LI->getPointerOperand();
10472 if (E->State == TreeEntry::Vectorize) {
10473 NewLI = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(VecTy, PO, LI->getAlign());
10474
10475 // The pointer operand uses an in-tree scalar so we add the new
10476 // LoadInst to ExternalUses list to make sure that an extract will
10477 // be generated in the future.
10478 if (TreeEntry *Entry = getTreeEntry(PO)) {
10479 // Find which lane we need to extract.
10480 unsigned FoundLane = Entry->findLaneForValue(PO);
10481 ExternalUses.emplace_back(PO, NewLI, FoundLane);
10482 }
10483 } else {
10484 assert(E->State == TreeEntry::ScatterVectorize && "Unhandled state");
10485 Value *VecPtr = vectorizeOperand(E, 0);
10486 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10487 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10488 return E->VectorizedValue;
10489 }
10490 // Use the minimum alignment of the gathered loads.
10491 Align CommonAlignment = LI->getAlign();
10492 for (Value *V : E->Scalars)
10493 CommonAlignment =
10494 std::min(CommonAlignment, cast<LoadInst>(V)->getAlign());
10495 NewLI = Builder.CreateMaskedGather(VecTy, VecPtr, CommonAlignment);
10496 }
10497 Value *V = propagateMetadata(NewLI, E->Scalars);
10498
10499 V = FinalShuffle(V, E);
10500 E->VectorizedValue = V;
10501 ++NumVectorInstructions;
10502 return V;
10503 }
10504 case Instruction::Store: {
10505 auto *SI = cast<StoreInst>(VL0);
10506 unsigned AS = SI->getPointerAddressSpace();
10507
10508 setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);
10509
10510 Value *VecValue = vectorizeOperand(E, 0);
10511 VecValue = FinalShuffle(VecValue, E);
10512
10513 Value *ScalarPtr = SI->getPointerOperand();
10514 Value *VecPtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(
10515 ScalarPtr, VecValue->getType()->getPointerTo(AS));
10516 StoreInst *ST =
10517 Builder.CreateAlignedStore(VecValue, VecPtr, SI->getAlign());
10518
10519 // The pointer operand uses an in-tree scalar, so add the new BitCast or
10520 // StoreInst to ExternalUses to make sure that an extract will be
10521 // generated in the future.
10522 if (TreeEntry *Entry = getTreeEntry(ScalarPtr)) {
10523 // Find which lane we need to extract.
10524 unsigned FoundLane = Entry->findLaneForValue(ScalarPtr);
10525 ExternalUses.push_back(ExternalUser(
10526 ScalarPtr, ScalarPtr != VecPtr ? cast<User>(VecPtr) : ST,
10527 FoundLane));
10528 }
10529
10530 Value *V = propagateMetadata(ST, E->Scalars);
10531
10532 E->VectorizedValue = V;
10533 ++NumVectorInstructions;
10534 return V;
10535 }
10536 case Instruction::GetElementPtr: {
10537 auto *GEP0 = cast<GetElementPtrInst>(VL0);
10538 setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);
10539
10540 Value *Op0 = vectorizeOperand(E, 0);
10541 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10542 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10543 return E->VectorizedValue;
10544 }
10545
10546 SmallVector<Value *> OpVecs;
10547 for (int J = 1, N = GEP0->getNumOperands(); J < N; ++J) {
10548 Value *OpVec = vectorizeOperand(E, J);
10549 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10550 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10551 return E->VectorizedValue;
10552 }
10553 OpVecs.push_back(OpVec);
10554 }
10555
10556 Value *V = Builder.CreateGEP(GEP0->getSourceElementType(), Op0, OpVecs);
10557 if (Instruction *I = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(V)) {
10558 SmallVector<Value *> GEPs;
10559 for (Value *V : E->Scalars) {
10560 if (isa<GetElementPtrInst>(V))
10561 GEPs.push_back(V);
10562 }
10563 V = propagateMetadata(I, GEPs);
10564 }
10565
10566 V = FinalShuffle(V, E);
10567
10568 E->VectorizedValue = V;
10569 ++NumVectorInstructions;
10570
10571 return V;
10572 }
10573 case Instruction::Call: {
10574 CallInst *CI = cast<CallInst>(VL0);
10575 setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);
10576
10577 Intrinsic::ID IID = Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
10578 if (Function *FI = CI->getCalledFunction())
10579 IID = FI->getIntrinsicID();
10580
10581 Intrinsic::ID ID = getVectorIntrinsicIDForCall(CI, TLI);
10582
10583 auto VecCallCosts = getVectorCallCosts(CI, VecTy, TTI, TLI);
10584 bool UseIntrinsic = ID != Intrinsic::not_intrinsic &&
10585 VecCallCosts.first <= VecCallCosts.second;
10586
10587 Value *ScalarArg = nullptr;
10588 std::vector<Value *> OpVecs;
10589 SmallVector<Type *, 2> TysForDecl;
10590 // Add return type if intrinsic is overloaded on it.
10591 if (isVectorIntrinsicWithOverloadTypeAtArg(IID, -1))
10592 TysForDecl.push_back(
10593 FixedVectorType::get(CI->getType(), E->Scalars.size()));
10594 for (int j = 0, e = CI->arg_size(); j < e; ++j) {
10595 ValueList OpVL;
10596 // Some intrinsics have scalar arguments. This argument should not be
10597 // vectorized.
10598 if (UseIntrinsic && isVectorIntrinsicWithScalarOpAtArg(IID, j)) {
10599 CallInst *CEI = cast<CallInst>(VL0);
10600 ScalarArg = CEI->getArgOperand(j);
10601 OpVecs.push_back(CEI->getArgOperand(j));
10602 if (isVectorIntrinsicWithOverloadTypeAtArg(IID, j))
10603 TysForDecl.push_back(ScalarArg->getType());
10604 continue;
10605 }
10606
10607 Value *OpVec = vectorizeOperand(E, j);
10608 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10609 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10610 return E->VectorizedValue;
10611 }
10612 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: OpVec[" << j << "]: " << *OpVec << "\n");
10613 OpVecs.push_back(OpVec);
10614 if (isVectorIntrinsicWithOverloadTypeAtArg(IID, j))
10615 TysForDecl.push_back(OpVec->getType());
10616 }
10617
10618 Function *CF;
10619 if (!UseIntrinsic) {
10620 VFShape Shape =
10621 VFShape::get(*CI, ElementCount::getFixed(static_cast<unsigned>(
10622 VecTy->getNumElements())),
10623 false /*HasGlobalPred*/);
10624 CF = VFDatabase(*CI).getVectorizedFunction(Shape);
10625 } else {
10626 CF = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), ID, TysForDecl);
10627 }
10628
10629 SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 1> OpBundles;
10630 CI->getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles);
10631 Value *V = Builder.CreateCall(CF, OpVecs, OpBundles);
10632
10633 // The scalar argument uses an in-tree scalar so we add the new vectorized
10634 // call to ExternalUses list to make sure that an extract will be
10635 // generated in the future.
10636 if (ScalarArg) {
10637 if (TreeEntry *Entry = getTreeEntry(ScalarArg)) {
10638 // Find which lane we need to extract.
10639 unsigned FoundLane = Entry->findLaneForValue(ScalarArg);
10640 ExternalUses.push_back(
10641 ExternalUser(ScalarArg, cast<User>(V), FoundLane));
10642 }
10643 }
10644
10645 propagateIRFlags(V, E->Scalars, VL0);
10646 V = FinalShuffle(V, E);
10647
10648 E->VectorizedValue = V;
10649 ++NumVectorInstructions;
10650 return V;
10651 }
10652 case Instruction::ShuffleVector: {
10653 assert(E->isAltShuffle() &&
10654 ((Instruction::isBinaryOp(E->getOpcode()) &&
10655 Instruction::isBinaryOp(E->getAltOpcode())) ||
10656 (Instruction::isCast(E->getOpcode()) &&
10657 Instruction::isCast(E->getAltOpcode())) ||
10658 (isa<CmpInst>(VL0) && isa<CmpInst>(E->getAltOp()))) &&
10659 "Invalid Shuffle Vector Operand");
10660
10661 Value *LHS = nullptr, *RHS = nullptr;
10662 if (Instruction::isBinaryOp(E->getOpcode()) || isa<CmpInst>(VL0)) {
10663 setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);
10664 LHS = vectorizeOperand(E, 0);
10665 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10666 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10667 return E->VectorizedValue;
10668 }
10669 RHS = vectorizeOperand(E, 1);
10670 } else {
10671 setInsertPointAfterBundle(E);
10672 LHS = vectorizeOperand(E, 0);
10673 }
10674 if (E->VectorizedValue) {
10675 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Diamond merged for " << *VL0 << ".\n");
10676 return E->VectorizedValue;
10677 }
10678
10679 Value *V0, *V1;
10680 if (Instruction::isBinaryOp(E->getOpcode())) {
10681 V0 = Builder.CreateBinOp(
10682 static_cast<Instruction::BinaryOps>(E->getOpcode()), LHS, RHS);
10683 V1 = Builder.CreateBinOp(
10684 static_cast<Instruction::BinaryOps>(E->getAltOpcode()), LHS, RHS);
10685 } else if (auto *CI0 = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(VL0)) {
10686 V0 = Builder.CreateCmp(CI0->getPredicate(), LHS, RHS);
10687 auto *AltCI = cast<CmpInst>(E->getAltOp());
10688 CmpInst::Predicate AltPred = AltCI->getPredicate();
10689 V1 = Builder.CreateCmp(AltPred, LHS, RHS);
10690 } else {
10691 V0 = Builder.CreateCast(
10692 static_cast<Instruction::CastOps>(E->getOpcode()), LHS, VecTy);
10693 V1 = Builder.CreateCast(
10694 static_cast<Instruction::CastOps>(E->getAltOpcode()), LHS, VecTy);
10695 }
10696 // Add V0 and V1 to later analysis to try to find and remove matching
10697 // instruction, if any.
10698 for (Value *V : {V0, V1}) {
10699 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {
10700 GatherShuffleExtractSeq.insert(I);
10701 CSEBlocks.insert(I->getParent());
10702 }
10703 }
10704
10705 // Create shuffle to take alternate operations from the vector.
10706 // Also, gather up main and alt scalar ops to propagate IR flags to
10707 // each vector operation.
10708 ValueList OpScalars, AltScalars;
10709 SmallVector<int> Mask;
10710 buildShuffleEntryMask(
10711 E->Scalars, E->ReorderIndices, E->ReuseShuffleIndices,
10712 [E, this](Instruction *I) {
10713 assert(E->isOpcodeOrAlt(I) && "Unexpected main/alternate opcode");
10714 return isAlternateInstruction(I, E->getMainOp(), E->getAltOp(),
10715 *TLI);
10716 },
10717 Mask, &OpScalars, &AltScalars);
10718
10719 propagateIRFlags(V0, OpScalars);
10720 propagateIRFlags(V1, AltScalars);
10721
10722 Value *V = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(V0, V1, Mask);
10723 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {
10724 V = propagateMetadata(I, E->Scalars);
10725 GatherShuffleExtractSeq.insert(I);
10726 CSEBlocks.insert(I->getParent());
10727 }
10728
10729 E->VectorizedValue = V;
10730 ++NumVectorInstructions;
10731
10732 return V;
10733 }
10734 default:
10735 llvm_unreachable("unknown inst");
10736 }
10737 return nullptr;
10738}
10739
10740Value *BoUpSLP::vectorizeTree() {
10741 ExtraValueToDebugLocsMap ExternallyUsedValues;
10742 SmallVector<std::pair<Value *, Value *>> ReplacedExternals;
10743 return vectorizeTree(ExternallyUsedValues, ReplacedExternals);
10744}
10745
10746namespace {
10747/// Data type for handling buildvector sequences with the reused scalars from
10748/// other tree entries.
10749struct ShuffledInsertData {
10750 /// List of insertelements to be replaced by shuffles.
10751 SmallVector<InsertElementInst *> InsertElements;
10752 /// The parent vectors and shuffle mask for the given list of inserts.
10753 MapVector<Value *, SmallVector<int>> ValueMasks;
10754};
10755} // namespace
10756
10757Value *BoUpSLP::vectorizeTree(
10758 const ExtraValueToDebugLocsMap &ExternallyUsedValues,
10759 SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<Value *, Value *>> &ReplacedExternals,
10760 Instruction *ReductionRoot) {
10761 // All blocks must be scheduled before any instructions are inserted.
10762 for (auto &BSIter : BlocksSchedules) {
10763 scheduleBlock(BSIter.second.get());
10764 }
10765 // Clean Entry-to-LastInstruction table. It can be affected after scheduling,
10766 // need to rebuild it.
10767 EntryToLastInstruction.clear();
10768
10769 Builder.SetInsertPoint(ReductionRoot ? ReductionRoot
10770 : &F->getEntryBlock().front());
10771 auto *VectorRoot = vectorizeTree(VectorizableTree[0].get());
10772 // Run through the list of postponed gathers and emit them, replacing the temp
10773 // emitted allocas with actual vector instructions.
10774 ArrayRef<const TreeEntry *> PostponedNodes = PostponedGathers.getArrayRef();
10775 DenseMap<Value *, SmallVector<TreeEntry *>> PostponedValues;
10776 for (const TreeEntry *E : PostponedNodes) {
10777 auto *TE = const_cast<TreeEntry *>(E);
10778 if (auto *VecTE = getTreeEntry(TE->Scalars.front()))
10779 if (VecTE->isSame(TE->UserTreeIndices.front().UserTE->getOperand(
10780 TE->UserTreeIndices.front().EdgeIdx)))
10781 // Found gather node which is absolutely the same as one of the
10782 // vectorized nodes. It may happen after reordering.
10783 continue;
10784 auto *PrevVec = cast<Instruction>(TE->VectorizedValue);
10785 TE->VectorizedValue = nullptr;
10786 auto *UserI =
10787 cast<Instruction>(TE->UserTreeIndices.front().UserTE->VectorizedValue);
10788 Builder.SetInsertPoint(PrevVec);
10789 Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(UserI->getDebugLoc());
10790 Value *Vec = vectorizeTree(TE);
10791 PrevVec->replaceAllUsesWith(Vec);
10792 PostponedValues.try_emplace(Vec).first->second.push_back(TE);
10793 // Replace the stub vector node, if it was used before for one of the
10794 // buildvector nodes already.
10795 auto It = PostponedValues.find(PrevVec);
10796 if (It != PostponedValues.end()) {
10797 for (TreeEntry *VTE : It->getSecond())
10798 VTE->VectorizedValue = Vec;
10799 }
10800 eraseInstruction(PrevVec);
10801 }
10802
10803 // If the vectorized tree can be rewritten in a smaller type, we truncate the
10804 // vectorized root. InstCombine will then rewrite the entire expression. We
10805 // sign extend the extracted values below.
10806 auto *ScalarRoot = VectorizableTree[0]->Scalars[0];
10807 if (MinBWs.count(ScalarRoot)) {
10808 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(VectorRoot)) {
10809 // If current instr is a phi and not the last phi, insert it after the
10810 // last phi node.
10811 if (isa<PHINode>(I))
10812 Builder.SetInsertPoint(&*I->getParent()->getFirstInsertionPt());
10813 else
10814 Builder.SetInsertPoint(&*++BasicBlock::iterator(I));
10815 }
10816 auto BundleWidth = VectorizableTree[0]->Scalars.size();
10817 auto *MinTy = IntegerType::get(F->getContext(), MinBWs[ScalarRoot].first);
10818 auto *VecTy = FixedVectorType::get(MinTy, BundleWidth);
10819 auto *Trunc = Builder.CreateTrunc(VectorRoot, VecTy);
10820 VectorizableTree[0]->VectorizedValue = Trunc;
10821 }
10822
10823 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Extracting " << ExternalUses.size()
10824 << " values .\n");
10825
10826 SmallVector<ShuffledInsertData> ShuffledInserts;
10827 // Maps vector instruction to original insertelement instruction
10828 DenseMap<Value *, InsertElementInst *> VectorToInsertElement;
10829 // Maps extract Scalar to the corresponding extractelement instruction in the
10830 // basic block. Only one extractelement per block should be emitted.
10831 DenseMap<Value *, DenseMap<BasicBlock *, Instruction *>> ScalarToEEs;
10832 // Extract all of the elements with the external uses.
10833 for (const auto &ExternalUse : ExternalUses) {
10834 Value *Scalar = ExternalUse.Scalar;
10835 llvm::User *User = ExternalUse.User;
10836
10837 // Skip users that we already RAUW. This happens when one instruction
10838 // has multiple uses of the same value.
10839 if (User && !is_contained(Scalar->users(), User))
10840 continue;
10841 TreeEntry *E = getTreeEntry(Scalar);
10842 assert(E && "Invalid scalar");
10843 assert(E->State != TreeEntry::NeedToGather &&
10844 "Extracting from a gather list");
10845 // Non-instruction pointers are not deleted, just skip them.
10846 if (E->getOpcode() == Instruction::GetElementPtr &&
10847 !isa<GetElementPtrInst>(Scalar))
10848 continue;
10849
10850 Value *Vec = E->VectorizedValue;
10851 assert(Vec && "Can't find vectorizable value");
10852
10853 Value *Lane = Builder.getInt32(ExternalUse.Lane);
10854 auto ExtractAndExtendIfNeeded = [&](Value *Vec) {
10855 if (Scalar->getType() != Vec->getType()) {
10856 Value *Ex = nullptr;
10857 auto It = ScalarToEEs.find(Scalar);
10858 if (It != ScalarToEEs.end()) {
10859 // No need to emit many extracts, just move the only one in the
10860 // current block.
10861 auto EEIt = It->second.find(Builder.GetInsertBlock());
10862 if (EEIt != It->second.end()) {
10863 Instruction *I = EEIt->second;
10864 if (Builder.GetInsertPoint() != Builder.GetInsertBlock()->end() &&
10865 Builder.GetInsertPoint()->comesBefore(I))
10866 I->moveBefore(&*Builder.GetInsertPoint());
10867 Ex = I;
10868 }
10869 }
10870 if (!Ex) {
10871 // "Reuse" the existing extract to improve final codegen.
10872 if (auto *ES = dyn_cast<ExtractElementInst>(Scalar)) {
10873 Ex = Builder.CreateExtractElement(ES->getOperand(0),
10874 ES->getOperand(1));
10875 } else {
10876 Ex = Builder.CreateExtractElement(Vec, Lane);
10877 }
10878 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Ex))
10879 ScalarToEEs[Scalar].try_emplace(Builder.GetInsertBlock(), I);
10880 }
10881 // The then branch of the previous if may produce constants, since 0
10882 // operand might be a constant.
10883 if (auto *ExI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Ex)) {
10884 GatherShuffleExtractSeq.insert(ExI);
10885 CSEBlocks.insert(ExI->getParent());
10886 }
10887 // If necessary, sign-extend or zero-extend ScalarRoot
10888 // to the larger type.
10889 if (!MinBWs.count(ScalarRoot))
10890 return Ex;
10891 if (MinBWs[ScalarRoot].second)
10892 return Builder.CreateSExt(Ex, Scalar->getType());
10893 return Builder.CreateZExt(Ex, Scalar->getType());
10894 }
10895 assert(isa<FixedVectorType>(Scalar->getType()) &&
10896 isa<InsertElementInst>(Scalar) &&
10897 "In-tree scalar of vector type is not insertelement?");
10898 auto *IE = cast<InsertElementInst>(Scalar);
10899 VectorToInsertElement.try_emplace(Vec, IE);
10900 return Vec;
10901 };
10902 // If User == nullptr, the Scalar is used as extra arg. Generate
10903 // ExtractElement instruction and update the record for this scalar in
10904 // ExternallyUsedValues.
10905 if (!User) {
10906 assert(ExternallyUsedValues.count(Scalar) &&
10907 "Scalar with nullptr as an external user must be registered in "
10908 "ExternallyUsedValues map");
10909 if (auto *VecI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Vec)) {
10910 if (auto *PHI = dyn_cast<PHINode>(VecI))
10911 Builder.SetInsertPoint(PHI->getParent()->getFirstNonPHI());
10912 else
10913 Builder.SetInsertPoint(VecI->getParent(),
10914 std::next(VecI->getIterator()));
10915 } else {
10916 Builder.SetInsertPoint(&F->getEntryBlock().front());
10917 }
10918 Value *NewInst = ExtractAndExtendIfNeeded(Vec);
10919 // Required to update internally referenced instructions.
10920 Scalar->replaceAllUsesWith(NewInst);
10921 ReplacedExternals.emplace_back(Scalar, NewInst);
10922 continue;
10923 }
10924
10925 if (auto *VU = dyn_cast<InsertElementInst>(User)) {
10926 // Skip if the scalar is another vector op or Vec is not an instruction.
10927 if (!Scalar->getType()->isVectorTy() && isa<Instruction>(Vec)) {
10928 if (auto *FTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(User->getType())) {
10929 std::optional<unsigned> InsertIdx = getInsertIndex(VU);
10930 if (InsertIdx) {
10931 // Need to use original vector, if the root is truncated.
10932 if (MinBWs.count(Scalar) &&
10933 VectorizableTree[0]->VectorizedValue == Vec)
10934 Vec = VectorRoot;
10935 auto *It =
10936 find_if(ShuffledInserts, [VU](const ShuffledInsertData &Data) {
10937 // Checks if 2 insertelements are from the same buildvector.
10938 InsertElementInst *VecInsert = Data.InsertElements.front();
10939 return areTwoInsertFromSameBuildVector(
10940 VU, VecInsert,
10941 [](InsertElementInst *II) { return II->getOperand(0); });
10942 });
10943 unsigned Idx = *InsertIdx;
10944 if (It == ShuffledInserts.end()) {
10945 (void)ShuffledInserts.emplace_back();
10946 It = std::next(ShuffledInserts.begin(),
10947 ShuffledInserts.size() - 1);
10948 SmallVectorImpl<int> &Mask = It->ValueMasks[Vec];
10949 if (Mask.empty())
10950 Mask.assign(FTy->getNumElements(), PoisonMaskElem);
10951 // Find the insertvector, vectorized in tree, if any.
10952 Value *Base = VU;
10953 while (auto *IEBase = dyn_cast<InsertElementInst>(Base)) {
10954 if (IEBase != User &&
10955 (!IEBase->hasOneUse() ||
10956 getInsertIndex(IEBase).value_or(Idx) == Idx))
10957 break;
10958 // Build the mask for the vectorized insertelement instructions.
10959 if (const TreeEntry *E = getTreeEntry(IEBase)) {
10960 do {
10961 IEBase = cast<InsertElementInst>(Base);
10962 int IEIdx = *getInsertIndex(IEBase);
10963 assert(Mask[Idx] == PoisonMaskElem &&
10964 "InsertElementInstruction used already.");
10965 Mask[IEIdx] = IEIdx;
10966 Base = IEBase->getOperand(0);
10967 } while (E == getTreeEntry(Base));
10968 break;
10969 }
10970 Base = cast<InsertElementInst>(Base)->getOperand(0);
10971 // After the vectorization the def-use chain has changed, need
10972 // to look through original insertelement instructions, if they
10973 // get replaced by vector instructions.
10974 auto It = VectorToInsertElement.find(Base);
10975 if (It != VectorToInsertElement.end())
10976 Base = It->second;
10977 }
10978 }
10979 SmallVectorImpl<int> &Mask = It->ValueMasks[Vec];
10980 if (Mask.empty())
10981 Mask.assign(FTy->getNumElements(), PoisonMaskElem);
10982 Mask[Idx] = ExternalUse.Lane;
10983 It->InsertElements.push_back(cast<InsertElementInst>(User));
10984 continue;
10985 }
10986 }
10987 }
10988 }
10989
10990 // Generate extracts for out-of-tree users.
10991 // Find the insertion point for the extractelement lane.
10992 if (auto *VecI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Vec)) {
10993 if (PHINode *PH = dyn_cast<PHINode>(User)) {
10994 for (int i = 0, e = PH->getNumIncomingValues(); i != e; ++i) {
10995 if (PH->getIncomingValue(i) == Scalar) {
10996 Instruction *IncomingTerminator =
10997 PH->getIncomingBlock(i)->getTerminator();
10998 if (isa<CatchSwitchInst>(IncomingTerminator)) {
10999 Builder.SetInsertPoint(VecI->getParent(),
11000 std::next(VecI->getIterator()));
11001 } else {
11002 Builder.SetInsertPoint(PH->getIncomingBlock(i)->getTerminator());
11003 }
11004 Value *NewInst = ExtractAndExtendIfNeeded(Vec);
11005 PH->setOperand(i, NewInst);
11006 }
11007 }
11008 } else {
11009 Builder.SetInsertPoint(cast<Instruction>(User));
11010 Value *NewInst = ExtractAndExtendIfNeeded(Vec);
11011 User->replaceUsesOfWith(Scalar, NewInst);
11012 }
11013 } else {
11014 Builder.SetInsertPoint(&F->getEntryBlock().front());
11015 Value *NewInst = ExtractAndExtendIfNeeded(Vec);
11016 User->replaceUsesOfWith(Scalar, NewInst);
11017 }
11018
11019 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Replaced:" << *User << ".\n");
11020 }
11021
11022 auto CreateShuffle = [&](Value *V1, Value *V2, ArrayRef<int> Mask) {
11023 SmallVector<int> CombinedMask1(Mask.size(), PoisonMaskElem);
11024 SmallVector<int> CombinedMask2(Mask.size(), PoisonMaskElem);
11025 int VF = cast<FixedVectorType>(V1->getType())->getNumElements();
11026 for (int I = 0, E = Mask.size(); I < E; ++I) {
11027 if (Mask[I] < VF)
11028 CombinedMask1[I] = Mask[I];
11029 else
11030 CombinedMask2[I] = Mask[I] - VF;
11031 }
11032 ShuffleInstructionBuilder ShuffleBuilder(Builder, *this);
11033 ShuffleBuilder.add(V1, CombinedMask1);
11034 if (V2)
11035 ShuffleBuilder.add(V2, CombinedMask2);
11036 return ShuffleBuilder.finalize(std::nullopt);
11037 };
11038
11039 auto &&ResizeToVF = [&CreateShuffle](Value *Vec, ArrayRef<int> Mask,
11040 bool ForSingleMask) {
11041 unsigned VF = Mask.size();
11042 unsigned VecVF = cast<FixedVectorType>(Vec->getType())->getNumElements();
11043 if (VF != VecVF) {
11044 if (any_of(Mask, [VF](int Idx) { return Idx >= static_cast<int>(VF); })) {
11045 Vec = CreateShuffle(Vec, nullptr, Mask);
11046 return std::make_pair(Vec, true);
11047 }
11048 if (!ForSingleMask) {
11049 SmallVector<int> ResizeMask(VF, PoisonMaskElem);
11050 for (unsigned I = 0; I < VF; ++I) {
11051 if (Mask[I] != PoisonMaskElem)
11052 ResizeMask[Mask[I]] = Mask[I];
11053 }
11054 Vec = CreateShuffle(Vec, nullptr, ResizeMask);
11055 }
11056 }
11057
11058 return std::make_pair(Vec, false);
11059 };
11060 // Perform shuffling of the vectorize tree entries for better handling of
11061 // external extracts.
11062 for (int I = 0, E = ShuffledInserts.size(); I < E; ++I) {
11063 // Find the first and the last instruction in the list of insertelements.
11064 sort(ShuffledInserts[I].InsertElements, isFirstInsertElement);
11065 InsertElementInst *FirstInsert = ShuffledInserts[I].InsertElements.front();
11066 InsertElementInst *LastInsert = ShuffledInserts[I].InsertElements.back();
11067 Builder.SetInsertPoint(LastInsert);
11068 auto Vector = ShuffledInserts[I].ValueMasks.takeVector();
11069 Value *NewInst = performExtractsShuffleAction<Value>(
11070 MutableArrayRef(Vector.data(), Vector.size()),
11071 FirstInsert->getOperand(0),
11072 [](Value *Vec) {
11073 return cast<VectorType>(Vec->getType())
11074 ->getElementCount()
11075 .getKnownMinValue();
11076 },
11077 ResizeToVF,
11078 [FirstInsert, &CreateShuffle](ArrayRef<int> Mask,
11079 ArrayRef<Value *> Vals) {
11080 assert((Vals.size() == 1 || Vals.size() == 2) &&
11081 "Expected exactly 1 or 2 input values.");
11082 if (Vals.size() == 1) {
11083 // Do not create shuffle if the mask is a simple identity
11084 // non-resizing mask.
11085 if (Mask.size() != cast<FixedVectorType>(Vals.front()->getType())
11086 ->getNumElements() ||
11087 !ShuffleVectorInst::isIdentityMask(Mask))
11088 return CreateShuffle(Vals.front(), nullptr, Mask);
11089 return Vals.front();
11090 }
11091 return CreateShuffle(Vals.front() ? Vals.front()
11092 : FirstInsert->getOperand(0),
11093 Vals.back(), Mask);
11094 });
11095 auto It = ShuffledInserts[I].InsertElements.rbegin();
11096 // Rebuild buildvector chain.
11097 InsertElementInst *II = nullptr;
11098 if (It != ShuffledInserts[I].InsertElements.rend())
11099 II = *It;
11100 SmallVector<Instruction *> Inserts;
11101 while (It != ShuffledInserts[I].InsertElements.rend()) {
11102 assert(II && "Must be an insertelement instruction.");
11103 if (*It == II)
11104 ++It;
11105 else
11106 Inserts.push_back(cast<Instruction>(II));
11107 II = dyn_cast<InsertElementInst>(II->getOperand(0));
11108 }
11109 for (Instruction *II : reverse(Inserts)) {
11110 II->replaceUsesOfWith(II->getOperand(0), NewInst);
11111 if (auto *NewI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(NewInst))
11112 if (II->getParent() == NewI->getParent() && II->comesBefore(NewI))
11113 II->moveAfter(NewI);
11114 NewInst = II;
11115 }
11116 LastInsert->replaceAllUsesWith(NewInst);
11117 for (InsertElementInst *IE : reverse(ShuffledInserts[I].InsertElements)) {
11118 IE->replaceUsesOfWith(IE->getOperand(0),
11119 PoisonValue::get(IE->getOperand(0)->getType()));
11120 IE->replaceUsesOfWith(IE->getOperand(1),
11121 PoisonValue::get(IE->getOperand(1)->getType()));
11122 eraseInstruction(IE);
11123 }
11124 CSEBlocks.insert(LastInsert->getParent());
11125 }
11126
11127 SmallVector<Instruction *> RemovedInsts;
11128 // For each vectorized value:
11129 for (auto &TEPtr : VectorizableTree) {
11130 TreeEntry *Entry = TEPtr.get();
11131
11132 // No need to handle users of gathered values.
11133 if (Entry->State == TreeEntry::NeedToGather)
11134 continue;
11135
11136 assert(Entry->VectorizedValue && "Can't find vectorizable value");
11137
11138 // For each lane:
11139 for (int Lane = 0, LE = Entry->Scalars.size(); Lane != LE; ++Lane) {
11140 Value *Scalar = Entry->Scalars[Lane];
11141
11142 if (Entry->getOpcode() == Instruction::GetElementPtr &&
11143 !isa<GetElementPtrInst>(Scalar))
11144 continue;
11145#ifndef NDEBUG
11146 Type *Ty = Scalar->getType();
11147 if (!Ty->isVoidTy()) {
11148 for (User *U : Scalar->users()) {
11149 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: \tvalidating user:" << *U << ".\n");
11150
11151 // It is legal to delete users in the ignorelist.
11152 assert((getTreeEntry(U) ||
11153 (UserIgnoreList && UserIgnoreList->contains(U)) ||
11154 (isa_and_nonnull<Instruction>(U) &&
11155 isDeleted(cast<Instruction>(U)))) &&
11156 "Deleting out-of-tree value");
11157 }
11158 }
11159#endif
11160 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: \tErasing scalar:" << *Scalar << ".\n");
11161 eraseInstruction(cast<Instruction>(Scalar));
11162 // Retain to-be-deleted instructions for some debug-info
11163 // bookkeeping. NOTE: eraseInstruction only marks the instruction for
11164 // deletion - instructions are not deleted until later.
11165 RemovedInsts.push_back(cast<Instruction>(Scalar));
11166 }
11167 }
11168
11169 // Merge the DIAssignIDs from the about-to-be-deleted instructions into the
11170 // new vector instruction.
11171 if (auto *V = dyn_cast<Instruction>(VectorizableTree[0]->VectorizedValue))
11172 V->mergeDIAssignID(RemovedInsts);
11173
11174 Builder.ClearInsertionPoint();
11175 InstrElementSize.clear();
11176
11177 return VectorizableTree[0]->VectorizedValue;
11178}
11179
11180void BoUpSLP::optimizeGatherSequence() {
11181 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Optimizing " << GatherShuffleExtractSeq.size()
11182 << " gather sequences instructions.\n");
11183 // LICM InsertElementInst sequences.
11184 for (Instruction *I : GatherShuffleExtractSeq) {
11185 if (isDeleted(I))
11186 continue;
11187
11188 // Check if this block is inside a loop.
11189 Loop *L = LI->getLoopFor(I->getParent());
11190 if (!L)
11191 continue;
11192
11193 // Check if it has a preheader.
11194 BasicBlock *PreHeader = L->getLoopPreheader();
11195 if (!PreHeader)
11196 continue;
11197
11198 // If the vector or the element that we insert into it are
11199 // instructions that are defined in this basic block then we can't
11200 // hoist this instruction.
11201 if (any_of(I->operands(), [L](Value *V) {
11202 auto *OpI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V);
11203 return OpI && L->contains(OpI);
11204 }))
11205 continue;
11206
11207 // We can hoist this instruction. Move it to the pre-header.
11208 I->moveBefore(PreHeader->getTerminator());
11209 CSEBlocks.insert(PreHeader);
11210 }
11211
11212 // Make a list of all reachable blocks in our CSE queue.
11213 SmallVector<const DomTreeNode *, 8> CSEWorkList;
11214 CSEWorkList.reserve(CSEBlocks.size());
11215 for (BasicBlock *BB : CSEBlocks)
11216 if (DomTreeNode *N = DT->getNode(BB)) {
11217 assert(DT->isReachableFromEntry(N));
11218 CSEWorkList.push_back(N);
11219 }
11220
11221 // Sort blocks by domination. This ensures we visit a block after all blocks
11222 // dominating it are visited.
11223 llvm::sort(CSEWorkList, [](const DomTreeNode *A, const DomTreeNode *B) {
11224 assert((A == B) == (A->getDFSNumIn() == B->getDFSNumIn()) &&
11225 "Different nodes should have different DFS numbers");
11226 return A->getDFSNumIn() < B->getDFSNumIn();
11227 });
11228
11229 // Less defined shuffles can be replaced by the more defined copies.
11230 // Between two shuffles one is less defined if it has the same vector operands
11231 // and its mask indeces are the same as in the first one or undefs. E.g.
11232 // shuffle %0, poison, <0, 0, 0, undef> is less defined than shuffle %0,
11233 // poison, <0, 0, 0, 0>.
11234 auto &&IsIdenticalOrLessDefined = [this](Instruction *I1, Instruction *I2,
11235 SmallVectorImpl<int> &NewMask) {
11236 if (I1->getType() != I2->getType())
11237 return false;
11238 auto *SI1 = dyn_cast<ShuffleVectorInst>(I1);
11239 auto *SI2 = dyn_cast<ShuffleVectorInst>(I2);
11240 if (!SI1 || !SI2)
11241 return I1->isIdenticalTo(I2);
11242 if (SI1->isIdenticalTo(SI2))
11243 return true;
11244 for (int I = 0, E = SI1->getNumOperands(); I < E; ++I)
11245 if (SI1->getOperand(I) != SI2->getOperand(I))
11246 return false;
11247 // Check if the second instruction is more defined than the first one.
11248 NewMask.assign(SI2->getShuffleMask().begin(), SI2->getShuffleMask().end());
11249 ArrayRef<int> SM1 = SI1->getShuffleMask();
11250 // Count trailing undefs in the mask to check the final number of used
11251 // registers.
11252 unsigned LastUndefsCnt = 0;
11253 for (int I = 0, E = NewMask.size(); I < E; ++I) {
11254 if (SM1[I] == PoisonMaskElem)
11255 ++LastUndefsCnt;
11256 else
11257 LastUndefsCnt = 0;
11258 if (NewMask[I] != PoisonMaskElem && SM1[I] != PoisonMaskElem &&
11259 NewMask[I] != SM1[I])
11260 return false;
11261 if (NewMask[I] == PoisonMaskElem)
11262 NewMask[I] = SM1[I];
11263 }
11264 // Check if the last undefs actually change the final number of used vector
11265 // registers.
11266 return SM1.size() - LastUndefsCnt > 1 &&
11267 TTI->getNumberOfParts(SI1->getType()) ==
11268 TTI->getNumberOfParts(
11269 FixedVectorType::get(SI1->getType()->getElementType(),
11270 SM1.size() - LastUndefsCnt));
11271 };
11272 // Perform O(N^2) search over the gather/shuffle sequences and merge identical
11273 // instructions. TODO: We can further optimize this scan if we split the
11274 // instructions into different buckets based on the insert lane.
11275 SmallVector<Instruction *, 16> Visited;
11276 for (auto I = CSEWorkList.begin(), E = CSEWorkList.end(); I != E; ++I) {
11277 assert(*I &&
11278 (I == CSEWorkList.begin() || !DT->dominates(*I, *std::prev(I))) &&
11279 "Worklist not sorted properly!");
11280 BasicBlock *BB = (*I)->getBlock();
11281 // For all instructions in blocks containing gather sequences:
11282 for (Instruction &In : llvm::make_early_inc_range(*BB)) {
11283 if (isDeleted(&In))
11284 continue;
11285 if (!isa<InsertElementInst, ExtractElementInst, ShuffleVectorInst>(&In) &&
11286 !GatherShuffleExtractSeq.contains(&In))
11287 continue;
11288
11289 // Check if we can replace this instruction with any of the
11290 // visited instructions.
11291 bool Replaced = false;
11292 for (Instruction *&V : Visited) {
11293 SmallVector<int> NewMask;
11294 if (IsIdenticalOrLessDefined(&In, V, NewMask) &&
11295 DT->dominates(V->getParent(), In.getParent())) {
11296 In.replaceAllUsesWith(V);
11297 eraseInstruction(&In);
11298 if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<ShuffleVectorInst>(V))
11299 if (!NewMask.empty())
11300 SI->setShuffleMask(NewMask);
11301 Replaced = true;
11302 break;
11303 }
11304 if (isa<ShuffleVectorInst>(In) && isa<ShuffleVectorInst>(V) &&
11305 GatherShuffleExtractSeq.contains(V) &&
11306 IsIdenticalOrLessDefined(V, &In, NewMask) &&
11307 DT->dominates(In.getParent(), V->getParent())) {
11308 In.moveAfter(V);
11309 V->replaceAllUsesWith(&In);
11310 eraseInstruction(V);
11311 if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<ShuffleVectorInst>(&In))
11312 if (!NewMask.empty())
11313 SI->setShuffleMask(NewMask);
11314 V = &In;
11315 Replaced = true;
11316 break;
11317 }
11318 }
11319 if (!Replaced) {
11320 assert(!is_contained(Visited, &In));
11321 Visited.push_back(&In);
11322 }
11323 }
11324 }
11325 CSEBlocks.clear();
11326 GatherShuffleExtractSeq.clear();
11327}
11328
11329BoUpSLP::ScheduleData *
11330BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::buildBundle(ArrayRef<Value *> VL) {
11331 ScheduleData *Bundle = nullptr;
11332 ScheduleData *PrevInBundle = nullptr;
11333 for (Value *V : VL) {
11334 if (doesNotNeedToBeScheduled(V))
11335 continue;
11336 ScheduleData *BundleMember = getScheduleData(V);
11337 assert(BundleMember &&
11338 "no ScheduleData for bundle member "
11339 "(maybe not in same basic block)");
11340 assert(BundleMember->isSchedulingEntity() &&
11341 "bundle member already part of other bundle");
11342 if (PrevInBundle) {
11343 PrevInBundle->NextInBundle = BundleMember;
11344 } else {
11345 Bundle = BundleMember;
11346 }
11347
11348 // Group the instructions to a bundle.
11349 BundleMember->FirstInBundle = Bundle;
11350 PrevInBundle = BundleMember;
11351 }
11352 assert(Bundle && "Failed to find schedule bundle");
11353 return Bundle;
11354}
11355
11356// Groups the instructions to a bundle (which is then a single scheduling entity)
11357// and schedules instructions until the bundle gets ready.
11358std::optional<BoUpSLP::ScheduleData *>
11359BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::tryScheduleBundle(ArrayRef<Value *> VL, BoUpSLP *SLP,
11360 const InstructionsState &S) {
11361 // No need to schedule PHIs, insertelement, extractelement and extractvalue
11362 // instructions.
11363 if (isa<PHINode>(S.OpValue) || isVectorLikeInstWithConstOps(S.OpValue) ||
11364 doesNotNeedToSchedule(VL))
11365 return nullptr;
11366
11367 // Initialize the instruction bundle.
11368 Instruction *OldScheduleEnd = ScheduleEnd;
11369 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: bundle: " << *S.OpValue << "\n");
11370
11371 auto TryScheduleBundleImpl = [this, OldScheduleEnd, SLP](bool ReSchedule,
11372 ScheduleData *Bundle) {
11373 // The scheduling region got new instructions at the lower end (or it is a
11374 // new region for the first bundle). This makes it necessary to
11375 // recalculate all dependencies.
11376 // It is seldom that this needs to be done a second time after adding the
11377 // initial bundle to the region.
11378 if (ScheduleEnd != OldScheduleEnd) {
11379 for (auto *I = ScheduleStart; I != ScheduleEnd; I = I->getNextNode())
11380 doForAllOpcodes(I, [](ScheduleData *SD) { SD->clearDependencies(); });
11381 ReSchedule = true;
11382 }
11383 if (Bundle) {
11384 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: try schedule bundle " << *Bundle
11385 << " in block " << BB->getName() << "\n");
11386 calculateDependencies(Bundle, /*InsertInReadyList=*/true, SLP);
11387 }
11388
11389 if (ReSchedule) {
11390 resetSchedule();
11391 initialFillReadyList(ReadyInsts);
11392 }
11393
11394 // Now try to schedule the new bundle or (if no bundle) just calculate
11395 // dependencies. As soon as the bundle is "ready" it means that there are no
11396 // cyclic dependencies and we can schedule it. Note that's important that we
11397 // don't "schedule" the bundle yet (see cancelScheduling).
11398 while (((!Bundle && ReSchedule) || (Bundle && !Bundle->isReady())) &&
11399 !ReadyInsts.empty()) {
11400 ScheduleData *Picked = ReadyInsts.pop_back_val();
11401 assert(Picked->isSchedulingEntity() && Picked->isReady() &&
11402 "must be ready to schedule");
11403 schedule(Picked, ReadyInsts);
11404 }
11405 };
11406
11407 // Make sure that the scheduling region contains all
11408 // instructions of the bundle.
11409 for (Value *V : VL) {
11410 if (doesNotNeedToBeScheduled(V))
11411 continue;
11412 if (!extendSchedulingRegion(V, S)) {
11413 // If the scheduling region got new instructions at the lower end (or it
11414 // is a new region for the first bundle). This makes it necessary to
11415 // recalculate all dependencies.
11416 // Otherwise the compiler may crash trying to incorrectly calculate
11417 // dependencies and emit instruction in the wrong order at the actual
11418 // scheduling.
11419 TryScheduleBundleImpl(/*ReSchedule=*/false, nullptr);
11420 return std::nullopt;
11421 }
11422 }
11423
11424 bool ReSchedule = false;
11425 for (Value *V : VL) {
11426 if (doesNotNeedToBeScheduled(V))
11427 continue;
11428 ScheduleData *BundleMember = getScheduleData(V);
11429 assert(BundleMember &&
11430 "no ScheduleData for bundle member (maybe not in same basic block)");
11431
11432 // Make sure we don't leave the pieces of the bundle in the ready list when
11433 // whole bundle might not be ready.
11434 ReadyInsts.remove(BundleMember);
11435
11436 if (!BundleMember->IsScheduled)
11437 continue;
11438 // A bundle member was scheduled as single instruction before and now
11439 // needs to be scheduled as part of the bundle. We just get rid of the
11440 // existing schedule.
11441 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: reset schedule because " << *BundleMember
11442 << " was already scheduled\n");
11443 ReSchedule = true;
11444 }
11445
11446 auto *Bundle = buildBundle(VL);
11447 TryScheduleBundleImpl(ReSchedule, Bundle);
11448 if (!Bundle->isReady()) {
11449 cancelScheduling(VL, S.OpValue);
11450 return std::nullopt;
11451 }
11452 return Bundle;
11453}
11454
11455void BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::cancelScheduling(ArrayRef<Value *> VL,
11456 Value *OpValue) {
11457 if (isa<PHINode>(OpValue) || isVectorLikeInstWithConstOps(OpValue) ||
11458 doesNotNeedToSchedule(VL))
11459 return;
11460
11461 if (doesNotNeedToBeScheduled(OpValue))
11462 OpValue = *find_if_not(VL, doesNotNeedToBeScheduled);
11463 ScheduleData *Bundle = getScheduleData(OpValue);
11464 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: cancel scheduling of " << *Bundle << "\n");
11465 assert(!Bundle->IsScheduled &&
11466 "Can't cancel bundle which is already scheduled");
11467 assert(Bundle->isSchedulingEntity() &&
11468 (Bundle->isPartOfBundle() || needToScheduleSingleInstruction(VL)) &&
11469 "tried to unbundle something which is not a bundle");
11470
11471 // Remove the bundle from the ready list.
11472 if (Bundle->isReady())
11473 ReadyInsts.remove(Bundle);
11474
11475 // Un-bundle: make single instructions out of the bundle.
11476 ScheduleData *BundleMember = Bundle;
11477 while (BundleMember) {
11478 assert(BundleMember->FirstInBundle == Bundle && "corrupt bundle links");
11479 BundleMember->FirstInBundle = BundleMember;
11480 ScheduleData *Next = BundleMember->NextInBundle;
11481 BundleMember->NextInBundle = nullptr;
11482 BundleMember->TE = nullptr;
11483 if (BundleMember->unscheduledDepsInBundle() == 0) {
11484 ReadyInsts.insert(BundleMember);
11485 }
11486 BundleMember = Next;
11487 }
11488}
11489
11490BoUpSLP::ScheduleData *BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::allocateScheduleDataChunks() {
11491 // Allocate a new ScheduleData for the instruction.
11492 if (ChunkPos >= ChunkSize) {
11493 ScheduleDataChunks.push_back(std::make_unique<ScheduleData[]>(ChunkSize));
11494 ChunkPos = 0;
11495 }
11496 return &(ScheduleDataChunks.back()[ChunkPos++]);
11497}
11498
11499bool BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::extendSchedulingRegion(Value *V,
11500 const InstructionsState &S) {
11501 if (getScheduleData(V, isOneOf(S, V)))
11502 return true;
11503 Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V);
11504 assert(I && "bundle member must be an instruction");
11505 assert(!isa<PHINode>(I) && !isVectorLikeInstWithConstOps(I) &&
11506 !doesNotNeedToBeScheduled(I) &&
11507 "phi nodes/insertelements/extractelements/extractvalues don't need to "
11508 "be scheduled");
11509 auto &&CheckScheduleForI = [this, &S](Instruction *I) -> bool {
11510 ScheduleData *ISD = getScheduleData(I);
11511 if (!ISD)
11512 return false;
11513 assert(isInSchedulingRegion(ISD) &&
11514 "ScheduleData not in scheduling region");
11515 ScheduleData *SD = allocateScheduleDataChunks();
11516 SD->Inst = I;
11517 SD->init(SchedulingRegionID, S.OpValue);
11518 ExtraScheduleDataMap[I][S.OpValue] = SD;
11519 return true;
11520 };
11521 if (CheckScheduleForI(I))
11522 return true;
11523 if (!ScheduleStart) {
11524 // It's the first instruction in the new region.
11525 initScheduleData(I, I->getNextNode(), nullptr, nullptr);
11526 ScheduleStart = I;
11527 ScheduleEnd = I->getNextNode();
11528 if (isOneOf(S, I) != I)
11529 CheckScheduleForI(I);
11530 assert(ScheduleEnd && "tried to vectorize a terminator?");
11531 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: initialize schedule region to " << *I << "\n");
11532 return true;
11533 }
11534 // Search up and down at the same time, because we don't know if the new
11535 // instruction is above or below the existing scheduling region.
11536 // Ignore debug info (and other "AssumeLike" intrinsics) so that's not counted
11537 // against the budget. Otherwise debug info could affect codegen.
11538 BasicBlock::reverse_iterator UpIter =
11539 ++ScheduleStart->getIterator().getReverse();
11540 BasicBlock::reverse_iterator UpperEnd = BB->rend();
11541 BasicBlock::iterator DownIter = ScheduleEnd->getIterator();
11542 BasicBlock::iterator LowerEnd = BB->end();
11543 auto IsAssumeLikeIntr = [](const Instruction &I) {
11544 if (auto *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(&I))
11545 return II->isAssumeLikeIntrinsic();
11546 return false;
11547 };
11548 UpIter = std::find_if_not(UpIter, UpperEnd, IsAssumeLikeIntr);
11549 DownIter = std::find_if_not(DownIter, LowerEnd, IsAssumeLikeIntr);
11550 while (UpIter != UpperEnd && DownIter != LowerEnd && &*UpIter != I &&
11551 &*DownIter != I) {
11552 if (++ScheduleRegionSize > ScheduleRegionSizeLimit) {
11553 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: exceeded schedule region size limit\n");
11554 return false;
11555 }
11556
11557 ++UpIter;
11558 ++DownIter;
11559
11560 UpIter = std::find_if_not(UpIter, UpperEnd, IsAssumeLikeIntr);
11561 DownIter = std::find_if_not(DownIter, LowerEnd, IsAssumeLikeIntr);
11562 }
11563 if (DownIter == LowerEnd || (UpIter != UpperEnd && &*UpIter == I)) {
11564 assert(I->getParent() == ScheduleStart->getParent() &&
11565 "Instruction is in wrong basic block.");
11566 initScheduleData(I, ScheduleStart, nullptr, FirstLoadStoreInRegion);
11567 ScheduleStart = I;
11568 if (isOneOf(S, I) != I)
11569 CheckScheduleForI(I);
11570 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: extend schedule region start to " << *I
11571 << "\n");
11572 return true;
11573 }
11574 assert((UpIter == UpperEnd || (DownIter != LowerEnd && &*DownIter == I)) &&
11575 "Expected to reach top of the basic block or instruction down the "
11576 "lower end.");
11577 assert(I->getParent() == ScheduleEnd->getParent() &&
11578 "Instruction is in wrong basic block.");
11579 initScheduleData(ScheduleEnd, I->getNextNode(), LastLoadStoreInRegion,
11580 nullptr);
11581 ScheduleEnd = I->getNextNode();
11582 if (isOneOf(S, I) != I)
11583 CheckScheduleForI(I);
11584 assert(ScheduleEnd && "tried to vectorize a terminator?");
11585 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: extend schedule region end to " << *I << "\n");
11586 return true;
11587}
11588
11589void BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::initScheduleData(Instruction *FromI,
11590 Instruction *ToI,
11591 ScheduleData *PrevLoadStore,
11592 ScheduleData *NextLoadStore) {
11593 ScheduleData *CurrentLoadStore = PrevLoadStore;
11594 for (Instruction *I = FromI; I != ToI; I = I->getNextNode()) {
11595 // No need to allocate data for non-schedulable instructions.
11596 if (doesNotNeedToBeScheduled(I))
11597 continue;
11598 ScheduleData *SD = ScheduleDataMap.lookup(I);
11599 if (!SD) {
11600 SD = allocateScheduleDataChunks();
11601 ScheduleDataMap[I] = SD;
11602 SD->Inst = I;
11603 }
11604 assert(!isInSchedulingRegion(SD) &&
11605 "new ScheduleData already in scheduling region");
11606 SD->init(SchedulingRegionID, I);
11607
11608 if (I->mayReadOrWriteMemory() &&
11609 (!isa<IntrinsicInst>(I) ||
11610 (cast<IntrinsicInst>(I)->getIntrinsicID() != Intrinsic::sideeffect &&
11611 cast<IntrinsicInst>(I)->getIntrinsicID() !=
11612 Intrinsic::pseudoprobe))) {
11613 // Update the linked list of memory accessing instructions.
11614 if (CurrentLoadStore) {
11615 CurrentLoadStore->NextLoadStore = SD;
11616 } else {
11617 FirstLoadStoreInRegion = SD;
11618 }
11619 CurrentLoadStore = SD;
11620 }
11621
11622 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::stacksave>()) ||
11623 match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::stackrestore>()))
11624 RegionHasStackSave = true;
11625 }
11626 if (NextLoadStore) {
11627 if (CurrentLoadStore)
11628 CurrentLoadStore->NextLoadStore = NextLoadStore;
11629 } else {
11630 LastLoadStoreInRegion = CurrentLoadStore;
11631 }
11632}
11633
11634void BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::calculateDependencies(ScheduleData *SD,
11635 bool InsertInReadyList,
11636 BoUpSLP *SLP) {
11637 assert(SD->isSchedulingEntity());
11638
11639 SmallVector<ScheduleData *, 10> WorkList;
11640 WorkList.push_back(SD);
11641
11642 while (!WorkList.empty()) {
11643 ScheduleData *SD = WorkList.pop_back_val();
11644 for (ScheduleData *BundleMember = SD; BundleMember;
11645 BundleMember = BundleMember->NextInBundle) {
11646 assert(isInSchedulingRegion(BundleMember));
11647 if (BundleMember->hasValidDependencies())
11648 continue;
11649
11650 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: update deps of " << *BundleMember
11651 << "\n");
11652 BundleMember->Dependencies = 0;
11653 BundleMember->resetUnscheduledDeps();
11654
11655 // Handle def-use chain dependencies.
11656 if (BundleMember->OpValue != BundleMember->Inst) {
11657 if (ScheduleData *UseSD = getScheduleData(BundleMember->Inst)) {
11658 BundleMember->Dependencies++;
11659 ScheduleData *DestBundle = UseSD->FirstInBundle;
11660 if (!DestBundle->IsScheduled)
11661 BundleMember->incrementUnscheduledDeps(1);
11662 if (!DestBundle->hasValidDependencies())
11663 WorkList.push_back(DestBundle);
11664 }
11665 } else {
11666 for (User *U : BundleMember->Inst->users()) {
11667 if (ScheduleData *UseSD = getScheduleData(cast<Instruction>(U))) {
11668 BundleMember->Dependencies++;
11669 ScheduleData *DestBundle = UseSD->FirstInBundle;
11670 if (!DestBundle->IsScheduled)
11671 BundleMember->incrementUnscheduledDeps(1);
11672 if (!DestBundle->hasValidDependencies())
11673 WorkList.push_back(DestBundle);
11674 }
11675 }
11676 }
11677
11678 auto makeControlDependent = [&](Instruction *I) {
11679 auto *DepDest = getScheduleData(I);
11680 assert(DepDest && "must be in schedule window");
11681 DepDest->ControlDependencies.push_back(BundleMember);
11682 BundleMember->Dependencies++;
11683 ScheduleData *DestBundle = DepDest->FirstInBundle;
11684 if (!DestBundle->IsScheduled)
11685 BundleMember->incrementUnscheduledDeps(1);
11686 if (!DestBundle->hasValidDependencies())
11687 WorkList.push_back(DestBundle);
11688 };
11689
11690 // Any instruction which isn't safe to speculate at the beginning of the
11691 // block is control dependend on any early exit or non-willreturn call
11692 // which proceeds it.
11693 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(BundleMember->Inst)) {
11694 for (Instruction *I = BundleMember->Inst->getNextNode();
11695 I != ScheduleEnd; I = I->getNextNode()) {
11696 if (isSafeToSpeculativelyExecute(I, &*BB->begin(), SLP->AC))
11697 continue;
11698
11699 // Add the dependency
11700 makeControlDependent(I);
11701
11702 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(I))
11703 // Everything past here must be control dependent on I.
11704 break;
11705 }
11706 }
11707
11708 if (RegionHasStackSave) {
11709 // If we have an inalloc alloca instruction, it needs to be scheduled
11710 // after any preceeding stacksave. We also need to prevent any alloca
11711 // from reordering above a preceeding stackrestore.
11712 if (match(BundleMember->Inst, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::stacksave>()) ||
11713 match(BundleMember->Inst, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::stackrestore>())) {
