11714 for (Instruction *I = BundleMember->Inst->getNextNode();
11715 I != ScheduleEnd; I = I->getNextNode()) {
11716 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::stacksave>()) ||
11717 match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::stackrestore>()))
11718 // Any allocas past here must be control dependent on I, and I
11719 // must be memory dependend on BundleMember->Inst.
11720 break;
11721
11722 if (!isa<AllocaInst>(I))
11723 continue;
11724
11725 // Add the dependency
11726 makeControlDependent(I);
11727 }
11728 }
11729
11730 // In addition to the cases handle just above, we need to prevent
11731 // allocas and loads/stores from moving below a stacksave or a
11732 // stackrestore. Avoiding moving allocas below stackrestore is currently
11733 // thought to be conservatism. Moving loads/stores below a stackrestore
11734 // can lead to incorrect code.
11735 if (isa<AllocaInst>(BundleMember->Inst) ||
11736 BundleMember->Inst->mayReadOrWriteMemory()) {
11737 for (Instruction *I = BundleMember->Inst->getNextNode();
11738 I != ScheduleEnd; I = I->getNextNode()) {
11739 if (!match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::stacksave>()) &&
11740 !match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::stackrestore>()))
11741 continue;
11742
11743 // Add the dependency
11744 makeControlDependent(I);
11745 break;
11746 }
11747 }
11748 }
11749
11750 // Handle the memory dependencies (if any).
11751 ScheduleData *DepDest = BundleMember->NextLoadStore;
11752 if (!DepDest)
11753 continue;
11754 Instruction *SrcInst = BundleMember->Inst;
11755 assert(SrcInst->mayReadOrWriteMemory() &&
11756 "NextLoadStore list for non memory effecting bundle?");
11757 MemoryLocation SrcLoc = getLocation(SrcInst);
11758 bool SrcMayWrite = BundleMember->Inst->mayWriteToMemory();
11759 unsigned numAliased = 0;
11760 unsigned DistToSrc = 1;
11761
11762 for (; DepDest; DepDest = DepDest->NextLoadStore) {
11763 assert(isInSchedulingRegion(DepDest));
11764
11765 // We have two limits to reduce the complexity:
11766 // 1) AliasedCheckLimit: It's a small limit to reduce calls to
11767 // SLP->isAliased (which is the expensive part in this loop).
11768 // 2) MaxMemDepDistance: It's for very large blocks and it aborts
11769 // the whole loop (even if the loop is fast, it's quadratic).
11770 // It's important for the loop break condition (see below) to
11771 // check this limit even between two read-only instructions.
11772 if (DistToSrc >= MaxMemDepDistance ||
11773 ((SrcMayWrite || DepDest->Inst->mayWriteToMemory()) &&
11774 (numAliased >= AliasedCheckLimit ||
11775 SLP->isAliased(SrcLoc, SrcInst, DepDest->Inst)))) {
11776
11777 // We increment the counter only if the locations are aliased
11778 // (instead of counting all alias checks). This gives a better
11779 // balance between reduced runtime and accurate dependencies.
11780 numAliased++;
11781
11782 DepDest->MemoryDependencies.push_back(BundleMember);
11783 BundleMember->Dependencies++;
11784 ScheduleData *DestBundle = DepDest->FirstInBundle;
11785 if (!DestBundle->IsScheduled) {
11786 BundleMember->incrementUnscheduledDeps(1);
11787 }
11788 if (!DestBundle->hasValidDependencies()) {
11789 WorkList.push_back(DestBundle);
11790 }
11791 }
11792
11793 // Example, explaining the loop break condition: Let's assume our
11794 // starting instruction is i0 and MaxMemDepDistance = 3.
11795 //
11796 // +--------v--v--v
11797 // i0,i1,i2,i3,i4,i5,i6,i7,i8
11798 // +--------^--^--^
11799 //
11800 // MaxMemDepDistance let us stop alias-checking at i3 and we add
11801 // dependencies from i0 to i3,i4,.. (even if they are not aliased).
11802 // Previously we already added dependencies from i3 to i6,i7,i8
11803 // (because of MaxMemDepDistance). As we added a dependency from
11804 // i0 to i3, we have transitive dependencies from i0 to i6,i7,i8
11805 // and we can abort this loop at i6.
11806 if (DistToSrc >= 2 * MaxMemDepDistance)
11807 break;
11808 DistToSrc++;
11809 }
11810 }
11811 if (InsertInReadyList && SD->isReady()) {
11812 ReadyInsts.insert(SD);
11813 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: gets ready on update: " << *SD->Inst
11814 << "\n");
11815 }
11816 }
11817}
11818
11819void BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::resetSchedule() {
11820 assert(ScheduleStart &&
11821 "tried to reset schedule on block which has not been scheduled");
11822 for (Instruction *I = ScheduleStart; I != ScheduleEnd; I = I->getNextNode()) {
11823 doForAllOpcodes(I, [&](ScheduleData *SD) {
11824 assert(isInSchedulingRegion(SD) &&
11825 "ScheduleData not in scheduling region");
11826 SD->IsScheduled = false;
11827 SD->resetUnscheduledDeps();
11828 });
11829 }
11830 ReadyInsts.clear();
11831}
11832
11833void BoUpSLP::scheduleBlock(BlockScheduling *BS) {
11834 if (!BS->ScheduleStart)
11835 return;
11836
11837 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: schedule block " << BS->BB->getName() << "\n");
11838
11839 // A key point - if we got here, pre-scheduling was able to find a valid
11840 // scheduling of the sub-graph of the scheduling window which consists
11841 // of all vector bundles and their transitive users. As such, we do not
11842 // need to reschedule anything *outside of* that subgraph.
11843
11844 BS->resetSchedule();
11845
11846 // For the real scheduling we use a more sophisticated ready-list: it is
11847 // sorted by the original instruction location. This lets the final schedule
11848 // be as close as possible to the original instruction order.
11849 // WARNING: If changing this order causes a correctness issue, that means
11850 // there is some missing dependence edge in the schedule data graph.
11851 struct ScheduleDataCompare {
11852 bool operator()(ScheduleData *SD1, ScheduleData *SD2) const {
11853 return SD2->SchedulingPriority < SD1->SchedulingPriority;
11854 }
11855 };
11856 std::set<ScheduleData *, ScheduleDataCompare> ReadyInsts;
11857
11858 // Ensure that all dependency data is updated (for nodes in the sub-graph)
11859 // and fill the ready-list with initial instructions.
11860 int Idx = 0;
11861 for (auto *I = BS->ScheduleStart; I != BS->ScheduleEnd;
11862 I = I->getNextNode()) {
11863 BS->doForAllOpcodes(I, [this, &Idx, BS](ScheduleData *SD) {
11864 TreeEntry *SDTE = getTreeEntry(SD->Inst);
11865 (void)SDTE;
11866 assert((isVectorLikeInstWithConstOps(SD->Inst) ||
11867 SD->isPartOfBundle() ==
11868 (SDTE && !doesNotNeedToSchedule(SDTE->Scalars))) &&
11869 "scheduler and vectorizer bundle mismatch");
11870 SD->FirstInBundle->SchedulingPriority = Idx++;
11871
11872 if (SD->isSchedulingEntity() && SD->isPartOfBundle())
11873 BS->calculateDependencies(SD, false, this);
11874 });
11875 }
11876 BS->initialFillReadyList(ReadyInsts);
11877
11878 Instruction *LastScheduledInst = BS->ScheduleEnd;
11879
11880 // Do the "real" scheduling.
11881 while (!ReadyInsts.empty()) {
11882 ScheduleData *picked = *ReadyInsts.begin();
11883 ReadyInsts.erase(ReadyInsts.begin());
11884
11885 // Move the scheduled instruction(s) to their dedicated places, if not
11886 // there yet.
11887 for (ScheduleData *BundleMember = picked; BundleMember;
11888 BundleMember = BundleMember->NextInBundle) {
11889 Instruction *pickedInst = BundleMember->Inst;
11890 if (pickedInst->getNextNode() != LastScheduledInst)
11891 pickedInst->moveBefore(LastScheduledInst);
11892 LastScheduledInst = pickedInst;
11893 }
11894
11895 BS->schedule(picked, ReadyInsts);
11896 }
11897
11898 // Check that we didn't break any of our invariants.
11899#ifdef EXPENSIVE_CHECKS
11900 BS->verify();
11901#endif
11902
11903#if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(EXPENSIVE_CHECKS)
11904 // Check that all schedulable entities got scheduled
11905 for (auto *I = BS->ScheduleStart; I != BS->ScheduleEnd; I = I->getNextNode()) {
11906 BS->doForAllOpcodes(I, [&](ScheduleData *SD) {
11907 if (SD->isSchedulingEntity() && SD->hasValidDependencies()) {
11908 assert(SD->IsScheduled && "must be scheduled at this point");
11909 }
11910 });
11911 }
11912#endif
11913
11914 // Avoid duplicate scheduling of the block.
11915 BS->ScheduleStart = nullptr;
11916}
11917
11918unsigned BoUpSLP::getVectorElementSize(Value *V) {
11919 // If V is a store, just return the width of the stored value (or value
11920 // truncated just before storing) without traversing the expression tree.
11921 // This is the common case.
11922 if (auto *Store = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(V))
11923 return DL->getTypeSizeInBits(Store->getValueOperand()->getType());
11924
11925 if (auto *IEI = dyn_cast<InsertElementInst>(V))
11926 return getVectorElementSize(IEI->getOperand(1));
11927
11928 auto E = InstrElementSize.find(V);
11929 if (E != InstrElementSize.end())
11930 return E->second;
11931
11932 // If V is not a store, we can traverse the expression tree to find loads
11933 // that feed it. The type of the loaded value may indicate a more suitable
11934 // width than V's type. We want to base the vector element size on the width
11935 // of memory operations where possible.
11936 SmallVector<std::pair<Instruction *, BasicBlock *>, 16> Worklist;
11937 SmallPtrSet<Instruction *, 16> Visited;
11938 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {
11939 Worklist.emplace_back(I, I->getParent());
11940 Visited.insert(I);
11941 }
11942
11943 // Traverse the expression tree in bottom-up order looking for loads. If we
11944 // encounter an instruction we don't yet handle, we give up.
11945 auto Width = 0u;
11946 while (!Worklist.empty()) {
11947 Instruction *I;
11948 BasicBlock *Parent;
11949 std::tie(I, Parent) = Worklist.pop_back_val();
11950
11951 // We should only be looking at scalar instructions here. If the current
11952 // instruction has a vector type, skip.
11953 auto *Ty = I->getType();
11954 if (isa<VectorType>(Ty))
11955 continue;
11956
11957 // If the current instruction is a load, update MaxWidth to reflect the
11958 // width of the loaded value.
11959 if (isa<LoadInst, ExtractElementInst, ExtractValueInst>(I))
11960 Width = std::max<unsigned>(Width, DL->getTypeSizeInBits(Ty));
11961
11962 // Otherwise, we need to visit the operands of the instruction. We only
11963 // handle the interesting cases from buildTree here. If an operand is an
11964 // instruction we haven't yet visited and from the same basic block as the
11965 // user or the use is a PHI node, we add it to the worklist.
11966 else if (isa<PHINode, CastInst, GetElementPtrInst, CmpInst, SelectInst,
11967 BinaryOperator, UnaryOperator>(I)) {
11968 for (Use &U : I->operands())
11969 if (auto *J = dyn_cast<Instruction>(U.get()))
11970 if (Visited.insert(J).second &&
11971 (isa<PHINode>(I) || J->getParent() == Parent))
11972 Worklist.emplace_back(J, J->getParent());
11973 } else {
11974 break;
11975 }
11976 }
11977
11978 // If we didn't encounter a memory access in the expression tree, or if we
11979 // gave up for some reason, just return the width of V. Otherwise, return the
11980 // maximum width we found.
11981 if (!Width) {
11982 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(V))
11983 V = CI->getOperand(0);
11984 Width = DL->getTypeSizeInBits(V->getType());
11985 }
11986
11987 for (Instruction *I : Visited)
11988 InstrElementSize[I] = Width;
11989
11990 return Width;
11991}
11992
11993// Determine if a value V in a vectorizable expression Expr can be demoted to a
11994// smaller type with a truncation. We collect the values that will be demoted
11995// in ToDemote and additional roots that require investigating in Roots.
11996static bool collectValuesToDemote(Value *V, SmallPtrSetImpl<Value *> &Expr,
11997 SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &ToDemote,
11998 SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Roots) {
11999 // We can always demote constants.
12000 if (isa<Constant>(V)) {
12001 ToDemote.push_back(V);
12002 return true;
12003 }
12004
12005 // If the value is not an instruction in the expression with only one use, it
12006 // cannot be demoted.
12007 auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V);
12008 if (!I || !I->hasOneUse() || !Expr.count(I))
12009 return false;
12010
12011 switch (I->getOpcode()) {
12012
12013 // We can always demote truncations and extensions. Since truncations can
12014 // seed additional demotion, we save the truncated value.
12015 case Instruction::Trunc:
12016 Roots.push_back(I->getOperand(0));
12017 break;
12018 case Instruction::ZExt:
12019 case Instruction::SExt:
12020 if (isa<ExtractElementInst, InsertElementInst>(I->getOperand(0)))
12021 return false;
12022 break;
12023
12024 // We can demote certain binary operations if we can demote both of their
12025 // operands.
12026 case Instruction::Add:
12027 case Instruction::Sub:
12028 case Instruction::Mul:
12029 case Instruction::And:
12030 case Instruction::Or:
12031 case Instruction::Xor:
12032 if (!collectValuesToDemote(I->getOperand(0), Expr, ToDemote, Roots) ||
12033 !collectValuesToDemote(I->getOperand(1), Expr, ToDemote, Roots))
12034 return false;
12035 break;
12036
12037 // We can demote selects if we can demote their true and false values.
12038 case Instruction::Select: {
12039 SelectInst *SI = cast<SelectInst>(I);
12040 if (!collectValuesToDemote(SI->getTrueValue(), Expr, ToDemote, Roots) ||
12041 !collectValuesToDemote(SI->getFalseValue(), Expr, ToDemote, Roots))
12042 return false;
12043 break;
12044 }
12045
12046 // We can demote phis if we can demote all their incoming operands. Note that
12047 // we don't need to worry about cycles since we ensure single use above.
12048 case Instruction::PHI: {
12049 PHINode *PN = cast<PHINode>(I);
12050 for (Value *IncValue : PN->incoming_values())
12051 if (!collectValuesToDemote(IncValue, Expr, ToDemote, Roots))
12052 return false;
12053 break;
12054 }
12055
12056 // Otherwise, conservatively give up.
12057 default:
12058 return false;
12059 }
12060
12061 // Record the value that we can demote.
12062 ToDemote.push_back(V);
12063 return true;
12064}
12065
12066void BoUpSLP::computeMinimumValueSizes() {
12067 // If there are no external uses, the expression tree must be rooted by a
12068 // store. We can't demote in-memory values, so there is nothing to do here.
12069 if (ExternalUses.empty())
12070 return;
12071
12072 // We only attempt to truncate integer expressions.
12073 auto &TreeRoot = VectorizableTree[0]->Scalars;
12074 auto *TreeRootIT = dyn_cast<IntegerType>(TreeRoot[0]->getType());
12075 if (!TreeRootIT)
12076 return;
12077
12078 // If the expression is not rooted by a store, these roots should have
12079 // external uses. We will rely on InstCombine to rewrite the expression in
12080 // the narrower type. However, InstCombine only rewrites single-use values.
12081 // This means that if a tree entry other than a root is used externally, it
12082 // must have multiple uses and InstCombine will not rewrite it. The code
12083 // below ensures that only the roots are used externally.
12084 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 32> Expr(TreeRoot.begin(), TreeRoot.end());
12085 for (auto &EU : ExternalUses)
12086 if (!Expr.erase(EU.Scalar))
12087 return;
12088 if (!Expr.empty())
12089 return;
12090
12091 // Collect the scalar values of the vectorizable expression. We will use this
12092 // context to determine which values can be demoted. If we see a truncation,
12093 // we mark it as seeding another demotion.
12094 for (auto &EntryPtr : VectorizableTree)
12095 Expr.insert(EntryPtr->Scalars.begin(), EntryPtr->Scalars.end());
12096
12097 // Ensure the roots of the vectorizable tree don't form a cycle. They must
12098 // have a single external user that is not in the vectorizable tree.
12099 for (auto *Root : TreeRoot)
12100 if (!Root->hasOneUse() || Expr.count(*Root->user_begin()))
12101 return;
12102
12103 // Conservatively determine if we can actually truncate the roots of the
12104 // expression. Collect the values that can be demoted in ToDemote and
12105 // additional roots that require investigating in Roots.
12106 SmallVector<Value *, 32> ToDemote;
12107 SmallVector<Value *, 4> Roots;
12108 for (auto *Root : TreeRoot)
12109 if (!collectValuesToDemote(Root, Expr, ToDemote, Roots))
12110 return;
12111
12112 // The maximum bit width required to represent all the values that can be
12113 // demoted without loss of precision. It would be safe to truncate the roots
12114 // of the expression to this width.
12115 auto MaxBitWidth = 8u;
12116
12117 // We first check if all the bits of the roots are demanded. If they're not,
12118 // we can truncate the roots to this narrower type.
12119 for (auto *Root : TreeRoot) {
12120 auto Mask = DB->getDemandedBits(cast<Instruction>(Root));
12121 MaxBitWidth = std::max<unsigned>(Mask.getBitWidth() - Mask.countl_zero(),
12122 MaxBitWidth);
12123 }
12124
12125 // True if the roots can be zero-extended back to their original type, rather
12126 // than sign-extended. We know that if the leading bits are not demanded, we
12127 // can safely zero-extend. So we initialize IsKnownPositive to True.
12128 bool IsKnownPositive = true;
12129
12130 // If all the bits of the roots are demanded, we can try a little harder to
12131 // compute a narrower type. This can happen, for example, if the roots are
12132 // getelementptr indices. InstCombine promotes these indices to the pointer
12133 // width. Thus, all their bits are technically demanded even though the
12134 // address computation might be vectorized in a smaller type.
12135 //
12136 // We start by looking at each entry that can be demoted. We compute the
12137 // maximum bit width required to store the scalar by using ValueTracking to
12138 // compute the number of high-order bits we can truncate.
12139 if (MaxBitWidth == DL->getTypeSizeInBits(TreeRoot[0]->getType()) &&
12140 llvm::all_of(TreeRoot, [](Value *R) {
12141 assert(R->hasOneUse() && "Root should have only one use!");
12142 return isa<GetElementPtrInst>(R->user_back());
12143 })) {
12144 MaxBitWidth = 8u;
12145
12146 // Determine if the sign bit of all the roots is known to be zero. If not,
12147 // IsKnownPositive is set to False.
12148 IsKnownPositive = llvm::all_of(TreeRoot, [&](Value *R) {
12149 KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(R, *DL);
12150 return Known.isNonNegative();
12151 });
12152
12153 // Determine the maximum number of bits required to store the scalar
12154 // values.
12155 for (auto *Scalar : ToDemote) {
12156 auto NumSignBits = ComputeNumSignBits(Scalar, *DL, 0, AC, nullptr, DT);
12157 auto NumTypeBits = DL->getTypeSizeInBits(Scalar->getType());
12158 MaxBitWidth = std::max<unsigned>(NumTypeBits - NumSignBits, MaxBitWidth);
12159 }
12160
12161 // If we can't prove that the sign bit is zero, we must add one to the
12162 // maximum bit width to account for the unknown sign bit. This preserves
12163 // the existing sign bit so we can safely sign-extend the root back to the
12164 // original type. Otherwise, if we know the sign bit is zero, we will
12165 // zero-extend the root instead.
12166 //
12167 // FIXME: This is somewhat suboptimal, as there will be cases where adding
12168 // one to the maximum bit width will yield a larger-than-necessary
12169 // type. In general, we need to add an extra bit only if we can't
12170 // prove that the upper bit of the original type is equal to the
12171 // upper bit of the proposed smaller type. If these two bits are the
12172 // same (either zero or one) we know that sign-extending from the
12173 // smaller type will result in the same value. Here, since we can't
12174 // yet prove this, we are just making the proposed smaller type
12175 // larger to ensure correctness.
12176 if (!IsKnownPositive)
12177 ++MaxBitWidth;
12178 }
12179
12180 // Round MaxBitWidth up to the next power-of-two.
12181 MaxBitWidth = llvm::bit_ceil(MaxBitWidth);
12182
12183 // If the maximum bit width we compute is less than the with of the roots'
12184 // type, we can proceed with the narrowing. Otherwise, do nothing.
12185 if (MaxBitWidth >= TreeRootIT->getBitWidth())
12186 return;
12187
12188 // If we can truncate the root, we must collect additional values that might
12189 // be demoted as a result. That is, those seeded by truncations we will
12190 // modify.
12191 while (!Roots.empty())
12192 collectValuesToDemote(Roots.pop_back_val(), Expr, ToDemote, Roots);
12193
12194 // Finally, map the values we can demote to the maximum bit with we computed.
12195 for (auto *Scalar : ToDemote)
12196 MinBWs[Scalar] = std::make_pair(MaxBitWidth, !IsKnownPositive);
12197}
12198
12199PreservedAnalyses SLPVectorizerPass::run(Function &F, FunctionAnalysisManager &AM) {
12200 auto *SE = &AM.getResult<ScalarEvolutionAnalysis>(F);
12201 auto *TTI = &AM.getResult<TargetIRAnalysis>(F);
12202 auto *TLI = AM.getCachedResult<TargetLibraryAnalysis>(F);
12203 auto *AA = &AM.getResult<AAManager>(F);
12204 auto *LI = &AM.getResult<LoopAnalysis>(F);
12205 auto *DT = &AM.getResult<DominatorTreeAnalysis>(F);
12206 auto *AC = &AM.getResult<AssumptionAnalysis>(F);
12207 auto *DB = &AM.getResult<DemandedBitsAnalysis>(F);
12208 auto *ORE = &AM.getResult<OptimizationRemarkEmitterAnalysis>(F);
12209
12210 bool Changed = runImpl(F, SE, TTI, TLI, AA, LI, DT, AC, DB, ORE);
12211 if (!Changed)
12212 return PreservedAnalyses::all();
12213
12214 PreservedAnalyses PA;
12215 PA.preserveSet<CFGAnalyses>();
12216 return PA;
12217}
12218
12219bool SLPVectorizerPass::runImpl(Function &F, ScalarEvolution *SE_,
12220 TargetTransformInfo *TTI_,
12221 TargetLibraryInfo *TLI_, AAResults *AA_,
12222 LoopInfo *LI_, DominatorTree *DT_,
12223 AssumptionCache *AC_, DemandedBits *DB_,
12224 OptimizationRemarkEmitter *ORE_) {
12225 if (!RunSLPVectorization)
12226 return false;
12227 SE = SE_;
12228 TTI = TTI_;
12229 TLI = TLI_;
12230 AA = AA_;
12231 LI = LI_;
12232 DT = DT_;
12233 AC = AC_;
12234 DB = DB_;
12235 DL = &F.getParent()->getDataLayout();
12236
12237 Stores.clear();
12238 GEPs.clear();
12239 bool Changed = false;
12240
12241 // If the target claims to have no vector registers don't attempt
12242 // vectorization.
12243 if (!TTI->getNumberOfRegisters(TTI->getRegisterClassForType(true))) {
12244 LLVM_DEBUG(
12245 dbgs() << "SLP: Didn't find any vector registers for target, abort.\n");
12246 return false;
12247 }
12248
12249 // Don't vectorize when the attribute NoImplicitFloat is used.
12250 if (F.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::NoImplicitFloat))
12251 return false;
12252
12253 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Analyzing blocks in " << F.getName() << ".\n");
12254
12255 // Use the bottom up slp vectorizer to construct chains that start with
12256 // store instructions.
12257 BoUpSLP R(&F, SE, TTI, TLI, AA, LI, DT, AC, DB, DL, ORE_);
12258
12259 // A general note: the vectorizer must use BoUpSLP::eraseInstruction() to
12260 // delete instructions.
12261
12262 // Update DFS numbers now so that we can use them for ordering.
12263 DT->updateDFSNumbers();
12264
12265 // Scan the blocks in the function in post order.
12266 for (auto *BB : post_order(&F.getEntryBlock())) {
12267 // Start new block - clear the list of reduction roots.
12268 R.clearReductionData();
12269 collectSeedInstructions(BB);
12270
12271 // Vectorize trees that end at stores.
12272 if (!Stores.empty()) {
12273 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Found stores for " << Stores.size()
12274 << " underlying objects.\n");
12275 Changed |= vectorizeStoreChains(R);
12276 }
12277
12278 // Vectorize trees that end at reductions.
12279 Changed |= vectorizeChainsInBlock(BB, R);
12280
12281 // Vectorize the index computations of getelementptr instructions. This
12282 // is primarily intended to catch gather-like idioms ending at
12283 // non-consecutive loads.
12284 if (!GEPs.empty()) {
12285 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Found GEPs for " << GEPs.size()
12286 << " underlying objects.\n");
12287 Changed |= vectorizeGEPIndices(BB, R);
12288 }
12289 }
12290
12291 if (Changed) {
12292 R.optimizeGatherSequence();
12293 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: vectorized \"" << F.getName() << "\"\n");
12294 }
12295 return Changed;
12296}
12297
12298bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeStoreChain(ArrayRef<Value *> Chain, BoUpSLP &R,
12299 unsigned Idx, unsigned MinVF) {
12300 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Analyzing a store chain of length " << Chain.size()
12301 << "\n");
12302 const unsigned Sz = R.getVectorElementSize(Chain[0]);
12303 unsigned VF = Chain.size();
12304
12305 if (!isPowerOf2_32(Sz) || !isPowerOf2_32(VF) || VF < 2 || VF < MinVF)
12306 return false;
12307
12308 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Analyzing " << VF << " stores at offset " << Idx
12309 << "\n");
12310
12311 R.buildTree(Chain);
12312 if (R.isTreeTinyAndNotFullyVectorizable())
12313 return false;
12314 if (R.isLoadCombineCandidate())
12315 return false;
12316 R.reorderTopToBottom();
12317 R.reorderBottomToTop();
12318 R.buildExternalUses();
12319
12320 R.computeMinimumValueSizes();
12321
12322 InstructionCost Cost = R.getTreeCost();
12323
12324 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Found cost = " << Cost << " for VF=" << VF << "\n");
12325 if (Cost < -SLPCostThreshold) {
12326 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Decided to vectorize cost = " << Cost << "\n");
12327
12328 using namespace ore;
12329
12330 R.getORE()->emit(OptimizationRemark(SV_NAME, "StoresVectorized",
12331 cast<StoreInst>(Chain[0]))
12332 << "Stores SLP vectorized with cost " << NV("Cost", Cost)
12333 << " and with tree size "
12334 << NV("TreeSize", R.getTreeSize()));
12335
12336 R.vectorizeTree();
12337 return true;
12338 }
12339
12340 return false;
12341}
12342
12343bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeStores(ArrayRef<StoreInst *> Stores,
12344 BoUpSLP &R) {
12345 // We may run into multiple chains that merge into a single chain. We mark the
12346 // stores that we vectorized so that we don't visit the same store twice.
12347 BoUpSLP::ValueSet VectorizedStores;
12348 bool Changed = false;
12349
12350 int E = Stores.size();
12351 SmallBitVector Tails(E, false);
12352 int MaxIter = MaxStoreLookup.getValue();
12353 SmallVector<std::pair<int, int>, 16> ConsecutiveChain(
12354 E, std::make_pair(E, INT_MAX));
12355 SmallVector<SmallBitVector, 4> CheckedPairs(E, SmallBitVector(E, false));
12356 int IterCnt;
12357 auto &&FindConsecutiveAccess = [this, &Stores, &Tails, &IterCnt, MaxIter,
12358 &CheckedPairs,
12359 &ConsecutiveChain](int K, int Idx) {
12360 if (IterCnt >= MaxIter)
12361 return true;
12362 if (CheckedPairs[Idx].test(K))
12363 return ConsecutiveChain[K].second == 1 &&
12364 ConsecutiveChain[K].first == Idx;
12365 ++IterCnt;
12366 CheckedPairs[Idx].set(K);
12367 CheckedPairs[K].set(Idx);
12368 std::optional<int> Diff = getPointersDiff(
12369 Stores[K]->getValueOperand()->getType(), Stores[K]->getPointerOperand(),
12370 Stores[Idx]->getValueOperand()->getType(),
12371 Stores[Idx]->getPointerOperand(), *DL, *SE, /*StrictCheck=*/true);
12372 if (!Diff || *Diff == 0)
12373 return false;
12374 int Val = *Diff;
12375 if (Val < 0) {
12376 if (ConsecutiveChain[Idx].second > -Val) {
12377 Tails.set(K);
12378 ConsecutiveChain[Idx] = std::make_pair(K, -Val);
12379 }
12380 return false;
12381 }
12382 if (ConsecutiveChain[K].second <= Val)
12383 return false;
12384
12385 Tails.set(Idx);
12386 ConsecutiveChain[K] = std::make_pair(Idx, Val);
12387 return Val == 1;
12388 };
12389 // Do a quadratic search on all of the given stores in reverse order and find
12390 // all of the pairs of stores that follow each other.
12391 for (int Idx = E - 1; Idx >= 0; --Idx) {
12392 // If a store has multiple consecutive store candidates, search according
12393 // to the sequence: Idx-1, Idx+1, Idx-2, Idx+2, ...
12394 // This is because usually pairing with immediate succeeding or preceding
12395 // candidate create the best chance to find slp vectorization opportunity.
12396 const int MaxLookDepth = std::max(E - Idx, Idx + 1);
12397 IterCnt = 0;
12398 for (int Offset = 1, F = MaxLookDepth; Offset < F; ++Offset)
12399 if ((Idx >= Offset && FindConsecutiveAccess(Idx - Offset, Idx)) ||
12400 (Idx + Offset < E && FindConsecutiveAccess(Idx + Offset, Idx)))
12401 break;
12402 }
12403
12404 // Tracks if we tried to vectorize stores starting from the given tail
12405 // already.
12406 SmallBitVector TriedTails(E, false);
12407 // For stores that start but don't end a link in the chain:
12408 for (int Cnt = E; Cnt > 0; --Cnt) {
12409 int I = Cnt - 1;
12410 if (ConsecutiveChain[I].first == E || Tails.test(I))
12411 continue;
12412 // We found a store instr that starts a chain. Now follow the chain and try
12413 // to vectorize it.
12414 BoUpSLP::ValueList Operands;
12415 // Collect the chain into a list.
12416 while (I != E && !VectorizedStores.count(Stores[I])) {
12417 Operands.push_back(Stores[I]);
12418 Tails.set(I);
12419 if (ConsecutiveChain[I].second != 1) {
12420 // Mark the new end in the chain and go back, if required. It might be
12421 // required if the original stores come in reversed order, for example.
12422 if (ConsecutiveChain[I].first != E &&
12423 Tails.test(ConsecutiveChain[I].first) && !TriedTails.test(I) &&
12424 !VectorizedStores.count(Stores[ConsecutiveChain[I].first])) {
12425 TriedTails.set(I);
12426 Tails.reset(ConsecutiveChain[I].first);
12427 if (Cnt < ConsecutiveChain[I].first + 2)
12428 Cnt = ConsecutiveChain[I].first + 2;
12429 }
12430 break;
12431 }
12432 // Move to the next value in the chain.
12433 I = ConsecutiveChain[I].first;
12434 }
12435 assert(!Operands.empty() && "Expected non-empty list of stores.");
12436
12437 unsigned MaxVecRegSize = R.getMaxVecRegSize();
12438 unsigned EltSize = R.getVectorElementSize(Operands[0]);
12439 unsigned MaxElts = llvm::bit_floor(MaxVecRegSize / EltSize);
12440
12441 unsigned MaxVF = std::min(R.getMaximumVF(EltSize, Instruction::Store),
12442 MaxElts);
12443 auto *Store = cast<StoreInst>(Operands[0]);
12444 Type *StoreTy = Store->getValueOperand()->getType();
12445 Type *ValueTy = StoreTy;
12446 if (auto *Trunc = dyn_cast<TruncInst>(Store->getValueOperand()))
12447 ValueTy = Trunc->getSrcTy();
12448 unsigned MinVF = TTI->getStoreMinimumVF(
12449 R.getMinVF(DL->getTypeSizeInBits(ValueTy)), StoreTy, ValueTy);
12450
12451 if (MaxVF <= MinVF) {
12452 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Vectorization infeasible as MaxVF (" << MaxVF << ") <= "
12453 << "MinVF (" << MinVF << ")\n");
12454 }
12455
12456 // FIXME: Is division-by-2 the correct step? Should we assert that the
12457 // register size is a power-of-2?
12458 unsigned StartIdx = 0;
12459 for (unsigned Size = MaxVF; Size >= MinVF; Size /= 2) {
12460 for (unsigned Cnt = StartIdx, E = Operands.size(); Cnt + Size <= E;) {
12461 ArrayRef<Value *> Slice = ArrayRef(Operands).slice(Cnt, Size);
12462 if (!VectorizedStores.count(Slice.front()) &&
12463 !VectorizedStores.count(Slice.back()) &&
12464 vectorizeStoreChain(Slice, R, Cnt, MinVF)) {
12465 // Mark the vectorized stores so that we don't vectorize them again.
12466 VectorizedStores.insert(Slice.begin(), Slice.end());
12467 Changed = true;
12468 // If we vectorized initial block, no need to try to vectorize it
12469 // again.
12470 if (Cnt == StartIdx)
12471 StartIdx += Size;
12472 Cnt += Size;
12473 continue;
12474 }
12475 ++Cnt;
12476 }
12477 // Check if the whole array was vectorized already - exit.
12478 if (StartIdx >= Operands.size())
12479 break;
12480 }
12481 }
12482
12483 return Changed;
12484}
12485
12486void SLPVectorizerPass::collectSeedInstructions(BasicBlock *BB) {
12487 // Initialize the collections. We will make a single pass over the block.
12488 Stores.clear();
12489 GEPs.clear();
12490
12491 // Visit the store and getelementptr instructions in BB and organize them in
12492 // Stores and GEPs according to the underlying objects of their pointer
12493 // operands.
12494 for (Instruction &I : *BB) {
12495 // Ignore store instructions that are volatile or have a pointer operand
12496 // that doesn't point to a scalar type.
12497 if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(&I)) {
12498 if (!SI->isSimple())
12499 continue;
12500 if (!isValidElementType(SI->getValueOperand()->getType()))
12501 continue;
12502 Stores[getUnderlyingObject(SI->getPointerOperand())].push_back(SI);
12503 }
12504
12505 // Ignore getelementptr instructions that have more than one index, a
12506 // constant index, or a pointer operand that doesn't point to a scalar
12507 // type.
12508 else if (auto *GEP = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(&I)) {
12509 auto Idx = GEP->idx_begin()->get();
12510 if (GEP->getNumIndices() > 1 || isa<Constant>(Idx))
12511 continue;
12512 if (!isValidElementType(Idx->getType()))
12513 continue;
12514 if (GEP->getType()->isVectorTy())
12515 continue;
12516 GEPs[GEP->getPointerOperand()].push_back(GEP);
12517 }
12518 }
12519}
12520
12521bool SLPVectorizerPass::tryToVectorizeList(ArrayRef<Value *> VL, BoUpSLP &R,
12522 bool MaxVFOnly) {
12523 if (VL.size() < 2)
12524 return false;
12525
12526 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Trying to vectorize a list of length = "
12527 << VL.size() << ".\n");
12528
12529 // Check that all of the parts are instructions of the same type,
12530 // we permit an alternate opcode via InstructionsState.
12531 InstructionsState S = getSameOpcode(VL, *TLI);
12532 if (!S.getOpcode())
12533 return false;
12534
12535 Instruction *I0 = cast<Instruction>(S.OpValue);
12536 // Make sure invalid types (including vector type) are rejected before
12537 // determining vectorization factor for scalar instructions.
12538 for (Value *V : VL) {
12539 Type *Ty = V->getType();
12540 if (!isa<InsertElementInst>(V) && !isValidElementType(Ty)) {
12541 // NOTE: the following will give user internal llvm type name, which may
12542 // not be useful.
12543 R.getORE()->emit([&]() {
12544 std::string type_str;
12545 llvm::raw_string_ostream rso(type_str);
12546 Ty->print(rso);
12547 return OptimizationRemarkMissed(SV_NAME, "UnsupportedType", I0)
12548 << "Cannot SLP vectorize list: type "
12549 << rso.str() + " is unsupported by vectorizer";
12550 });
12551 return false;
12552 }
12553 }
12554
12555 unsigned Sz = R.getVectorElementSize(I0);
12556 unsigned MinVF = R.getMinVF(Sz);
12557 unsigned MaxVF = std::max<unsigned>(llvm::bit_floor(VL.size()), MinVF);
12558 MaxVF = std::min(R.getMaximumVF(Sz, S.getOpcode()), MaxVF);
12559 if (MaxVF < 2) {
12560 R.getORE()->emit([&]() {
12561 return OptimizationRemarkMissed(SV_NAME, "SmallVF", I0)
12562 << "Cannot SLP vectorize list: vectorization factor "
12563 << "less than 2 is not supported";
12564 });
12565 return false;
12566 }
12567
12568 bool Changed = false;
12569 bool CandidateFound = false;
12570 InstructionCost MinCost = SLPCostThreshold.getValue();
12571 Type *ScalarTy = VL[0]->getType();
12572 if (auto *IE = dyn_cast<InsertElementInst>(VL[0]))
12573 ScalarTy = IE->getOperand(1)->getType();
12574
12575 unsigned NextInst = 0, MaxInst = VL.size();
12576 for (unsigned VF = MaxVF; NextInst + 1 < MaxInst && VF >= MinVF; VF /= 2) {
12577 // No actual vectorization should happen, if number of parts is the same as
12578 // provided vectorization factor (i.e. the scalar type is used for vector
12579 // code during codegen).
12580 auto *VecTy = FixedVectorType::get(ScalarTy, VF);
12581 if (TTI->getNumberOfParts(VecTy) == VF)
12582 continue;
12583 for (unsigned I = NextInst; I < MaxInst; ++I) {
12584 unsigned ActualVF = std::min(MaxInst - I, VF);
12585
12586 if (!isPowerOf2_32(ActualVF))
12587 continue;
12588
12589 if (MaxVFOnly && ActualVF < MaxVF)
12590 break;
12591 if ((VF > MinVF && ActualVF <= VF / 2) || (VF == MinVF && ActualVF < 2))
12592 break;
12593
12594 ArrayRef<Value *> Ops = VL.slice(I, ActualVF);
12595 // Check that a previous iteration of this loop did not delete the Value.
12596 if (llvm::any_of(Ops, [&R](Value *V) {
12597 auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V);
12598 return I && R.isDeleted(I);
12599 }))
12600 continue;
12601
12602 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Analyzing " << ActualVF << " operations "
12603 << "\n");
12604
12605 R.buildTree(Ops);
12606 if (R.isTreeTinyAndNotFullyVectorizable())
12607 continue;
12608 R.reorderTopToBottom();
12609 R.reorderBottomToTop(
12610 /*IgnoreReorder=*/!isa<InsertElementInst>(Ops.front()) &&
12611 !R.doesRootHaveInTreeUses());
12612 R.buildExternalUses();
12613
12614 R.computeMinimumValueSizes();
12615 InstructionCost Cost = R.getTreeCost();
12616 CandidateFound = true;
12617 MinCost = std::min(MinCost, Cost);
12618
12619 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Found cost = " << Cost
12620 << " for VF=" << ActualVF << "\n");
12621 if (Cost < -SLPCostThreshold) {
12622 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Vectorizing list at cost:" << Cost << ".\n");
12623 R.getORE()->emit(OptimizationRemark(SV_NAME, "VectorizedList",
12624 cast<Instruction>(Ops[0]))
12625 << "SLP vectorized with cost " << ore::NV("Cost", Cost)
12626 << " and with tree size "
12627 << ore::NV("TreeSize", R.getTreeSize()));
12628
12629 R.vectorizeTree();
12630 // Move to the next bundle.
12631 I += VF - 1;
12632 NextInst = I + 1;
12633 Changed = true;
12634 }
12635 }
12636 }
12637
12638 if (!Changed && CandidateFound) {
12639 R.getORE()->emit([&]() {
12640 return OptimizationRemarkMissed(SV_NAME, "NotBeneficial", I0)
12641 << "List vectorization was possible but not beneficial with cost "
12642 << ore::NV("Cost", MinCost) << " >= "
12643 << ore::NV("Treshold", -SLPCostThreshold);
12644 });
12645 } else if (!Changed) {
12646 R.getORE()->emit([&]() {
12647 return OptimizationRemarkMissed(SV_NAME, "NotPossible", I0)
12648 << "Cannot SLP vectorize list: vectorization was impossible"
12649 << " with available vectorization factors";
12650 });
12651 }
12652 return Changed;
12653}
12654
12655bool SLPVectorizerPass::tryToVectorize(Instruction *I, BoUpSLP &R) {
12656 if (!I)
12657 return false;
12658
12659 if (!isa<BinaryOperator, CmpInst>(I) || isa<VectorType>(I->getType()))
12660 return false;
12661
12662 Value *P = I->getParent();
12663
12664 // Vectorize in current basic block only.
12665 auto *Op0 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(I->getOperand(0));
12666 auto *Op1 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(I->getOperand(1));
12667 if (!Op0 || !Op1 || Op0->getParent() != P || Op1->getParent() != P)
12668 return false;
12669
12670 // First collect all possible candidates
12671 SmallVector<std::pair<Value *, Value *>, 4> Candidates;
12672 Candidates.emplace_back(Op0, Op1);
12673
12674 auto *A = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(Op0);
12675 auto *B = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(Op1);
12676 // Try to skip B.
12677 if (A && B && B->hasOneUse()) {
12678 auto *B0 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(B->getOperand(0));
12679 auto *B1 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(B->getOperand(1));
12680 if (B0 && B0->getParent() == P)
12681 Candidates.emplace_back(A, B0);
12682 if (B1 && B1->getParent() == P)
12683 Candidates.emplace_back(A, B1);
12684 }
12685 // Try to skip A.
12686 if (B && A && A->hasOneUse()) {
12687 auto *A0 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(A->getOperand(0));
12688 auto *A1 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(A->getOperand(1));
12689 if (A0 && A0->getParent() == P)
12690 Candidates.emplace_back(A0, B);
12691 if (A1 && A1->getParent() == P)
12692 Candidates.emplace_back(A1, B);
12693 }
12694
12695 if (Candidates.size() == 1)
12696 return tryToVectorizeList({Op0, Op1}, R);
12697
12698 // We have multiple options. Try to pick the single best.
12699 std::optional<int> BestCandidate = R.findBestRootPair(Candidates);
12700 if (!BestCandidate)
12701 return false;
12702 return tryToVectorizeList(
12703 {Candidates[*BestCandidate].first, Candidates[*BestCandidate].second}, R);
12704}
12705
12706namespace {
12707
12708/// Model horizontal reductions.
12709///
12710/// A horizontal reduction is a tree of reduction instructions that has values
12711/// that can be put into a vector as its leaves. For example:
12712///
12713/// mul mul mul mul
12714/// \ / \ /
12715/// + +
12716/// \ /
12717/// +
12718/// This tree has "mul" as its leaf values and "+" as its reduction
12719/// instructions. A reduction can feed into a store or a binary operation
12720/// feeding a phi.
12721/// ...
12722/// \ /
12723/// +
12724/// |
12725/// phi +=
12726///
12727/// Or:
12728/// ...
12729/// \ /
12730/// +
12731/// |
12732/// *p =
12733///
12734class HorizontalReduction {
12735 using ReductionOpsType = SmallVector<Value *, 16>;
12736 using ReductionOpsListType = SmallVector<ReductionOpsType, 2>;
12737 ReductionOpsListType ReductionOps;
12738 /// List of possibly reduced values.
12739 SmallVector<SmallVector<Value *>> ReducedVals;
12740 /// Maps reduced value to the corresponding reduction operation.
12741 DenseMap<Value *, SmallVector<Instruction *>> ReducedValsToOps;
12742 // Use map vector to make stable output.
12743 MapVector<Instruction *, Value *> ExtraArgs;
12744 WeakTrackingVH ReductionRoot;
12745 /// The type of reduction operation.
12746 RecurKind RdxKind;
12747 /// Checks if the optimization of original scalar identity operations on
12748 /// matched horizontal reductions is enabled and allowed.
12749 bool IsSupportedHorRdxIdentityOp = false;
12750
12751 static bool isCmpSelMinMax(Instruction *I) {
12752 return match(I, m_Select(m_Cmp(), m_Value(), m_Value())) &&
12753 RecurrenceDescriptor::isMinMaxRecurrenceKind(getRdxKind(I));
12754 }
12755
12756 // And/or are potentially poison-safe logical patterns like:
12757 // select x, y, false
12758 // select x, true, y
12759 static bool isBoolLogicOp(Instruction *I) {
12760 return isa<SelectInst>(I) &&
12761 (match(I, m_LogicalAnd()) || match(I, m_LogicalOr()));
12762 }
12763
12764 /// Checks if instruction is associative and can be vectorized.
12765 static bool isVectorizable(RecurKind Kind, Instruction *I) {
12766 if (Kind == RecurKind::None)
12767 return false;
12768
12769 // Integer ops that map to select instructions or intrinsics are fine.
12770 if (RecurrenceDescriptor::isIntMinMaxRecurrenceKind(Kind) ||
12771 isBoolLogicOp(I))
12772 return true;
12773
12774 if (Kind == RecurKind::FMax || Kind == RecurKind::FMin) {
12775 // FP min/max are associative except for NaN and -0.0. We do not
12776 // have to rule out -0.0 here because the intrinsic semantics do not
12777 // specify a fixed result for it.
12778 return I->getFastMathFlags().noNaNs();
12779 }
12780
12781 if (Kind == RecurKind::FMaximum || Kind == RecurKind::FMinimum)
12782 return true;
12783
12784 return I->isAssociative();
12785 }
12786
12787 static Value *getRdxOperand(Instruction *I, unsigned Index) {
12788 // Poison-safe 'or' takes the form: select X, true, Y
12789 // To make that work with the normal operand processing, we skip the
12790 // true value operand.
12791 // TODO: Change the code and data structures to handle this without a hack.
12792 if (getRdxKind(I) == RecurKind::Or && isa<SelectInst>(I) && Index == 1)
12793 return I->getOperand(2);
12794 return I->getOperand(Index);
12795 }
12796
12797 /// Creates reduction operation with the current opcode.
12798 static Value *createOp(IRBuilder<> &Builder, RecurKind Kind, Value *LHS,
12799 Value *RHS, const Twine &Name, bool UseSelect) {
12800 unsigned RdxOpcode = RecurrenceDescriptor::getOpcode(Kind);
12801 bool IsConstant = isConstant(LHS) && isConstant(RHS);
12802 switch (Kind) {
12803 case RecurKind::Or:
12804 if (UseSelect &&
12805 LHS->getType() == CmpInst::makeCmpResultType(LHS->getType()))
12806 return Builder.CreateSelect(LHS, Builder.getTrue(), RHS, Name);
12807 return Builder.CreateBinOp((Instruction::BinaryOps)RdxOpcode, LHS, RHS,
12808 Name);
12809 case RecurKind::And:
12810 if (UseSelect &&
12811 LHS->getType() == CmpInst::makeCmpResultType(LHS->getType()))
12812 return Builder.CreateSelect(LHS, RHS, Builder.getFalse(), Name);
12813 return Builder.CreateBinOp((Instruction::BinaryOps)RdxOpcode, LHS, RHS,
12814 Name);
12815 case RecurKind::Add:
12816 case RecurKind::Mul:
12817 case RecurKind::Xor:
12818 case RecurKind::FAdd:
12819 case RecurKind::FMul:
12820 return Builder.CreateBinOp((Instruction::BinaryOps)RdxOpcode, LHS, RHS,
12821 Name);
12822 case RecurKind::FMax:
12823 if (IsConstant)
12824 return ConstantFP::get(LHS->getType(),
12825 maxnum(cast<ConstantFP>(LHS)->getValueAPF(),
12826 cast<ConstantFP>(RHS)->getValueAPF()));
12827 return Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::maxnum, LHS, RHS);
12828 case RecurKind::FMin:
12829 if (IsConstant)
12830 return ConstantFP::get(LHS->getType(),
12831 minnum(cast<ConstantFP>(LHS)->getValueAPF(),
12832 cast<ConstantFP>(RHS)->getValueAPF()));
12833 return Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::minnum, LHS, RHS);
12834 case RecurKind::FMaximum:
12835 if (IsConstant)
12836 return ConstantFP::get(LHS->getType(),
12837 maximum(cast<ConstantFP>(LHS)->getValueAPF(),
12838 cast<ConstantFP>(RHS)->getValueAPF()));
12839 return Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::maximum, LHS, RHS);
12840 case RecurKind::FMinimum:
12841 if (IsConstant)
12842 return ConstantFP::get(LHS->getType(),
12843 minimum(cast<ConstantFP>(LHS)->getValueAPF(),
12844 cast<ConstantFP>(RHS)->getValueAPF()));
12845 return Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::minimum, LHS, RHS);
12846 case RecurKind::SMax:
12847 if (IsConstant || UseSelect) {
12848 Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmpSGT(LHS, RHS, Name);
12849 return Builder.CreateSelect(Cmp, LHS, RHS, Name);
12850 }
12851 return Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::smax, LHS, RHS);
12852 case RecurKind::SMin:
12853 if (IsConstant || UseSelect) {
12854 Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmpSLT(LHS, RHS, Name);
12855 return Builder.CreateSelect(Cmp, LHS, RHS, Name);
12856 }
12857 return Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::smin, LHS, RHS);
12858 case RecurKind::UMax:
12859 if (IsConstant || UseSelect) {
12860 Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmpUGT(LHS, RHS, Name);
12861 return Builder.CreateSelect(Cmp, LHS, RHS, Name);
12862 }
12863 return Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::umax, LHS, RHS);
12864 case RecurKind::UMin:
12865 if (IsConstant || UseSelect) {
12866 Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmpULT(LHS, RHS, Name);
12867 return Builder.CreateSelect(Cmp, LHS, RHS, Name);
12868 }
12869 return Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::umin, LHS, RHS);
12870 default:
12871 llvm_unreachable("Unknown reduction operation.");
12872 }
12873 }
12874
12875 /// Creates reduction operation with the current opcode with the IR flags
12876 /// from \p ReductionOps, dropping nuw/nsw flags.
12877 static Value *createOp(IRBuilder<> &Builder, RecurKind RdxKind, Value *LHS,
12878 Value *RHS, const Twine &Name,
12879 const ReductionOpsListType &ReductionOps) {
12880 bool UseSelect = ReductionOps.size() == 2 ||
12881 // Logical or/and.
12882 (ReductionOps.size() == 1 &&
12883 isa<SelectInst>(ReductionOps.front().front()));
12884 assert((!UseSelect || ReductionOps.size() != 2 ||
12885 isa<SelectInst>(ReductionOps[1][0])) &&
12886 "Expected cmp + select pairs for reduction");
12887 Value *Op = createOp(Builder, RdxKind, LHS, RHS, Name, UseSelect);
12888 if (RecurrenceDescriptor::isIntMinMaxRecurrenceKind(RdxKind)) {
12889 if (auto *Sel = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(Op)) {
12890 propagateIRFlags(Sel->getCondition(), ReductionOps[0], nullptr,
12891 /*IncludeWrapFlags=*/false);
12892 propagateIRFlags(Op, ReductionOps[1], nullptr,
12893 /*IncludeWrapFlags=*/false);
12894 return Op;
12895 }
12896 }
12897 propagateIRFlags(Op, ReductionOps[0], nullptr, /*IncludeWrapFlags=*/false);
12898 return Op;
12899 }
12900
12901public:
12902 static RecurKind getRdxKind(Value *V) {
12903 auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V);
12904 if (!I)
12905 return RecurKind::None;
12906 if (match(I, m_Add(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12907 return RecurKind::Add;
12908 if (match(I, m_Mul(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12909 return RecurKind::Mul;
12910 if (match(I, m_And(m_Value(), m_Value())) ||
12911 match(I, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12912 return RecurKind::And;
12913 if (match(I, m_Or(m_Value(), m_Value())) ||
12914 match(I, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12915 return RecurKind::Or;
12916 if (match(I, m_Xor(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12917 return RecurKind::Xor;
12918 if (match(I, m_FAdd(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12919 return RecurKind::FAdd;
12920 if (match(I, m_FMul(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12921 return RecurKind::FMul;
12922
12923 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::maxnum>(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12924 return RecurKind::FMax;
12925 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::minnum>(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12926 return RecurKind::FMin;
12927
12928 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::maximum>(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12929 return RecurKind::FMaximum;
12930 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::minimum>(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12931 return RecurKind::FMinimum;
12932 // This matches either cmp+select or intrinsics. SLP is expected to handle
12933 // either form.
12934 // TODO: If we are canonicalizing to intrinsics, we can remove several
12935 // special-case paths that deal with selects.
12936 if (match(I, m_SMax(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12937 return RecurKind::SMax;
12938 if (match(I, m_SMin(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12939 return RecurKind::SMin;
12940 if (match(I, m_UMax(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12941 return RecurKind::UMax;
12942 if (match(I, m_UMin(m_Value(), m_Value())))
12943 return RecurKind::UMin;
12944
12945 if (auto *Select = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(I)) {
12946 // Try harder: look for min/max pattern based on instructions producing
12947 // same values such as: select ((cmp Inst1, Inst2), Inst1, Inst2).
12948 // During the intermediate stages of SLP, it's very common to have
12949 // pattern like this (since optimizeGatherSequence is run only once
12950 // at the end):
12951 // %1 = extractelement <2 x i32> %a, i32 0
12952 // %2 = extractelement <2 x i32> %a, i32 1
12953 // %cond = icmp sgt i32 %1, %2
12954 // %3 = extractelement <2 x i32> %a, i32 0
12955 // %4 = extractelement <2 x i32> %a, i32 1
12956 // %select = select i1 %cond, i32 %3, i32 %4
12957 CmpInst::Predicate Pred;
12958 Instruction *L1;
12959 Instruction *L2;
12960
12961 Value *LHS = Select->getTrueValue();
12962 Value *RHS = Select->getFalseValue();
12963 Value *Cond = Select->getCondition();
12964
12965 // TODO: Support inverse predicates.
12966 if (match(Cond, m_Cmp(Pred, m_Specific(LHS), m_Instruction(L2)))) {
12967 if (!isa<ExtractElementInst>(RHS) ||
12968 !L2->isIdenticalTo(cast<Instruction>(RHS)))
12969 return RecurKind::None;
12970 } else if (match(Cond, m_Cmp(Pred, m_Instruction(L1), m_Specific(RHS)))) {
12971 if (!isa<ExtractElementInst>(LHS) ||
12972 !L1->isIdenticalTo(cast<Instruction>(LHS)))
12973 return RecurKind::None;
12974 } else {
12975 if (!isa<ExtractElementInst>(LHS) || !isa<ExtractElementInst>(RHS))
12976 return RecurKind::None;
12977 if (!match(Cond, m_Cmp(Pred, m_Instruction(L1), m_Instruction(L2))) ||
12978 !L1->isIdenticalTo(cast<Instruction>(LHS)) ||
12979 !L2->isIdenticalTo(cast<Instruction>(RHS)))
12980 return RecurKind::None;
12981 }
12982
12983 switch (Pred) {
12984 default:
12985 return RecurKind::None;
12986 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
12987 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGE:
12988 return RecurKind::SMax;
12989 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
12990 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
12991 return RecurKind::SMin;
12992 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
12993 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
12994 return RecurKind::UMax;
12995 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
12996 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
12997 return RecurKind::UMin;
12998 }
12999 }
13000 return RecurKind::None;
13001 }
13002
13003 /// Get the index of the first operand.
13004 static unsigned getFirstOperandIndex(Instruction *I) {
13005 return isCmpSelMinMax(I) ? 1 : 0;
13006 }
13007
13008private:
13009 /// Total number of operands in the reduction operation.
13010 static unsigned getNumberOfOperands(Instruction *I) {
13011 return isCmpSelMinMax(I) ? 3 : 2;
13012 }
13013
13014 /// Checks if the instruction is in basic block \p BB.
13015 /// For a cmp+sel min/max reduction check that both ops are in \p BB.
13016 static bool hasSameParent(Instruction *I, BasicBlock *BB) {
13017 if (isCmpSelMinMax(I) || isBoolLogicOp(I)) {
13018 auto *Sel = cast<SelectInst>(I);
13019 auto *Cmp = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Sel->getCondition());
13020 return Sel->getParent() == BB && Cmp && Cmp->getParent() == BB;
13021 }
13022 return I->getParent() == BB;
13023 }
13024
13025 /// Expected number of uses for reduction operations/reduced values.
13026 static bool hasRequiredNumberOfUses(bool IsCmpSelMinMax, Instruction *I) {
13027 if (IsCmpSelMinMax) {
13028 // SelectInst must be used twice while the condition op must have single
13029 // use only.
13030 if (auto *Sel = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(I))
13031 return Sel->hasNUses(2) && Sel->getCondition()->hasOneUse();
13032 return I->hasNUses(2);
13033 }
13034
13035 // Arithmetic reduction operation must be used once only.
13036 return I->hasOneUse();
13037 }
13038
13039 /// Initializes the list of reduction operations.
13040 void initReductionOps(Instruction *I) {
13041 if (isCmpSelMinMax(I))
13042 ReductionOps.assign(2, ReductionOpsType());
13043 else
13044 ReductionOps.assign(1, ReductionOpsType());
13045 }
13046
13047 /// Add all reduction operations for the reduction instruction \p I.
13048 void addReductionOps(Instruction *I) {
13049 if (isCmpSelMinMax(I)) {
13050 ReductionOps[0].emplace_back(cast<SelectInst>(I)->getCondition());
13051 ReductionOps[1].emplace_back(I);
13052 } else {
13053 ReductionOps[0].emplace_back(I);
13054 }
13055 }
13056
13057 static bool isGoodForReduction(ArrayRef<Value *> Data) {
13058 int Sz = Data.size();
13059 auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Data.front());
13060 return Sz > 1 || isConstant(Data.front()) ||
13061 (I && !isa<LoadInst>(I) && isValidForAlternation(I->getOpcode()));
13062 }
13063
13064public:
13065 HorizontalReduction() = default;
13066
13067 /// Try to find a reduction tree.
13068 bool matchAssociativeReduction(BoUpSLP &R, Instruction *Root,
13069 ScalarEvolution &SE, const DataLayout &DL,
13070 const TargetLibraryInfo &TLI) {
13071 RdxKind = HorizontalReduction::getRdxKind(Root);
13072 if (!isVectorizable(RdxKind, Root))
13073 return false;
13074
13075 // Analyze "regular" integer/FP types for reductions - no target-specific
13076 // types or pointers.
13077 Type *Ty = Root->getType();
13078 if (!isValidElementType(Ty) || Ty->isPointerTy())
13079 return false;
13080
13081 // Though the ultimate reduction may have multiple uses, its condition must
13082 // have only single use.
13083 if (auto *Sel = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(Root))
13084 if (!Sel->getCondition()->hasOneUse())
13085 return false;
13086
13087 ReductionRoot = Root;
13088
13089 // Iterate through all the operands of the possible reduction tree and
13090 // gather all the reduced values, sorting them by their value id.
13091 BasicBlock *BB = Root->getParent();
13092 bool IsCmpSelMinMax = isCmpSelMinMax(Root);
13093 SmallVector<Instruction *> Worklist(1, Root);
13094 // Checks if the operands of the \p TreeN instruction are also reduction
13095 // operations or should be treated as reduced values or an extra argument,
13096 // which is not part of the reduction.
13097 auto CheckOperands = [&](Instruction *TreeN,
13098 SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &ExtraArgs,
13099 SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &PossibleReducedVals,
13100 SmallVectorImpl<Instruction *> &ReductionOps) {
13101 for (int I = getFirstOperandIndex(TreeN),
13102 End = getNumberOfOperands(TreeN);
13103 I < End; ++I) {
13104 Value *EdgeVal = getRdxOperand(TreeN, I);
13105 ReducedValsToOps[EdgeVal].push_back(TreeN);
13106 auto *EdgeInst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(EdgeVal);
13107 // Edge has wrong parent - mark as an extra argument.
13108 if (EdgeInst && !isVectorLikeInstWithConstOps(EdgeInst) &&
13109 !hasSameParent(EdgeInst, BB)) {
13110 ExtraArgs.push_back(EdgeVal);
13111 continue;
13112 }
13113 // If the edge is not an instruction, or it is different from the main
13114 // reduction opcode or has too many uses - possible reduced value.
13115 // Also, do not try to reduce const values, if the operation is not
13116 // foldable.
13117 if (!EdgeInst || getRdxKind(EdgeInst) != RdxKind ||
13118 IsCmpSelMinMax != isCmpSelMinMax(EdgeInst) ||
13119 !hasRequiredNumberOfUses(IsCmpSelMinMax, EdgeInst) ||
13120 !isVectorizable(RdxKind, EdgeInst) ||
13121 (R.isAnalyzedReductionRoot(EdgeInst) &&
13122 all_of(EdgeInst->operands(), Constant::classof))) {
13123 PossibleReducedVals.push_back(EdgeVal);
13124 continue;
13125 }
13126 ReductionOps.push_back(EdgeInst);
13127 }
13128 };
13129 // Try to regroup reduced values so that it gets more profitable to try to
13130 // reduce them. Values are grouped by their value ids, instructions - by
13131 // instruction op id and/or alternate op id, plus do extra analysis for
13132 // loads (grouping them by the distabce between pointers) and cmp
13133 // instructions (grouping them by the predicate).
13134 MapVector<size_t, MapVector<size_t, MapVector<Value *, unsigned>>>
13135 PossibleReducedVals;
13136 initReductionOps(Root);
13137 DenseMap<Value *, SmallVector<LoadInst *>> LoadsMap;
13138 SmallSet<size_t, 2> LoadKeyUsed;
13139 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 4> DoNotReverseVals;
13140
13141 auto GenerateLoadsSubkey = [&](size_t Key, LoadInst *LI) {
13142 Value *Ptr = getUnderlyingObject(LI->getPointerOperand());
13143 if (LoadKeyUsed.contains(Key)) {
13144 auto LIt = LoadsMap.find(Ptr);
13145 if (LIt != LoadsMap.end()) {
13146 for (LoadInst *RLI : LIt->second) {
13147 if (getPointersDiff(RLI->getType(), RLI->getPointerOperand(),
13148 LI->getType(), LI->getPointerOperand(), DL, SE,
13149 /*StrictCheck=*/true))
13150 return hash_value(RLI->getPointerOperand());
13151 }
13152 for (LoadInst *RLI : LIt->second) {
13153 if (arePointersCompatible(RLI->getPointerOperand(),
13154 LI->getPointerOperand(), TLI)) {
13155 hash_code SubKey = hash_value(RLI->getPointerOperand());
13156 DoNotReverseVals.insert(RLI);
13157 return SubKey;
13158 }
13159 }
13160 if (LIt->second.size() > 2) {
13161 hash_code SubKey =
13162 hash_value(LIt->second.back()->getPointerOperand());
13163 DoNotReverseVals.insert(LIt->second.back());
13164 return SubKey;
13165 }
13166 }
13167 }
13168 LoadKeyUsed.insert(Key);
13169 LoadsMap.try_emplace(Ptr).first->second.push_back(LI);
13170 return hash_value(LI->getPointerOperand());
13171 };
13172
13173 while (!Worklist.empty()) {
13174 Instruction *TreeN = Worklist.pop_back_val();
13175 SmallVector<Value *> Args;
13176 SmallVector<Value *> PossibleRedVals;
13177 SmallVector<Instruction *> PossibleReductionOps;
13178 CheckOperands(TreeN, Args, PossibleRedVals, PossibleReductionOps);
13179 // If too many extra args - mark the instruction itself as a reduction
13180 // value, not a reduction operation.
13181 if (Args.size() < 2) {
13182 addReductionOps(TreeN);
13183 // Add extra args.
13184 if (!Args.empty()) {
13185 assert(Args.size() == 1 && "Expected only single argument.");
13186 ExtraArgs[TreeN] = Args.front();
13187 }
13188 // Add reduction values. The values are sorted for better vectorization
13189 // results.
13190 for (Value *V : PossibleRedVals) {
13191 size_t Key, Idx;
13192 std::tie(Key, Idx) = generateKeySubkey(V, &TLI, GenerateLoadsSubkey,
13193 /*AllowAlternate=*/false);
13194 ++PossibleReducedVals[Key][Idx]
13195 .insert(std::make_pair(V, 0))
13196 .first->second;
13197 }
13198 Worklist.append(PossibleReductionOps.rbegin(),
13199 PossibleReductionOps.rend());
13200 } else {
13201 size_t Key, Idx;
13202 std::tie(Key, Idx) = generateKeySubkey(TreeN, &TLI, GenerateLoadsSubkey,
13203 /*AllowAlternate=*/false);
13204 ++PossibleReducedVals[Key][Idx]
13205 .insert(std::make_pair(TreeN, 0))
13206 .first->second;
13207 }
13208 }
13209 auto PossibleReducedValsVect = PossibleReducedVals.takeVector();
13210 // Sort values by the total number of values kinds to start the reduction
13211 // from the longest possible reduced values sequences.
13212 for (auto &PossibleReducedVals : PossibleReducedValsVect) {
13213 auto PossibleRedVals = PossibleReducedVals.second.takeVector();
13214 SmallVector<SmallVector<Value *>> PossibleRedValsVect;
13215 for (auto It = PossibleRedVals.begin(), E = PossibleRedVals.end();
13216 It != E; ++It) {
13217 PossibleRedValsVect.emplace_back();
13218 auto RedValsVect = It->second.takeVector();
13219 stable_sort(RedValsVect, llvm::less_second());
13220 for (const std::pair<Value *, unsigned> &Data : RedValsVect)
13221 PossibleRedValsVect.back().append(Data.second, Data.first);
13222 }
13223 stable_sort(PossibleRedValsVect, [](const auto &P1, const auto &P2) {
13224 return P1.size() > P2.size();
13225 });
13226 int NewIdx = -1;
13227 for (ArrayRef<Value *> Data : PossibleRedValsVect) {
13228 if (isGoodForReduction(Data) ||
13229 (isa<LoadInst>(Data.front()) && NewIdx >= 0 &&
13230 isa<LoadInst>(ReducedVals[NewIdx].front()) &&
13231 getUnderlyingObject(
13232 cast<LoadInst>(Data.front())->getPointerOperand()) ==
13233 getUnderlyingObject(cast<LoadInst>(ReducedVals[NewIdx].front())
13234 ->getPointerOperand()))) {
13235 if (NewIdx < 0) {
13236 NewIdx = ReducedVals.size();
13237 ReducedVals.emplace_back();
13238 }
13239 if (DoNotReverseVals.contains(Data.front()))
13240 ReducedVals[NewIdx].append(Data.begin(), Data.end());
13241 else
13242 ReducedVals[NewIdx].append(Data.rbegin(), Data.rend());
13243 } else {
13244 ReducedVals.emplace_back().append(Data.rbegin(), Data.rend());
13245 }
13246 }
13247 }
13248 // Sort the reduced values by number of same/alternate opcode and/or pointer
13249 // operand.
13250 stable_sort(ReducedVals, [](ArrayRef<Value *> P1, ArrayRef<Value *> P2) {
13251 return P1.size() > P2.size();
13252 });
13253 return true;
13254 }
13255
13256 /// Attempt to vectorize the tree found by matchAssociativeReduction.
13257 Value *tryToReduce(BoUpSLP &V, TargetTransformInfo *TTI,
13258 const TargetLibraryInfo &TLI) {
13259 constexpr int ReductionLimit = 4;
13260 constexpr unsigned RegMaxNumber = 4;
13261 constexpr unsigned RedValsMaxNumber = 128;
13262 // If there are a sufficient number of reduction values, reduce
13263 // to a nearby power-of-2. We can safely generate oversized
13264 // vectors and rely on the backend to split them to legal sizes.
13265 unsigned NumReducedVals =
13266 std::accumulate(ReducedVals.begin(), ReducedVals.end(), 0,
13267 [](unsigned Num, ArrayRef<Value *> Vals) -> unsigned {
13268 if (!isGoodForReduction(Vals))
13269 return Num;
13270 return Num + Vals.size();
13271 });
13272 if (NumReducedVals < ReductionLimit &&
13273 (!AllowHorRdxIdenityOptimization ||
13274 all_of(ReducedVals, [](ArrayRef<Value *> RedV) {
13275 return RedV.size() < 2 || !allConstant(RedV) || !isSplat(RedV);
13276 }))) {
13277 for (ReductionOpsType &RdxOps : ReductionOps)
13278 for (Value *RdxOp : RdxOps)
13279 V.analyzedReductionRoot(cast<Instruction>(RdxOp));
13280 return nullptr;
13281 }
13282
13283 IRBuilder<> Builder(cast<Instruction>(ReductionRoot));
13284
13285 // Track the reduced values in case if they are replaced by extractelement
13286 // because of the vectorization.
13287 DenseMap<Value *, WeakTrackingVH> TrackedVals(
13288 ReducedVals.size() * ReducedVals.front().size() + ExtraArgs.size());
13289 BoUpSLP::ExtraValueToDebugLocsMap ExternallyUsedValues;
13290 SmallVector<std::pair<Value *, Value *>> ReplacedExternals;
13291 ExternallyUsedValues.reserve(ExtraArgs.size() + 1);
13292 // The same extra argument may be used several times, so log each attempt
13293 // to use it.
13294 for (const std::pair<Instruction *, Value *> &Pair : ExtraArgs) {
13295 assert(Pair.first && "DebugLoc must be set.");
13296 ExternallyUsedValues[Pair.second].push_back(Pair.first);
13297 TrackedVals.try_emplace(Pair.second, Pair.second);
13298 }
13299
13300 // The compare instruction of a min/max is the insertion point for new
13301 // instructions and may be replaced with a new compare instruction.
13302 auto &&GetCmpForMinMaxReduction = [](Instruction *RdxRootInst) {
13303 assert(isa<SelectInst>(RdxRootInst) &&
13304 "Expected min/max reduction to have select root instruction");
13305 Value *ScalarCond = cast<SelectInst>(RdxRootInst)->getCondition();
13306 assert(isa<Instruction>(ScalarCond) &&
13307 "Expected min/max reduction to have compare condition");
13308 return cast<Instruction>(ScalarCond);
13309 };
13310
13311 // Return new VectorizedTree, based on previous value.
13312 auto GetNewVectorizedTree = [&](Value *VectorizedTree, Value *Res) {
13313 if (VectorizedTree) {
13314 // Update the final value in the reduction.
13315 Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(
13316 cast<Instruction>(ReductionOps.front().front())->getDebugLoc());
13317 return createOp(Builder, RdxKind, VectorizedTree, Res, "op.rdx",
13318 ReductionOps);
13319 }
13320 // Initialize the final value in the reduction.
13321 return Res;
13322 };
13323 // The reduction root is used as the insertion point for new instructions,
13324 // so set it as externally used to prevent it from being deleted.
13325 ExternallyUsedValues[ReductionRoot];
13326 SmallDenseSet<Value *> IgnoreList(ReductionOps.size() *
13327 ReductionOps.front().size());
13328 for (ReductionOpsType &RdxOps : ReductionOps)
13329 for (Value *RdxOp : RdxOps) {
13330 if (!RdxOp)
13331 continue;
13332 IgnoreList.insert(RdxOp);
13333 }
13334 // Intersect the fast-math-flags from all reduction operations.
13335 FastMathFlags RdxFMF;
13336 RdxFMF.set();
13337 for (Value *U : IgnoreList)
13338 if (auto *FPMO = dyn_cast<FPMathOperator>(U))
13339 RdxFMF &= FPMO->getFastMathFlags();
13340 bool IsCmpSelMinMax = isCmpSelMinMax(cast<Instruction>(ReductionRoot));
13341
13342 // Need to track reduced vals, they may be changed during vectorization of
13343 // subvectors.
13344 for (ArrayRef<Value *> Candidates : ReducedVals)
13345 for (Value *V : Candidates)
13346 TrackedVals.try_emplace(V, V);
13347
13348 DenseMap<Value *, unsigned> VectorizedVals(ReducedVals.size());
13349 // List of the values that were reduced in other trees as part of gather
13350 // nodes and thus requiring extract if fully vectorized in other trees.
13351 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 4> RequiredExtract;
13352 Value *VectorizedTree = nullptr;
13353 bool CheckForReusedReductionOps = false;
13354 // Try to vectorize elements based on their type.
13355 for (unsigned I = 0, E = ReducedVals.size(); I < E; ++I) {
13356 ArrayRef<Value *> OrigReducedVals = ReducedVals[I];
13357 InstructionsState S = getSameOpcode(OrigReducedVals, TLI);
13358 SmallVector<Value *> Candidates;
13359 Candidates.reserve(2 * OrigReducedVals.size());
13360 DenseMap<Value *, Value *> TrackedToOrig(2 * OrigReducedVals.size());
13361 for (unsigned Cnt = 0, Sz = OrigReducedVals.size(); Cnt < Sz; ++Cnt) {
13362 Value *RdxVal = TrackedVals.find(OrigReducedVals[Cnt])->second;
13363 // Check if the reduction value was not overriden by the extractelement
13364 // instruction because of the vectorization and exclude it, if it is not
13365 // compatible with other values.
13366 if (auto *Inst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(RdxVal))
13367 if (isVectorLikeInstWithConstOps(Inst) &&
13368 (!S.getOpcode() || !S.isOpcodeOrAlt(Inst)))
13369 continue;
13370 Candidates.push_back(RdxVal);
13371 TrackedToOrig.try_emplace(RdxVal, OrigReducedVals[Cnt]);
13372 }
13373 bool ShuffledExtracts = false;
13374 // Try to handle shuffled extractelements.
13375 if (S.getOpcode() == Instruction::ExtractElement && !S.isAltShuffle() &&
13376 I + 1 < E) {
13377 InstructionsState NextS = getSameOpcode(ReducedVals[I + 1], TLI);
13378 if (NextS.getOpcode() == Instruction::ExtractElement &&
13379 !NextS.isAltShuffle()) {
13380 SmallVector<Value *> CommonCandidates(Candidates);
13381 for (Value *RV : ReducedVals[I + 1]) {
13382 Value *RdxVal = TrackedVals.find(RV)->second;
13383 // Check if the reduction value was not overriden by the
13384 // extractelement instruction because of the vectorization and
13385 // exclude it, if it is not compatible with other values.
13386 if (auto *Inst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(RdxVal))
13387 if (!NextS.getOpcode() || !NextS.isOpcodeOrAlt(Inst))
13388 continue;
13389 CommonCandidates.push_back(RdxVal);
13390 TrackedToOrig.try_emplace(RdxVal, RV);
13391 }
13392 SmallVector<int> Mask;
13393 if (isFixedVectorShuffle(CommonCandidates, Mask)) {
13394 ++I;
13395 Candidates.swap(CommonCandidates);
13396 ShuffledExtracts = true;
13397 }
13398 }
13399 }
13400
13401 // Emit code for constant values.
13402 if (AllowHorRdxIdenityOptimization && Candidates.size() > 1 &&
13403 allConstant(Candidates)) {
13404 Value *Res = Candidates.front();
13405 ++VectorizedVals.try_emplace(Candidates.front(), 0).first->getSecond();
13406 for (Value *VC : ArrayRef(Candidates).drop_front()) {
13407 Res = createOp(Builder, RdxKind, Res, VC, "const.rdx", ReductionOps);
13408 ++VectorizedVals.try_emplace(VC, 0).first->getSecond();
13409 if (auto *ResI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Res))
13410 V.analyzedReductionRoot(ResI);
13411 }
13412 VectorizedTree = GetNewVectorizedTree(VectorizedTree, Res);
13413 continue;
13414 }
13415
13416 unsigned NumReducedVals = Candidates.size();
13417 if (NumReducedVals < ReductionLimit &&
13418 (NumReducedVals < 2 || !AllowHorRdxIdenityOptimization ||
13419 !isSplat(Candidates)))
13420 continue;
13421
13422 // Check if we support repeated scalar values processing (optimization of
13423 // original scalar identity operations on matched horizontal reductions).
13424 IsSupportedHorRdxIdentityOp =
13425 AllowHorRdxIdenityOptimization && RdxKind != RecurKind::Mul &&
13426 RdxKind != RecurKind::FMul && RdxKind != RecurKind::FMulAdd;
13427 // Gather same values.
13428 MapVector<Value *, unsigned> SameValuesCounter;
13429 if (IsSupportedHorRdxIdentityOp)
13430 for (Value *V : Candidates)
13431 ++SameValuesCounter.insert(std::make_pair(V, 0)).first->second;
13432 // Used to check if the reduced values used same number of times. In this
13433 // case the compiler may produce better code. E.g. if reduced values are
13434 // aabbccdd (8 x values), then the first node of the tree will have a node
13435 // for 4 x abcd + shuffle <4 x abcd>, <0, 0, 1, 1, 2, 2, 3, 3>.
13436 // Plus, the final reduction will be performed on <8 x aabbccdd>.
13437 // Instead compiler may build <4 x abcd> tree immediately, + reduction (4
13438 // x abcd) * 2.
13439 // Currently it only handles add/fadd/xor. and/or/min/max do not require
13440 // this analysis, other operations may require an extra estimation of
13441 // the profitability.
13442 bool SameScaleFactor = false;
13443 bool OptReusedScalars = IsSupportedHorRdxIdentityOp &&
13444 SameValuesCounter.size() != Candidates.size();
13445 if (OptReusedScalars) {
13446 SameScaleFactor =
13447 (RdxKind == RecurKind::Add || RdxKind == RecurKind::FAdd ||
13448 RdxKind == RecurKind::Xor) &&
13449 all_of(drop_begin(SameValuesCounter),
13450 [&SameValuesCounter](const std::pair<Value *, unsigned> &P) {
13451 return P.second == SameValuesCounter.front().second;
13452 });
13453 Candidates.resize(SameValuesCounter.size());
13454 transform(SameValuesCounter, Candidates.begin(),
13455 [](const auto &P) { return P.first; });
13456 NumReducedVals = Candidates.size();
13457 // Have a reduction of the same element.
13458 if (NumReducedVals == 1) {
13459 Value *OrigV = TrackedToOrig.find(Candidates.front())->second;
13460 unsigned Cnt = SameValuesCounter.lookup(OrigV);
13461 Value *RedVal =
13462 emitScaleForReusedOps(Candidates.front(), Builder, Cnt);
13463 VectorizedTree = GetNewVectorizedTree(VectorizedTree, RedVal);
13464 VectorizedVals.try_emplace(OrigV, Cnt);
13465 continue;
13466 }
13467 }
13468
13469 unsigned MaxVecRegSize = V.getMaxVecRegSize();
13470 unsigned EltSize = V.getVectorElementSize(Candidates[0]);
13471 unsigned MaxElts =
13472 RegMaxNumber * llvm::bit_floor(MaxVecRegSize / EltSize);
13473
13474 unsigned ReduxWidth = std::min<unsigned>(
13475 llvm::bit_floor(NumReducedVals), std::max(RedValsMaxNumber, MaxElts));
13476 unsigned Start = 0;
13477 unsigned Pos = Start;
13478 // Restarts vectorization attempt with lower vector factor.
13479 unsigned PrevReduxWidth = ReduxWidth;
13480 bool CheckForReusedReductionOpsLocal = false;
13481 auto &&AdjustReducedVals = [&Pos, &Start, &ReduxWidth, NumReducedVals,
13482 &CheckForReusedReductionOpsLocal,
13483 &PrevReduxWidth, &V,
13484 &IgnoreList](bool IgnoreVL = false) {
13485 bool IsAnyRedOpGathered = !IgnoreVL && V.isAnyGathered(IgnoreList);
13486 if (!CheckForReusedReductionOpsLocal && PrevReduxWidth == ReduxWidth) {
13487 // Check if any of the reduction ops are gathered. If so, worth
13488 // trying again with less number of reduction ops.
13489 CheckForReusedReductionOpsLocal |= IsAnyRedOpGathered;
13490 }
13491 ++Pos;
13492 if (Pos < NumReducedVals - ReduxWidth + 1)
13493 return IsAnyRedOpGathered;
13494 Pos = Start;
13495 ReduxWidth /= 2;
13496 return IsAnyRedOpGathered;
13497 };
13498 bool AnyVectorized = false;
13499 while (Pos < NumReducedVals - ReduxWidth + 1 &&
13500 ReduxWidth >= ReductionLimit) {
13501 // Dependency in tree of the reduction ops - drop this attempt, try
13502 // later.
13503 if (CheckForReusedReductionOpsLocal && PrevReduxWidth != ReduxWidth &&
13504 Start == 0) {
13505 CheckForReusedReductionOps = true;
13506 break;
13507 }
13508 PrevReduxWidth = ReduxWidth;
13509 ArrayRef<Value *> VL(std::next(Candidates.begin(), Pos), ReduxWidth);
13510 // Beeing analyzed already - skip.
13511 if (V.areAnalyzedReductionVals(VL)) {
13512 (void)AdjustReducedVals(/*IgnoreVL=*/true);
13513 continue;
13514 }
13515 // Early exit if any of the reduction values were deleted during
13516 // previous vectorization attempts.
13517 if (any_of(VL, [&V](Value *RedVal) {
13518 auto *RedValI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(RedVal);
13519 if (!RedValI)
13520 return false;
13521 return V.isDeleted(RedValI);
13522 }))
13523 break;
13524 V.buildTree(VL, IgnoreList);
13525 if (V.isTreeTinyAndNotFullyVectorizable(/*ForReduction=*/true)) {
13526 if (!AdjustReducedVals())
13527 V.analyzedReductionVals(VL);
13528 continue;
13529 }
13530 if (V.isLoadCombineReductionCandidate(RdxKind)) {
13531 if (!AdjustReducedVals())
13532 V.analyzedReductionVals(VL);
13533 continue;
13534 }
13535 V.reorderTopToBottom();
13536 // No need to reorder the root node at all.
13537 V.reorderBottomToTop(/*IgnoreReorder=*/true);
13538 // Keep extracted other reduction values, if they are used in the
13539 // vectorization trees.
13540 BoUpSLP::ExtraValueToDebugLocsMap LocalExternallyUsedValues(
13541 ExternallyUsedValues);
13542 for (unsigned Cnt = 0, Sz = ReducedVals.size(); Cnt < Sz; ++Cnt) {
13543 if (Cnt == I || (ShuffledExtracts && Cnt == I - 1))
13544 continue;
13545 for_each(ReducedVals[Cnt],
13546 [&LocalExternallyUsedValues, &TrackedVals](Value *V) {
13547 if (isa<Instruction>(V))
13548 LocalExternallyUsedValues[TrackedVals[V]];
13549 });
13550 }
13551 if (!IsSupportedHorRdxIdentityOp) {
13552 // Number of uses of the candidates in the vector of values.
13553 assert(SameValuesCounter.empty() &&
13554 "Reused values counter map is not empty");
13555 for (unsigned Cnt = 0; Cnt < NumReducedVals; ++Cnt) {
13556 if (Cnt >= Pos && Cnt < Pos + ReduxWidth)
13557 continue;
13558 Value *V = Candidates[Cnt];
13559 Value *OrigV = TrackedToOrig.find(V)->second;
13560 ++SameValuesCounter[OrigV];
13561 }
13562 }
13563 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 4> VLScalars(VL.begin(), VL.end());
13564 // Gather externally used values.
13565 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 4> Visited;
13566 for (unsigned Cnt = 0; Cnt < NumReducedVals; ++Cnt) {
13567 if (Cnt >= Pos && Cnt < Pos + ReduxWidth)
13568 continue;
13569 Value *RdxVal = Candidates[Cnt];
13570 if (!Visited.insert(RdxVal).second)
13571 continue;
13572 // Check if the scalar was vectorized as part of the vectorization
13573 // tree but not the top node.
13574 if (!VLScalars.contains(RdxVal) && V.isVectorized(RdxVal)) {
13575 LocalExternallyUsedValues[RdxVal];
13576 continue;
13577 }
13578 Value *OrigV = TrackedToOrig.find(RdxVal)->second;
13579 unsigned NumOps =
13580 VectorizedVals.lookup(RdxVal) + SameValuesCounter[OrigV];
13581 if (NumOps != ReducedValsToOps.find(OrigV)->second.size())
13582 LocalExternallyUsedValues[RdxVal];
13583 }
13584 // Do not need the list of reused scalars in regular mode anymore.
13585 if (!IsSupportedHorRdxIdentityOp)
13586 SameValuesCounter.clear();
13587 for (Value *RdxVal : VL)
13588 if (RequiredExtract.contains(RdxVal))
13589 LocalExternallyUsedValues[RdxVal];
13590 // Update LocalExternallyUsedValues for the scalar, replaced by
13591 // extractelement instructions.
13592 for (const std::pair<Value *, Value *> &Pair : ReplacedExternals) {
13593 auto It = ExternallyUsedValues.find(Pair.first);
13594 if (It == ExternallyUsedValues.end())
13595 continue;
13596 LocalExternallyUsedValues[Pair.second].append(It->second);
13597 }
13598 V.buildExternalUses(LocalExternallyUsedValues);
13599
13600 V.computeMinimumValueSizes();
13601
13602 // Estimate cost.
13603 InstructionCost TreeCost = V.getTreeCost(VL);
13604 InstructionCost ReductionCost =
13605 getReductionCost(TTI, VL, IsCmpSelMinMax, ReduxWidth, RdxFMF);
13606 InstructionCost Cost = TreeCost + ReductionCost;
13607 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Found cost = " << Cost << " for reduction\n");
13608 if (!Cost.isValid())
13609 return nullptr;
13610 if (Cost >= -SLPCostThreshold) {
13611 V.getORE()->emit([&]() {
13612 return OptimizationRemarkMissed(
13613 SV_NAME, "HorSLPNotBeneficial",
13614 ReducedValsToOps.find(VL[0])->second.front())
13615 << "Vectorizing horizontal reduction is possible "
13616 << "but not beneficial with cost " << ore::NV("Cost", Cost)
13617 << " and threshold "
13618 << ore::NV("Threshold", -SLPCostThreshold);
13619 });
13620 if (!AdjustReducedVals())
13621 V.analyzedReductionVals(VL);
13622 continue;
13623 }
13624
13625 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Vectorizing horizontal reduction at cost:"
13626 << Cost << ". (HorRdx)\n");
13627 V.getORE()->emit([&]() {
13628 return OptimizationRemark(
13629 SV_NAME, "VectorizedHorizontalReduction",
13630 ReducedValsToOps.find(VL[0])->second.front())
13631 << "Vectorized horizontal reduction with cost "
13632 << ore::NV("Cost", Cost) << " and with tree size "
13633 << ore::NV("TreeSize", V.getTreeSize());
13634 });
13635
13636 Builder.setFastMathFlags(RdxFMF);
13637
13638 // Emit a reduction. If the root is a select (min/max idiom), the insert
13639 // point is the compare condition of that select.
13640 Instruction *RdxRootInst = cast<Instruction>(ReductionRoot);
13641 Instruction *InsertPt = RdxRootInst;
13642 if (IsCmpSelMinMax)
13643 InsertPt = GetCmpForMinMaxReduction(RdxRootInst);
13644
13645 // Vectorize a tree.
13646 Value *VectorizedRoot = V.vectorizeTree(LocalExternallyUsedValues,
13647 ReplacedExternals, InsertPt);
13648
13649 Builder.SetInsertPoint(InsertPt);
13650
13651 // To prevent poison from leaking across what used to be sequential,
13652 // safe, scalar boolean logic operations, the reduction operand must be
13653 // frozen.
13654 if (isBoolLogicOp(RdxRootInst))
13655 VectorizedRoot = Builder.CreateFreeze(VectorizedRoot);
13656
13657 // Emit code to correctly handle reused reduced values, if required.
13658 if (OptReusedScalars && !SameScaleFactor) {
13659 VectorizedRoot =
13660 emitReusedOps(VectorizedRoot, Builder, V.getRootNodeScalars(),
13661 SameValuesCounter, TrackedToOrig);
13662 }
13663
13664 Value *ReducedSubTree =
13665 emitReduction(VectorizedRoot, Builder, ReduxWidth, TTI);
13666
13667 // Improved analysis for add/fadd/xor reductions with same scale factor
13668 // for all operands of reductions. We can emit scalar ops for them
13669 // instead.
13670 if (OptReusedScalars && SameScaleFactor)
13671 ReducedSubTree = emitScaleForReusedOps(
13672 ReducedSubTree, Builder, SameValuesCounter.front().second);
13673
13674 VectorizedTree = GetNewVectorizedTree(VectorizedTree, ReducedSubTree);
13675 // Count vectorized reduced values to exclude them from final reduction.
13676 for (Value *RdxVal : VL) {
13677 Value *OrigV = TrackedToOrig.find(RdxVal)->second;
13678 if (IsSupportedHorRdxIdentityOp) {
13679 VectorizedVals.try_emplace(OrigV, SameValuesCounter[RdxVal]);
13680 continue;
13681 }
13682 ++VectorizedVals.try_emplace(OrigV, 0).first->getSecond();
13683 if (!V.isVectorized(RdxVal))
13684 RequiredExtract.insert(RdxVal);
13685 }
13686 Pos += ReduxWidth;
13687 Start = Pos;
13688 ReduxWidth = llvm::bit_floor(NumReducedVals - Pos);
13689 AnyVectorized = true;
13690 }
13691 if (OptReusedScalars && !AnyVectorized) {
13692 for (const std::pair<Value *, unsigned> &P : SameValuesCounter) {
13693 Value *RedVal = emitScaleForReusedOps(P.first, Builder, P.second);
13694 VectorizedTree = GetNewVectorizedTree(VectorizedTree, RedVal);
13695 Value *OrigV = TrackedToOrig.find(P.first)->second;
13696 VectorizedVals.try_emplace(OrigV, P.second);
13697 }
13698 continue;
13699 }
13700 }
13701 if (VectorizedTree) {
13702 // Reorder operands of bool logical op in the natural order to avoid
