13703 // possible problem with poison propagation. If not possible to reorder
13704 // (both operands are originally RHS), emit an extra freeze instruction
13705 // for the LHS operand.
13706 // I.e., if we have original code like this:
13707 // RedOp1 = select i1 ?, i1 LHS, i1 false
13708 // RedOp2 = select i1 RHS, i1 ?, i1 false
13709
13710 // Then, we swap LHS/RHS to create a new op that matches the poison
13711 // semantics of the original code.
13712
13713 // If we have original code like this and both values could be poison:
13714 // RedOp1 = select i1 ?, i1 LHS, i1 false
13715 // RedOp2 = select i1 ?, i1 RHS, i1 false
13716
13717 // Then, we must freeze LHS in the new op.
13718 auto &&FixBoolLogicalOps =
13719 [&Builder, VectorizedTree](Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
13720 Instruction *RedOp1, Instruction *RedOp2) {
13721 if (!isBoolLogicOp(RedOp1))
13722 return;
13723 if (LHS == VectorizedTree || getRdxOperand(RedOp1, 0) == LHS ||
13724 isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(LHS))
13725 return;
13726 if (!isBoolLogicOp(RedOp2))
13727 return;
13728 if (RHS == VectorizedTree || getRdxOperand(RedOp2, 0) == RHS ||
13729 isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(RHS)) {
13730 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
13731 return;
13732 }
13733 LHS = Builder.CreateFreeze(LHS);
13734 };
13735 // Finish the reduction.
13736 // Need to add extra arguments and not vectorized possible reduction
13737 // values.
13738 // Try to avoid dependencies between the scalar remainders after
13739 // reductions.
13740 auto &&FinalGen =
13741 [this, &Builder, &TrackedVals, &FixBoolLogicalOps](
13742 ArrayRef<std::pair<Instruction *, Value *>> InstVals) {
13743 unsigned Sz = InstVals.size();
13744 SmallVector<std::pair<Instruction *, Value *>> ExtraReds(Sz / 2 +
13745 Sz % 2);
13746 for (unsigned I = 0, E = (Sz / 2) * 2; I < E; I += 2) {
13747 Instruction *RedOp = InstVals[I + 1].first;
13748 Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(RedOp->getDebugLoc());
13749 Value *RdxVal1 = InstVals[I].second;
13750 Value *StableRdxVal1 = RdxVal1;
13751 auto It1 = TrackedVals.find(RdxVal1);
13752 if (It1 != TrackedVals.end())
13753 StableRdxVal1 = It1->second;
13754 Value *RdxVal2 = InstVals[I + 1].second;
13755 Value *StableRdxVal2 = RdxVal2;
13756 auto It2 = TrackedVals.find(RdxVal2);
13757 if (It2 != TrackedVals.end())
13758 StableRdxVal2 = It2->second;
13759 // To prevent poison from leaking across what used to be
13760 // sequential, safe, scalar boolean logic operations, the
13761 // reduction operand must be frozen.
13762 FixBoolLogicalOps(StableRdxVal1, StableRdxVal2, InstVals[I].first,
13763 RedOp);
13764 Value *ExtraRed = createOp(Builder, RdxKind, StableRdxVal1,
13765 StableRdxVal2, "op.rdx", ReductionOps);
13766 ExtraReds[I / 2] = std::make_pair(InstVals[I].first, ExtraRed);
13767 }
13768 if (Sz % 2 == 1)
13769 ExtraReds[Sz / 2] = InstVals.back();
13770 return ExtraReds;
13771 };
13772 SmallVector<std::pair<Instruction *, Value *>> ExtraReductions;
13773 ExtraReductions.emplace_back(cast<Instruction>(ReductionRoot),
13774 VectorizedTree);
13775 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 8> Visited;
13776 for (ArrayRef<Value *> Candidates : ReducedVals) {
13777 for (Value *RdxVal : Candidates) {
13778 if (!Visited.insert(RdxVal).second)
13779 continue;
13780 unsigned NumOps = VectorizedVals.lookup(RdxVal);
13781 for (Instruction *RedOp :
13782 ArrayRef(ReducedValsToOps.find(RdxVal)->second)
13783 .drop_back(NumOps))
13784 ExtraReductions.emplace_back(RedOp, RdxVal);
13785 }
13786 }
13787 for (auto &Pair : ExternallyUsedValues) {
13788 // Add each externally used value to the final reduction.
13789 for (auto *I : Pair.second)
13790 ExtraReductions.emplace_back(I, Pair.first);
13791 }
13792 // Iterate through all not-vectorized reduction values/extra arguments.
13793 while (ExtraReductions.size() > 1) {
13794 VectorizedTree = ExtraReductions.front().second;
13795 SmallVector<std::pair<Instruction *, Value *>> NewReds =
13796 FinalGen(ExtraReductions);
13797 ExtraReductions.swap(NewReds);
13798 }
13799 VectorizedTree = ExtraReductions.front().second;
13800
13801 ReductionRoot->replaceAllUsesWith(VectorizedTree);
13802
13803 // The original scalar reduction is expected to have no remaining
13804 // uses outside the reduction tree itself. Assert that we got this
13805 // correct, replace internal uses with undef, and mark for eventual
13806 // deletion.
13807#ifndef NDEBUG
13808 SmallSet<Value *, 4> IgnoreSet;
13809 for (ArrayRef<Value *> RdxOps : ReductionOps)
13810 IgnoreSet.insert(RdxOps.begin(), RdxOps.end());
13811#endif
13812 for (ArrayRef<Value *> RdxOps : ReductionOps) {
13813 for (Value *Ignore : RdxOps) {
13814 if (!Ignore)
13815 continue;
13816#ifndef NDEBUG
13817 for (auto *U : Ignore->users()) {
13818 assert(IgnoreSet.count(U) &&
13819 "All users must be either in the reduction ops list.");
13820 }
13821#endif
13822 if (!Ignore->use_empty()) {
13823 Value *Undef = UndefValue::get(Ignore->getType());
13824 Ignore->replaceAllUsesWith(Undef);
13825 }
13826 V.eraseInstruction(cast<Instruction>(Ignore));
13827 }
13828 }
13829 } else if (!CheckForReusedReductionOps) {
13830 for (ReductionOpsType &RdxOps : ReductionOps)
13831 for (Value *RdxOp : RdxOps)
13832 V.analyzedReductionRoot(cast<Instruction>(RdxOp));
13833 }
13834 return VectorizedTree;
13835 }
13836
13837private:
13838 /// Calculate the cost of a reduction.
13839 InstructionCost getReductionCost(TargetTransformInfo *TTI,
13840 ArrayRef<Value *> ReducedVals,
13841 bool IsCmpSelMinMax, unsigned ReduxWidth,
13842 FastMathFlags FMF) {
13843 TTI::TargetCostKind CostKind = TTI::TCK_RecipThroughput;
13844 Value *FirstReducedVal = ReducedVals.front();
13845 Type *ScalarTy = FirstReducedVal->getType();
13846 FixedVectorType *VectorTy = FixedVectorType::get(ScalarTy, ReduxWidth);
13847 InstructionCost VectorCost = 0, ScalarCost;
13848 // If all of the reduced values are constant, the vector cost is 0, since
13849 // the reduction value can be calculated at the compile time.
13850 bool AllConsts = allConstant(ReducedVals);
13851 auto EvaluateScalarCost = [&](function_ref<InstructionCost()> GenCostFn) {
13852 InstructionCost Cost = 0;
13853 // Scalar cost is repeated for N-1 elements.
13854 int Cnt = ReducedVals.size();
13855 for (Value *RdxVal : ReducedVals) {
13856 if (Cnt == 1)
13857 break;
13858 --Cnt;
13859 if (RdxVal->hasNUsesOrMore(IsCmpSelMinMax ? 3 : 2)) {
13860 Cost += GenCostFn();
13861 continue;
13862 }
13863 InstructionCost ScalarCost = 0;
13864 for (User *U : RdxVal->users()) {
13865 auto *RdxOp = cast<Instruction>(U);
13866 if (hasRequiredNumberOfUses(IsCmpSelMinMax, RdxOp)) {
13867 ScalarCost += TTI->getInstructionCost(RdxOp, CostKind);
13868 continue;
13869 }
13870 ScalarCost = InstructionCost::getInvalid();
13871 break;
13872 }
13873 if (ScalarCost.isValid())
13874 Cost += ScalarCost;
13875 else
13876 Cost += GenCostFn();
13877 }
13878 return Cost;
13879 };
13880 switch (RdxKind) {
13881 case RecurKind::Add:
13882 case RecurKind::Mul:
13883 case RecurKind::Or:
13884 case RecurKind::And:
13885 case RecurKind::Xor:
13886 case RecurKind::FAdd:
13887 case RecurKind::FMul: {
13888 unsigned RdxOpcode = RecurrenceDescriptor::getOpcode(RdxKind);
13889 if (!AllConsts)
13890 VectorCost =
13891 TTI->getArithmeticReductionCost(RdxOpcode, VectorTy, FMF, CostKind);
13892 ScalarCost = EvaluateScalarCost([&]() {
13893 return TTI->getArithmeticInstrCost(RdxOpcode, ScalarTy, CostKind);
13894 });
13895 break;
13896 }
13897 case RecurKind::FMax:
13898 case RecurKind::FMin:
13899 case RecurKind::FMaximum:
13900 case RecurKind::FMinimum:
13901 case RecurKind::SMax:
13902 case RecurKind::SMin:
13903 case RecurKind::UMax:
13904 case RecurKind::UMin: {
13905 Intrinsic::ID Id = getMinMaxReductionIntrinsicOp(RdxKind);
13906 if (!AllConsts)
13907 VectorCost = TTI->getMinMaxReductionCost(Id, VectorTy, FMF, CostKind);
13908 ScalarCost = EvaluateScalarCost([&]() {
13909 IntrinsicCostAttributes ICA(Id, ScalarTy, {ScalarTy, ScalarTy}, FMF);
13910 return TTI->getIntrinsicInstrCost(ICA, CostKind);
13911 });
13912 break;
13913 }
13914 default:
13915 llvm_unreachable("Expected arithmetic or min/max reduction operation");
13916 }
13917
13918 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Adding cost " << VectorCost - ScalarCost
13919 << " for reduction that starts with " << *FirstReducedVal
13920 << " (It is a splitting reduction)\n");
13921 return VectorCost - ScalarCost;
13922 }
13923
13924 /// Emit a horizontal reduction of the vectorized value.
13925 Value *emitReduction(Value *VectorizedValue, IRBuilder<> &Builder,
13926 unsigned ReduxWidth, const TargetTransformInfo *TTI) {
13927 assert(VectorizedValue && "Need to have a vectorized tree node");
13928 assert(isPowerOf2_32(ReduxWidth) &&
13929 "We only handle power-of-two reductions for now");
13930 assert(RdxKind != RecurKind::FMulAdd &&
13931 "A call to the llvm.fmuladd intrinsic is not handled yet");
13932
13933 ++NumVectorInstructions;
13934 return createSimpleTargetReduction(Builder, TTI, VectorizedValue, RdxKind);
13935 }
13936
13937 /// Emits optimized code for unique scalar value reused \p Cnt times.
13938 Value *emitScaleForReusedOps(Value *VectorizedValue, IRBuilderBase &Builder,
13939 unsigned Cnt) {
13940 assert(IsSupportedHorRdxIdentityOp &&
13941 "The optimization of matched scalar identity horizontal reductions "
13942 "must be supported.");
13943 switch (RdxKind) {
13944 case RecurKind::Add: {
13945 // res = mul vv, n
13946 Value *Scale = ConstantInt::get(VectorizedValue->getType(), Cnt);
13947 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Add (to-mul) " << Cnt << "of "
13948 << VectorizedValue << ". (HorRdx)\n");
13949 return Builder.CreateMul(VectorizedValue, Scale);
13950 }
13951 case RecurKind::Xor: {
13952 // res = n % 2 ? 0 : vv
13953 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Xor " << Cnt << "of " << VectorizedValue
13954 << ". (HorRdx)\n");
13955 if (Cnt % 2 == 0)
13956 return Constant::getNullValue(VectorizedValue->getType());
13957 return VectorizedValue;
13958 }
13959 case RecurKind::FAdd: {
13960 // res = fmul v, n
13961 Value *Scale = ConstantFP::get(VectorizedValue->getType(), Cnt);
13962 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: FAdd (to-fmul) " << Cnt << "of "
13963 << VectorizedValue << ". (HorRdx)\n");
13964 return Builder.CreateFMul(VectorizedValue, Scale);
13965 }
13966 case RecurKind::And:
13967 case RecurKind::Or:
13968 case RecurKind::SMax:
13969 case RecurKind::SMin:
13970 case RecurKind::UMax:
13971 case RecurKind::UMin:
13972 case RecurKind::FMax:
13973 case RecurKind::FMin:
13974 case RecurKind::FMaximum:
13975 case RecurKind::FMinimum:
13976 // res = vv
13977 return VectorizedValue;
13978 case RecurKind::Mul:
13979 case RecurKind::FMul:
13980 case RecurKind::FMulAdd:
13981 case RecurKind::SelectICmp:
13982 case RecurKind::SelectFCmp:
13983 case RecurKind::None:
13984 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected reduction kind for repeated scalar.");
13985 }
13986 return nullptr;
13987 }
13988
13989 /// Emits actual operation for the scalar identity values, found during
13990 /// horizontal reduction analysis.
13991 Value *emitReusedOps(Value *VectorizedValue, IRBuilderBase &Builder,
13992 ArrayRef<Value *> VL,
13993 const MapVector<Value *, unsigned> &SameValuesCounter,
13994 const DenseMap<Value *, Value *> &TrackedToOrig) {
13995 assert(IsSupportedHorRdxIdentityOp &&
13996 "The optimization of matched scalar identity horizontal reductions "
13997 "must be supported.");
13998 switch (RdxKind) {
13999 case RecurKind::Add: {
14000 // root = mul prev_root, <1, 1, n, 1>
14001 SmallVector<Constant *> Vals;
14002 for (Value *V : VL) {
14003 unsigned Cnt = SameValuesCounter.lookup(TrackedToOrig.find(V)->second);
14004 Vals.push_back(ConstantInt::get(V->getType(), Cnt, /*IsSigned=*/false));
14005 }
14006 auto *Scale = ConstantVector::get(Vals);
14007 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Add (to-mul) " << Scale << "of "
14008 << VectorizedValue << ". (HorRdx)\n");
14009 return Builder.CreateMul(VectorizedValue, Scale);
14010 }
14011 case RecurKind::And:
14012 case RecurKind::Or:
14013 // No need for multiple or/and(s).
14014 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: And/or of same " << VectorizedValue
14015 << ". (HorRdx)\n");
14016 return VectorizedValue;
14017 case RecurKind::SMax:
14018 case RecurKind::SMin:
14019 case RecurKind::UMax:
14020 case RecurKind::UMin:
14021 case RecurKind::FMax:
14022 case RecurKind::FMin:
14023 case RecurKind::FMaximum:
14024 case RecurKind::FMinimum:
14025 // No need for multiple min/max(s) of the same value.
14026 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Max/min of same " << VectorizedValue
14027 << ". (HorRdx)\n");
14028 return VectorizedValue;
14029 case RecurKind::Xor: {
14030 // Replace values with even number of repeats with 0, since
14031 // x xor x = 0.
14032 // root = shuffle prev_root, zeroinitalizer, <0, 1, 2, vf, 4, vf, 5, 6,
14033 // 7>, if elements 4th and 6th elements have even number of repeats.
14034 SmallVector<int> Mask(
14035 cast<FixedVectorType>(VectorizedValue->getType())->getNumElements(),
14036 PoisonMaskElem);
14037 std::iota(Mask.begin(), Mask.end(), 0);
14038 bool NeedShuffle = false;
14039 for (unsigned I = 0, VF = VL.size(); I < VF; ++I) {
14040 Value *V = VL[I];
14041 unsigned Cnt = SameValuesCounter.lookup(TrackedToOrig.find(V)->second);
14042 if (Cnt % 2 == 0) {
14043 Mask[I] = VF;
14044 NeedShuffle = true;
14045 }
14046 }
14047 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Xor <"; for (int I
14048 : Mask) dbgs()
14049 << I << " ";
14050 dbgs() << "> of " << VectorizedValue << ". (HorRdx)\n");
14051 if (NeedShuffle)
14052 VectorizedValue = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(
14053 VectorizedValue,
14054 ConstantVector::getNullValue(VectorizedValue->getType()), Mask);
14055 return VectorizedValue;
14056 }
14057 case RecurKind::FAdd: {
14058 // root = fmul prev_root, <1.0, 1.0, n.0, 1.0>
14059 SmallVector<Constant *> Vals;
14060 for (Value *V : VL) {
14061 unsigned Cnt = SameValuesCounter.lookup(TrackedToOrig.find(V)->second);
14062 Vals.push_back(ConstantFP::get(V->getType(), Cnt));
14063 }
14064 auto *Scale = ConstantVector::get(Vals);
14065 return Builder.CreateFMul(VectorizedValue, Scale);
14066 }
14067 case RecurKind::Mul:
14068 case RecurKind::FMul:
14069 case RecurKind::FMulAdd:
14070 case RecurKind::SelectICmp:
14071 case RecurKind::SelectFCmp:
14072 case RecurKind::None:
14073 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected reduction kind for reused scalars.");
14074 }
14075 return nullptr;
14076 }
14077};
14078} // end anonymous namespace
14079
14080static std::optional<unsigned> getAggregateSize(Instruction *InsertInst) {
14081 if (auto *IE = dyn_cast<InsertElementInst>(InsertInst))
14082 return cast<FixedVectorType>(IE->getType())->getNumElements();
14083
14084 unsigned AggregateSize = 1;
14085 auto *IV = cast<InsertValueInst>(InsertInst);
14086 Type *CurrentType = IV->getType();
14087 do {
14088 if (auto *ST = dyn_cast<StructType>(CurrentType)) {
14089 for (auto *Elt : ST->elements())
14090 if (Elt != ST->getElementType(0)) // check homogeneity
14091 return std::nullopt;
14092 AggregateSize *= ST->getNumElements();
14093 CurrentType = ST->getElementType(0);
14094 } else if (auto *AT = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(CurrentType)) {
14095 AggregateSize *= AT->getNumElements();
14096 CurrentType = AT->getElementType();
14097 } else if (auto *VT = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(CurrentType)) {
14098 AggregateSize *= VT->getNumElements();
14099 return AggregateSize;
14100 } else if (CurrentType->isSingleValueType()) {
14101 return AggregateSize;
14102 } else {
14103 return std::nullopt;
14104 }
14105 } while (true);
14106}
14107
14108static void findBuildAggregate_rec(Instruction *LastInsertInst,
14109 TargetTransformInfo *TTI,
14110 SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &BuildVectorOpds,
14111 SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &InsertElts,
14112 unsigned OperandOffset) {
14113 do {
14114 Value *InsertedOperand = LastInsertInst->getOperand(1);
14115 std::optional<unsigned> OperandIndex =
14116 getInsertIndex(LastInsertInst, OperandOffset);
14117 if (!OperandIndex)
14118 return;
14119 if (isa<InsertElementInst, InsertValueInst>(InsertedOperand)) {
14120 findBuildAggregate_rec(cast<Instruction>(InsertedOperand), TTI,
14121 BuildVectorOpds, InsertElts, *OperandIndex);
14122
14123 } else {
14124 BuildVectorOpds[*OperandIndex] = InsertedOperand;
14125 InsertElts[*OperandIndex] = LastInsertInst;
14126 }
14127 LastInsertInst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(LastInsertInst->getOperand(0));
14128 } while (LastInsertInst != nullptr &&
14129 isa<InsertValueInst, InsertElementInst>(LastInsertInst) &&
14130 LastInsertInst->hasOneUse());
14131}
14132
14133/// Recognize construction of vectors like
14134/// %ra = insertelement <4 x float> poison, float %s0, i32 0
14135/// %rb = insertelement <4 x float> %ra, float %s1, i32 1
14136/// %rc = insertelement <4 x float> %rb, float %s2, i32 2
14137/// %rd = insertelement <4 x float> %rc, float %s3, i32 3
14138/// starting from the last insertelement or insertvalue instruction.
14139///
14140/// Also recognize homogeneous aggregates like {<2 x float>, <2 x float>},
14141/// {{float, float}, {float, float}}, [2 x {float, float}] and so on.
14142/// See llvm/test/Transforms/SLPVectorizer/X86/pr42022.ll for examples.
14143///
14144/// Assume LastInsertInst is of InsertElementInst or InsertValueInst type.
14145///
14146/// \return true if it matches.
14147static bool findBuildAggregate(Instruction *LastInsertInst,
14148 TargetTransformInfo *TTI,
14149 SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &BuildVectorOpds,
14150 SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &InsertElts) {
14151
14152 assert((isa<InsertElementInst>(LastInsertInst) ||
14153 isa<InsertValueInst>(LastInsertInst)) &&
14154 "Expected insertelement or insertvalue instruction!");
14155
14156 assert((BuildVectorOpds.empty() && InsertElts.empty()) &&
14157 "Expected empty result vectors!");
14158
14159 std::optional<unsigned> AggregateSize = getAggregateSize(LastInsertInst);
14160 if (!AggregateSize)
14161 return false;
14162 BuildVectorOpds.resize(*AggregateSize);
14163 InsertElts.resize(*AggregateSize);
14164
14165 findBuildAggregate_rec(LastInsertInst, TTI, BuildVectorOpds, InsertElts, 0);
14166 llvm::erase_value(BuildVectorOpds, nullptr);
14167 llvm::erase_value(InsertElts, nullptr);
14168 if (BuildVectorOpds.size() >= 2)
14169 return true;
14170
14171 return false;
14172}
14173
14174/// Try and get a reduction instruction from a phi node.
14175///
14176/// Given a phi node \p P in a block \p ParentBB, consider possible reductions
14177/// if they come from either \p ParentBB or a containing loop latch.
14178///
14179/// \returns A candidate reduction value if possible, or \code nullptr \endcode
14180/// if not possible.
14181static Instruction *getReductionInstr(const DominatorTree *DT, PHINode *P,
14182 BasicBlock *ParentBB, LoopInfo *LI) {
14183 // There are situations where the reduction value is not dominated by the
14184 // reduction phi. Vectorizing such cases has been reported to cause
14185 // miscompiles. See PR25787.
14186 auto DominatedReduxValue = [&](Value *R) {
14187 return isa<Instruction>(R) &&
14188 DT->dominates(P->getParent(), cast<Instruction>(R)->getParent());
14189 };
14190
14191 Instruction *Rdx = nullptr;
14192
14193 // Return the incoming value if it comes from the same BB as the phi node.
14194 if (P->getIncomingBlock(0) == ParentBB) {
14195 Rdx = dyn_cast<Instruction>(P->getIncomingValue(0));
14196 } else if (P->getIncomingBlock(1) == ParentBB) {
14197 Rdx = dyn_cast<Instruction>(P->getIncomingValue(1));
14198 }
14199
14200 if (Rdx && DominatedReduxValue(Rdx))
14201 return Rdx;
14202
14203 // Otherwise, check whether we have a loop latch to look at.
14204 Loop *BBL = LI->getLoopFor(ParentBB);
14205 if (!BBL)
14206 return nullptr;
14207 BasicBlock *BBLatch = BBL->getLoopLatch();
14208 if (!BBLatch)
14209 return nullptr;
14210
14211 // There is a loop latch, return the incoming value if it comes from
14212 // that. This reduction pattern occasionally turns up.
14213 if (P->getIncomingBlock(0) == BBLatch) {
14214 Rdx = dyn_cast<Instruction>(P->getIncomingValue(0));
14215 } else if (P->getIncomingBlock(1) == BBLatch) {
14216 Rdx = dyn_cast<Instruction>(P->getIncomingValue(1));
14217 }
14218
14219 if (Rdx && DominatedReduxValue(Rdx))
14220 return Rdx;
14221
14222 return nullptr;
14223}
14224
14225static bool matchRdxBop(Instruction *I, Value *&V0, Value *&V1) {
14226 if (match(I, m_BinOp(m_Value(V0), m_Value(V1))))
14227 return true;
14228 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::maxnum>(m_Value(V0), m_Value(V1))))
14229 return true;
14230 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::minnum>(m_Value(V0), m_Value(V1))))
14231 return true;
14232 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::maximum>(m_Value(V0), m_Value(V1))))
14233 return true;
14234 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::minimum>(m_Value(V0), m_Value(V1))))
14235 return true;
14236 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::smax>(m_Value(V0), m_Value(V1))))
14237 return true;
14238 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::smin>(m_Value(V0), m_Value(V1))))
14239 return true;
14240 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::umax>(m_Value(V0), m_Value(V1))))
14241 return true;
14242 if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::umin>(m_Value(V0), m_Value(V1))))
14243 return true;
14244 return false;
14245}
14246
14247/// We could have an initial reduction that is not an add.
14248/// r *= v1 + v2 + v3 + v4
14249/// In such a case start looking for a tree rooted in the first '+'.
14250/// \Returns the new root if found, which may be nullptr if not an instruction.
14251static Instruction *tryGetSecondaryReductionRoot(PHINode *Phi,
14252 Instruction *Root) {
14253 assert((isa<BinaryOperator>(Root) || isa<SelectInst>(Root) ||
14254 isa<IntrinsicInst>(Root)) &&
14255 "Expected binop, select, or intrinsic for reduction matching");
14256 Value *LHS =
14257 Root->getOperand(HorizontalReduction::getFirstOperandIndex(Root));
14258 Value *RHS =
14259 Root->getOperand(HorizontalReduction::getFirstOperandIndex(Root) + 1);
14260 if (LHS == Phi)
14261 return dyn_cast<Instruction>(RHS);
14262 if (RHS == Phi)
14263 return dyn_cast<Instruction>(LHS);
14264 return nullptr;
14265}
14266
14267/// \p Returns the first operand of \p I that does not match \p Phi. If
14268/// operand is not an instruction it returns nullptr.
14269static Instruction *getNonPhiOperand(Instruction *I, PHINode *Phi) {
14270 Value *Op0 = nullptr;
14271 Value *Op1 = nullptr;
14272 if (!matchRdxBop(I, Op0, Op1))
14273 return nullptr;
14274 return dyn_cast<Instruction>(Op0 == Phi ? Op1 : Op0);
14275}
14276
14277/// \Returns true if \p I is a candidate instruction for reduction vectorization.
14278static bool isReductionCandidate(Instruction *I) {
14279 bool IsSelect = match(I, m_Select(m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value()));
14280 Value *B0 = nullptr, *B1 = nullptr;
14281 bool IsBinop = matchRdxBop(I, B0, B1);
14282 return IsBinop || IsSelect;
14283}
14284
14285bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeHorReduction(
14286 PHINode *P, Instruction *Root, BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R, TargetTransformInfo *TTI,
14287 SmallVectorImpl<WeakTrackingVH> &PostponedInsts) {
14288 if (!ShouldVectorizeHor)
14289 return false;
14290 bool TryOperandsAsNewSeeds = P && isa<BinaryOperator>(Root);
14291
14292 if (Root->getParent() != BB || isa<PHINode>(Root))
14293 return false;
14294
14295 // If we can find a secondary reduction root, use that instead.
14296 auto SelectRoot = [&]() {
14297 if (TryOperandsAsNewSeeds && isReductionCandidate(Root) &&
14298 HorizontalReduction::getRdxKind(Root) != RecurKind::None)
14299 if (Instruction *NewRoot = tryGetSecondaryReductionRoot(P, Root))
14300 return NewRoot;
14301 return Root;
14302 };
14303
14304 // Start analysis starting from Root instruction. If horizontal reduction is
14305 // found, try to vectorize it. If it is not a horizontal reduction or
14306 // vectorization is not possible or not effective, and currently analyzed
14307 // instruction is a binary operation, try to vectorize the operands, using
14308 // pre-order DFS traversal order. If the operands were not vectorized, repeat
14309 // the same procedure considering each operand as a possible root of the
14310 // horizontal reduction.
14311 // Interrupt the process if the Root instruction itself was vectorized or all
14312 // sub-trees not higher that RecursionMaxDepth were analyzed/vectorized.
14313 // If a horizintal reduction was not matched or vectorized we collect
14314 // instructions for possible later attempts for vectorization.
14315 std::queue<std::pair<Instruction *, unsigned>> Stack;
14316 Stack.emplace(SelectRoot(), 0);
14317 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 8> VisitedInstrs;
14318 bool Res = false;
14319 auto &&TryToReduce = [this, TTI, &R](Instruction *Inst) -> Value * {
14320 if (R.isAnalyzedReductionRoot(Inst))
14321 return nullptr;
14322 if (!isReductionCandidate(Inst))
14323 return nullptr;
14324 HorizontalReduction HorRdx;
14325 if (!HorRdx.matchAssociativeReduction(R, Inst, *SE, *DL, *TLI))
14326 return nullptr;
14327 return HorRdx.tryToReduce(R, TTI, *TLI);
14328 };
14329 auto TryAppendToPostponedInsts = [&](Instruction *FutureSeed) {
14330 if (TryOperandsAsNewSeeds && FutureSeed == Root) {
14331 FutureSeed = getNonPhiOperand(Root, P);
14332 if (!FutureSeed)
14333 return false;
14334 }
14335 // Do not collect CmpInst or InsertElementInst/InsertValueInst as their
14336 // analysis is done separately.
14337 if (!isa<CmpInst, InsertElementInst, InsertValueInst>(FutureSeed))
14338 PostponedInsts.push_back(FutureSeed);
14339 return true;
14340 };
14341
14342 while (!Stack.empty()) {
14343 Instruction *Inst;
14344 unsigned Level;
14345 std::tie(Inst, Level) = Stack.front();
14346 Stack.pop();
14347 // Do not try to analyze instruction that has already been vectorized.
14348 // This may happen when we vectorize instruction operands on a previous
14349 // iteration while stack was populated before that happened.
14350 if (R.isDeleted(Inst))
14351 continue;
14352 if (Value *VectorizedV = TryToReduce(Inst)) {
14353 Res = true;
14354 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(VectorizedV)) {
14355 // Try to find another reduction.
14356 Stack.emplace(I, Level);
14357 continue;
14358 }
14359 } else {
14360 // We could not vectorize `Inst` so try to use it as a future seed.
14361 if (!TryAppendToPostponedInsts(Inst)) {
14362 assert(Stack.empty() && "Expected empty stack");
14363 break;
14364 }
14365 }
14366
14367 // Try to vectorize operands.
14368 // Continue analysis for the instruction from the same basic block only to
14369 // save compile time.
14370 if (++Level < RecursionMaxDepth)
14371 for (auto *Op : Inst->operand_values())
14372 if (VisitedInstrs.insert(Op).second)
14373 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Op))
14374 // Do not try to vectorize CmpInst operands, this is done
14375 // separately.
14376 if (!isa<PHINode, CmpInst, InsertElementInst, InsertValueInst>(I) &&
14377 !R.isDeleted(I) && I->getParent() == BB)
14378 Stack.emplace(I, Level);
14379 }
14380 return Res;
14381}
14382
14383bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeRootInstruction(PHINode *P, Instruction *Root,
14384 BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R,
14385 TargetTransformInfo *TTI) {
14386 SmallVector<WeakTrackingVH> PostponedInsts;
14387 bool Res = vectorizeHorReduction(P, Root, BB, R, TTI, PostponedInsts);
14388 Res |= tryToVectorize(PostponedInsts, R);
14389 return Res;
14390}
14391
14392bool SLPVectorizerPass::tryToVectorize(ArrayRef<WeakTrackingVH> Insts,
14393 BoUpSLP &R) {
14394 bool Res = false;
14395 for (Value *V : Insts)
14396 if (auto *Inst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V); Inst && !R.isDeleted(Inst))
14397 Res |= tryToVectorize(Inst, R);
14398 return Res;
14399}
14400
14401bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeInsertValueInst(InsertValueInst *IVI,
14402 BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R) {
14403 const DataLayout &DL = BB->getModule()->getDataLayout();
14404 if (!R.canMapToVector(IVI->getType(), DL))
14405 return false;
14406
14407 SmallVector<Value *, 16> BuildVectorOpds;
14408 SmallVector<Value *, 16> BuildVectorInsts;
14409 if (!findBuildAggregate(IVI, TTI, BuildVectorOpds, BuildVectorInsts))
14410 return false;
14411
14412 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: array mappable to vector: " << *IVI << "\n");
14413 // Aggregate value is unlikely to be processed in vector register.
14414 return tryToVectorizeList(BuildVectorOpds, R);
14415}
14416
14417bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeInsertElementInst(InsertElementInst *IEI,
14418 BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R) {
14419 SmallVector<Value *, 16> BuildVectorInsts;
14420 SmallVector<Value *, 16> BuildVectorOpds;
14421 SmallVector<int> Mask;
14422 if (!findBuildAggregate(IEI, TTI, BuildVectorOpds, BuildVectorInsts) ||
14423 (llvm::all_of(
14424 BuildVectorOpds,
14425 [](Value *V) { return isa<ExtractElementInst, UndefValue>(V); }) &&
14426 isFixedVectorShuffle(BuildVectorOpds, Mask)))
14427 return false;
14428
14429 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: array mappable to vector: " << *IEI << "\n");
14430 return tryToVectorizeList(BuildVectorInsts, R);
14431}
14432
14433template <typename T>
14434static bool tryToVectorizeSequence(
14435 SmallVectorImpl<T *> &Incoming, function_ref<bool(T *, T *)> Comparator,
14436 function_ref<bool(T *, T *)> AreCompatible,
14437 function_ref<bool(ArrayRef<T *>, bool)> TryToVectorizeHelper,
14438 bool MaxVFOnly, BoUpSLP &R) {
14439 bool Changed = false;
14440 // Sort by type, parent, operands.
14441 stable_sort(Incoming, Comparator);
14442
14443 // Try to vectorize elements base on their type.
14444 SmallVector<T *> Candidates;
14445 for (auto *IncIt = Incoming.begin(), *E = Incoming.end(); IncIt != E;) {
14446 // Look for the next elements with the same type, parent and operand
14447 // kinds.
14448 auto *SameTypeIt = IncIt;
14449 while (SameTypeIt != E && AreCompatible(*SameTypeIt, *IncIt))
14450 ++SameTypeIt;
14451
14452 // Try to vectorize them.
14453 unsigned NumElts = (SameTypeIt - IncIt);
14454 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Trying to vectorize starting at nodes ("
14455 << NumElts << ")\n");
14456 // The vectorization is a 3-state attempt:
14457 // 1. Try to vectorize instructions with the same/alternate opcodes with the
14458 // size of maximal register at first.
14459 // 2. Try to vectorize remaining instructions with the same type, if
14460 // possible. This may result in the better vectorization results rather than
14461 // if we try just to vectorize instructions with the same/alternate opcodes.
14462 // 3. Final attempt to try to vectorize all instructions with the
14463 // same/alternate ops only, this may result in some extra final
14464 // vectorization.
14465 if (NumElts > 1 &&
14466 TryToVectorizeHelper(ArrayRef(IncIt, NumElts), MaxVFOnly)) {
14467 // Success start over because instructions might have been changed.
14468 Changed = true;
14469 } else {
14470 /// \Returns the minimum number of elements that we will attempt to
14471 /// vectorize.
14472 auto GetMinNumElements = [&R](Value *V) {
14473 unsigned EltSize = R.getVectorElementSize(V);
14474 return std::max(2U, R.getMaxVecRegSize() / EltSize);
14475 };
14476 if (NumElts < GetMinNumElements(*IncIt) &&
14477 (Candidates.empty() ||
14478 Candidates.front()->getType() == (*IncIt)->getType())) {
14479 Candidates.append(IncIt, std::next(IncIt, NumElts));
14480 }
14481 }
14482 // Final attempt to vectorize instructions with the same types.
14483 if (Candidates.size() > 1 &&
14484 (SameTypeIt == E || (*SameTypeIt)->getType() != (*IncIt)->getType())) {
14485 if (TryToVectorizeHelper(Candidates, /*MaxVFOnly=*/false)) {
14486 // Success start over because instructions might have been changed.
14487 Changed = true;
14488 } else if (MaxVFOnly) {
14489 // Try to vectorize using small vectors.
14490 for (auto *It = Candidates.begin(), *End = Candidates.end();
14491 It != End;) {
14492 auto *SameTypeIt = It;
14493 while (SameTypeIt != End && AreCompatible(*SameTypeIt, *It))
14494 ++SameTypeIt;
14495 unsigned NumElts = (SameTypeIt - It);
14496 if (NumElts > 1 && TryToVectorizeHelper(ArrayRef(It, NumElts),
14497 /*MaxVFOnly=*/false))
14498 Changed = true;
14499 It = SameTypeIt;
14500 }
14501 }
14502 Candidates.clear();
14503 }
14504
14505 // Start over at the next instruction of a different type (or the end).
14506 IncIt = SameTypeIt;
14507 }
14508 return Changed;
14509}
14510
14511/// Compare two cmp instructions. If IsCompatibility is true, function returns
14512/// true if 2 cmps have same/swapped predicates and mos compatible corresponding
14513/// operands. If IsCompatibility is false, function implements strict weak
14514/// ordering relation between two cmp instructions, returning true if the first
14515/// instruction is "less" than the second, i.e. its predicate is less than the
14516/// predicate of the second or the operands IDs are less than the operands IDs
14517/// of the second cmp instruction.
14518template <bool IsCompatibility>
14519static bool compareCmp(Value *V, Value *V2, TargetLibraryInfo &TLI,
14520 const DominatorTree &DT) {
14521 assert(isValidElementType(V->getType()) &&
14522 isValidElementType(V2->getType()) &&
14523 "Expected valid element types only.");
14524 auto *CI1 = cast<CmpInst>(V);
14525 auto *CI2 = cast<CmpInst>(V2);
14526 if (CI1->getOperand(0)->getType()->getTypeID() <
14527 CI2->getOperand(0)->getType()->getTypeID())
14528 return !IsCompatibility;
14529 if (CI1->getOperand(0)->getType()->getTypeID() >
14530 CI2->getOperand(0)->getType()->getTypeID())
14531 return false;
14532 CmpInst::Predicate Pred1 = CI1->getPredicate();
14533 CmpInst::Predicate Pred2 = CI2->getPredicate();
14534 CmpInst::Predicate SwapPred1 = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred1);
14535 CmpInst::Predicate SwapPred2 = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred2);
14536 CmpInst::Predicate BasePred1 = std::min(Pred1, SwapPred1);
14537 CmpInst::Predicate BasePred2 = std::min(Pred2, SwapPred2);
14538 if (BasePred1 < BasePred2)
14539 return !IsCompatibility;
14540 if (BasePred1 > BasePred2)
14541 return false;
14542 // Compare operands.
14543 bool LEPreds = Pred1 <= Pred2;
14544 bool GEPreds = Pred1 >= Pred2;
14545 for (int I = 0, E = CI1->getNumOperands(); I < E; ++I) {
14546 auto *Op1 = CI1->getOperand(LEPreds ? I : E - I - 1);
14547 auto *Op2 = CI2->getOperand(GEPreds ? I : E - I - 1);
14548 if (Op1->getValueID() < Op2->getValueID())
14549 return !IsCompatibility;
14550 if (Op1->getValueID() > Op2->getValueID())
14551 return false;
14552 if (auto *I1 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Op1))
14553 if (auto *I2 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Op2)) {
14554 if (IsCompatibility) {
14555 if (I1->getParent() != I2->getParent())
14556 return false;
14557 } else {
14558 // Try to compare nodes with same parent.
14559 DomTreeNodeBase<BasicBlock> *NodeI1 = DT.getNode(I1->getParent());
14560 DomTreeNodeBase<BasicBlock> *NodeI2 = DT.getNode(I2->getParent());
14561 if (!NodeI1)
14562 return NodeI2 != nullptr;
14563 if (!NodeI2)
14564 return false;
14565 assert((NodeI1 == NodeI2) ==
14566 (NodeI1->getDFSNumIn() == NodeI2->getDFSNumIn()) &&
14567 "Different nodes should have different DFS numbers");
14568 if (NodeI1 != NodeI2)
14569 return NodeI1->getDFSNumIn() < NodeI2->getDFSNumIn();
14570 }
14571 InstructionsState S = getSameOpcode({I1, I2}, TLI);
14572 if (S.getOpcode() && (IsCompatibility || !S.isAltShuffle()))
14573 continue;
14574 return !IsCompatibility && I1->getOpcode() < I2->getOpcode();
14575 }
14576 }
14577 return IsCompatibility;
14578}
14579
14580template <typename ItT>
14581bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeCmpInsts(iterator_range<ItT> CmpInsts,
14582 BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R) {
14583 bool Changed = false;
14584 // Try to find reductions first.
14585 for (CmpInst *I : CmpInsts) {
14586 if (R.isDeleted(I))
14587 continue;
14588 for (Value *Op : I->operands())
14589 if (auto *RootOp = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Op))
14590 Changed |= vectorizeRootInstruction(nullptr, RootOp, BB, R, TTI);
14591 }
14592 // Try to vectorize operands as vector bundles.
14593 for (CmpInst *I : CmpInsts) {
14594 if (R.isDeleted(I))
14595 continue;
14596 Changed |= tryToVectorize(I, R);
14597 }
14598 // Try to vectorize list of compares.
14599 // Sort by type, compare predicate, etc.
14600 auto CompareSorter = [&](Value *V, Value *V2) {
14601 if (V == V2)
14602 return false;
14603 return compareCmp<false>(V, V2, *TLI, *DT);
14604 };
14605
14606 auto AreCompatibleCompares = [&](Value *V1, Value *V2) {
14607 if (V1 == V2)
14608 return true;
14609 return compareCmp<true>(V1, V2, *TLI, *DT);
14610 };
14611
14612 SmallVector<Value *> Vals;
14613 for (Instruction *V : CmpInsts)
14614 if (!R.isDeleted(V) && isValidElementType(V->getType()))
14615 Vals.push_back(V);
14616 if (Vals.size() <= 1)
14617 return Changed;
14618 Changed |= tryToVectorizeSequence<Value>(
14619 Vals, CompareSorter, AreCompatibleCompares,
14620 [this, &R](ArrayRef<Value *> Candidates, bool MaxVFOnly) {
14621 // Exclude possible reductions from other blocks.
14622 bool ArePossiblyReducedInOtherBlock = any_of(Candidates, [](Value *V) {
14623 return any_of(V->users(), [V](User *U) {
14624 auto *Select = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(U);
14625 return Select &&
14626 Select->getParent() != cast<Instruction>(V)->getParent();
14627 });
14628 });
14629 if (ArePossiblyReducedInOtherBlock)
14630 return false;
14631 return tryToVectorizeList(Candidates, R, MaxVFOnly);
14632 },
14633 /*MaxVFOnly=*/true, R);
14634 return Changed;
14635}
14636
14637bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeInserts(InstSetVector &Instructions,
14638 BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R) {
14639 assert(all_of(Instructions,
14640 [](auto *I) {
14641 return isa<InsertElementInst, InsertValueInst>(I);
14642 }) &&
14643 "This function only accepts Insert instructions");
14644 bool OpsChanged = false;
14645 SmallVector<WeakTrackingVH> PostponedInsts;
14646 // pass1 - try to vectorize reductions only
14647 for (auto *I : reverse(Instructions)) {
14648 if (R.isDeleted(I))
14649 continue;
14650 OpsChanged |= vectorizeHorReduction(nullptr, I, BB, R, TTI, PostponedInsts);
14651 }
14652 // pass2 - try to match and vectorize a buildvector sequence.
14653 for (auto *I : reverse(Instructions)) {
14654 if (R.isDeleted(I) || isa<CmpInst>(I))
14655 continue;
14656 if (auto *LastInsertValue = dyn_cast<InsertValueInst>(I)) {
14657 OpsChanged |= vectorizeInsertValueInst(LastInsertValue, BB, R);
14658 } else if (auto *LastInsertElem = dyn_cast<InsertElementInst>(I)) {
14659 OpsChanged |= vectorizeInsertElementInst(LastInsertElem, BB, R);
14660 }
14661 }
14662 // Now try to vectorize postponed instructions.
14663 OpsChanged |= tryToVectorize(PostponedInsts, R);
14664
14665 Instructions.clear();
14666 return OpsChanged;
14667}
14668
14669bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeChainsInBlock(BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R) {
14670 bool Changed = false;
14671 SmallVector<Value *, 4> Incoming;
14672 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 16> VisitedInstrs;
14673 // Maps phi nodes to the non-phi nodes found in the use tree for each phi
14674 // node. Allows better to identify the chains that can be vectorized in the
14675 // better way.
14676 DenseMap<Value *, SmallVector<Value *, 4>> PHIToOpcodes;
14677 auto PHICompare = [this, &PHIToOpcodes](Value *V1, Value *V2) {
14678 assert(isValidElementType(V1->getType()) &&
14679 isValidElementType(V2->getType()) &&
14680 "Expected vectorizable types only.");
14681 // It is fine to compare type IDs here, since we expect only vectorizable
14682 // types, like ints, floats and pointers, we don't care about other type.
14683 if (V1->getType()->getTypeID() < V2->getType()->getTypeID())
14684 return true;
14685 if (V1->getType()->getTypeID() > V2->getType()->getTypeID())
14686 return false;
14687 ArrayRef<Value *> Opcodes1 = PHIToOpcodes[V1];
14688 ArrayRef<Value *> Opcodes2 = PHIToOpcodes[V2];
14689 if (Opcodes1.size() < Opcodes2.size())
14690 return true;
14691 if (Opcodes1.size() > Opcodes2.size())
14692 return false;
14693 std::optional<bool> ConstOrder;
14694 for (int I = 0, E = Opcodes1.size(); I < E; ++I) {
14695 // Undefs are compatible with any other value.
14696 if (isa<UndefValue>(Opcodes1[I]) || isa<UndefValue>(Opcodes2[I])) {
14697 if (!ConstOrder)
14698 ConstOrder =
14699 !isa<UndefValue>(Opcodes1[I]) && isa<UndefValue>(Opcodes2[I]);
14700 continue;
14701 }
14702 if (auto *I1 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Opcodes1[I]))
14703 if (auto *I2 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Opcodes2[I])) {
14704 DomTreeNodeBase<BasicBlock> *NodeI1 = DT->getNode(I1->getParent());
14705 DomTreeNodeBase<BasicBlock> *NodeI2 = DT->getNode(I2->getParent());
14706 if (!NodeI1)
14707 return NodeI2 != nullptr;
14708 if (!NodeI2)
14709 return false;
14710 assert((NodeI1 == NodeI2) ==
14711 (NodeI1->getDFSNumIn() == NodeI2->getDFSNumIn()) &&
14712 "Different nodes should have different DFS numbers");
14713 if (NodeI1 != NodeI2)
14714 return NodeI1->getDFSNumIn() < NodeI2->getDFSNumIn();
14715 InstructionsState S = getSameOpcode({I1, I2}, *TLI);
14716 if (S.getOpcode())
14717 continue;
14718 return I1->getOpcode() < I2->getOpcode();
14719 }
14720 if (isa<Constant>(Opcodes1[I]) && isa<Constant>(Opcodes2[I])) {
14721 if (!ConstOrder)
14722 ConstOrder = Opcodes1[I]->getValueID() < Opcodes2[I]->getValueID();
14723 continue;
14724 }
14725 if (Opcodes1[I]->getValueID() < Opcodes2[I]->getValueID())
14726 return true;
14727 if (Opcodes1[I]->getValueID() > Opcodes2[I]->getValueID())
14728 return false;
14729 }
14730 return ConstOrder && *ConstOrder;
14731 };
14732 auto AreCompatiblePHIs = [&PHIToOpcodes, this](Value *V1, Value *V2) {
14733 if (V1 == V2)
14734 return true;
14735 if (V1->getType() != V2->getType())
14736 return false;
14737 ArrayRef<Value *> Opcodes1 = PHIToOpcodes[V1];
14738 ArrayRef<Value *> Opcodes2 = PHIToOpcodes[V2];
14739 if (Opcodes1.size() != Opcodes2.size())
14740 return false;
14741 for (int I = 0, E = Opcodes1.size(); I < E; ++I) {
14742 // Undefs are compatible with any other value.
14743 if (isa<UndefValue>(Opcodes1[I]) || isa<UndefValue>(Opcodes2[I]))
14744 continue;
14745 if (auto *I1 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Opcodes1[I]))
14746 if (auto *I2 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Opcodes2[I])) {
14747 if (I1->getParent() != I2->getParent())
14748 return false;
14749 InstructionsState S = getSameOpcode({I1, I2}, *TLI);
14750 if (S.getOpcode())
14751 continue;
14752 return false;
14753 }
14754 if (isa<Constant>(Opcodes1[I]) && isa<Constant>(Opcodes2[I]))
14755 continue;
14756 if (Opcodes1[I]->getValueID() != Opcodes2[I]->getValueID())
14757 return false;
14758 }
14759 return true;
14760 };
14761
14762 bool HaveVectorizedPhiNodes = false;
14763 do {
14764 // Collect the incoming values from the PHIs.
14765 Incoming.clear();
14766 for (Instruction &I : *BB) {
14767 PHINode *P = dyn_cast<PHINode>(&I);
14768 if (!P)
14769 break;
14770
14771 // No need to analyze deleted, vectorized and non-vectorizable
14772 // instructions.
14773 if (!VisitedInstrs.count(P) && !R.isDeleted(P) &&
14774 isValidElementType(P->getType()))
14775 Incoming.push_back(P);
14776 }
14777
14778 // Find the corresponding non-phi nodes for better matching when trying to
14779 // build the tree.
14780 for (Value *V : Incoming) {
14781 SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Opcodes =
14782 PHIToOpcodes.try_emplace(V).first->getSecond();
14783 if (!Opcodes.empty())
14784 continue;
14785 SmallVector<Value *, 4> Nodes(1, V);
14786 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 4> Visited;
14787 while (!Nodes.empty()) {
14788 auto *PHI = cast<PHINode>(Nodes.pop_back_val());
14789 if (!Visited.insert(PHI).second)
14790 continue;
14791 for (Value *V : PHI->incoming_values()) {
14792 if (auto *PHI1 = dyn_cast<PHINode>((V))) {
14793 Nodes.push_back(PHI1);
14794 continue;
14795 }
14796 Opcodes.emplace_back(V);
14797 }
14798 }
14799 }
14800
14801 HaveVectorizedPhiNodes = tryToVectorizeSequence<Value>(
14802 Incoming, PHICompare, AreCompatiblePHIs,
14803 [this, &R](ArrayRef<Value *> Candidates, bool MaxVFOnly) {
14804 return tryToVectorizeList(Candidates, R, MaxVFOnly);
14805 },
14806 /*MaxVFOnly=*/true, R);
14807 Changed |= HaveVectorizedPhiNodes;
14808 VisitedInstrs.insert(Incoming.begin(), Incoming.end());
14809 } while (HaveVectorizedPhiNodes);
14810
14811 VisitedInstrs.clear();
14812
14813 InstSetVector PostProcessInserts;
14814 SmallSetVector<CmpInst *, 8> PostProcessCmps;
14815 // Vectorizes Inserts in `PostProcessInserts` and if `VecctorizeCmps` is true
14816 // also vectorizes `PostProcessCmps`.
14817 auto VectorizeInsertsAndCmps = [&](bool VectorizeCmps) {
14818 bool Changed = vectorizeInserts(PostProcessInserts, BB, R);
14819 if (VectorizeCmps) {
14820 Changed |= vectorizeCmpInsts(reverse(PostProcessCmps), BB, R);
14821 PostProcessCmps.clear();
14822 }
14823 PostProcessInserts.clear();
14824 return Changed;
14825 };
14826 // Returns true if `I` is in `PostProcessInserts` or `PostProcessCmps`.
14827 auto IsInPostProcessInstrs = [&](Instruction *I) {
14828 if (auto *Cmp = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(I))
14829 return PostProcessCmps.contains(Cmp);
14830 return isa<InsertElementInst, InsertValueInst>(I) &&
14831 PostProcessInserts.contains(I);
14832 };
14833 // Returns true if `I` is an instruction without users, like terminator, or
14834 // function call with ignored return value, store. Ignore unused instructions
14835 // (basing on instruction type, except for CallInst and InvokeInst).
14836 auto HasNoUsers = [](Instruction *I) {
14837 return I->use_empty() &&
14838 (I->getType()->isVoidTy() || isa<CallInst, InvokeInst>(I));
14839 };
14840 for (BasicBlock::iterator it = BB->begin(), e = BB->end(); it != e; ++it) {
14841 // Skip instructions with scalable type. The num of elements is unknown at
14842 // compile-time for scalable type.
14843 if (isa<ScalableVectorType>(it->getType()))
14844 continue;
14845
14846 // Skip instructions marked for the deletion.
14847 if (R.isDeleted(&*it))
14848 continue;
14849 // We may go through BB multiple times so skip the one we have checked.
14850 if (!VisitedInstrs.insert(&*it).second) {
14851 if (HasNoUsers(&*it) &&
14852 VectorizeInsertsAndCmps(/*VectorizeCmps=*/it->isTerminator())) {
14853 // We would like to start over since some instructions are deleted
14854 // and the iterator may become invalid value.
14855 Changed = true;
14856 it = BB->begin();
14857 e = BB->end();
14858 }
14859 continue;
14860 }
14861
14862 if (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(it))
14863 continue;
14864
14865 // Try to vectorize reductions that use PHINodes.
14866 if (PHINode *P = dyn_cast<PHINode>(it)) {
14867 // Check that the PHI is a reduction PHI.
14868 if (P->getNumIncomingValues() == 2) {
14869 // Try to match and vectorize a horizontal reduction.
14870 Instruction *Root = getReductionInstr(DT, P, BB, LI);
14871 if (Root && vectorizeRootInstruction(P, Root, BB, R, TTI)) {
14872 Changed = true;
14873 it = BB->begin();
14874 e = BB->end();
14875 continue;
14876 }
14877 }
14878 // Try to vectorize the incoming values of the PHI, to catch reductions
14879 // that feed into PHIs.
14880 for (unsigned I = 0, E = P->getNumIncomingValues(); I != E; I++) {
14881 // Skip if the incoming block is the current BB for now. Also, bypass
14882 // unreachable IR for efficiency and to avoid crashing.
14883 // TODO: Collect the skipped incoming values and try to vectorize them
14884 // after processing BB.
14885 if (BB == P->getIncomingBlock(I) ||
14886 !DT->isReachableFromEntry(P->getIncomingBlock(I)))
14887 continue;
14888
14889 // Postponed instructions should not be vectorized here, delay their
14890 // vectorization.
14891 if (auto *PI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(P->getIncomingValue(I));
14892 PI && !IsInPostProcessInstrs(PI))
14893 Changed |= vectorizeRootInstruction(nullptr, PI,
14894 P->getIncomingBlock(I), R, TTI);
14895 }
14896 continue;
14897 }
14898
14899 if (HasNoUsers(&*it)) {
14900 bool OpsChanged = false;
14901 auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(it);
14902 bool TryToVectorizeRoot = ShouldStartVectorizeHorAtStore || !SI;
14903 if (SI) {
14904 auto I = Stores.find(getUnderlyingObject(SI->getPointerOperand()));
14905 // Try to vectorize chain in store, if this is the only store to the
14906 // address in the block.
14907 // TODO: This is just a temporarily solution to save compile time. Need
14908 // to investigate if we can safely turn on slp-vectorize-hor-store
14909 // instead to allow lookup for reduction chains in all non-vectorized
14910 // stores (need to check side effects and compile time).
14911 TryToVectorizeRoot = (I == Stores.end() || I->second.size() == 1) &&
14912 SI->getValueOperand()->hasOneUse();
14913 }
14914 if (TryToVectorizeRoot) {
14915 for (auto *V : it->operand_values()) {
14916 // Postponed instructions should not be vectorized here, delay their
14917 // vectorization.
14918 if (auto *VI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V);
14919 VI && !IsInPostProcessInstrs(VI))
14920 // Try to match and vectorize a horizontal reduction.
14921 OpsChanged |= vectorizeRootInstruction(nullptr, VI, BB, R, TTI);
14922 }
14923 }
14924 // Start vectorization of post-process list of instructions from the
14925 // top-tree instructions to try to vectorize as many instructions as
14926 // possible.
14927 OpsChanged |=
14928 VectorizeInsertsAndCmps(/*VectorizeCmps=*/it->isTerminator());
14929 if (OpsChanged) {
14930 // We would like to start over since some instructions are deleted
14931 // and the iterator may become invalid value.
14932 Changed = true;
14933 it = BB->begin();
14934 e = BB->end();
14935 continue;
14936 }
14937 }
14938
14939 if (isa<InsertElementInst, InsertValueInst>(it))
14940 PostProcessInserts.insert(&*it);
14941 else if (isa<CmpInst>(it))
14942 PostProcessCmps.insert(cast<CmpInst>(&*it));
14943 }
14944
14945 return Changed;
14946}
14947
14948bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeGEPIndices(BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R) {
14949 auto Changed = false;
14950 for (auto &Entry : GEPs) {
14951 // If the getelementptr list has fewer than two elements, there's nothing
14952 // to do.
14953 if (Entry.second.size() < 2)
14954 continue;
14955
14956 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Analyzing a getelementptr list of length "
14957 << Entry.second.size() << ".\n");
14958
14959 // Process the GEP list in chunks suitable for the target's supported
14960 // vector size. If a vector register can't hold 1 element, we are done. We
14961 // are trying to vectorize the index computations, so the maximum number of
14962 // elements is based on the size of the index expression, rather than the
14963 // size of the GEP itself (the target's pointer size).
14964 unsigned MaxVecRegSize = R.getMaxVecRegSize();
14965 unsigned EltSize = R.getVectorElementSize(*Entry.second[0]->idx_begin());
14966 if (MaxVecRegSize < EltSize)
14967 continue;
14968
14969 unsigned MaxElts = MaxVecRegSize / EltSize;
14970 for (unsigned BI = 0, BE = Entry.second.size(); BI < BE; BI += MaxElts) {
14971 auto Len = std::min<unsigned>(BE - BI, MaxElts);
14972 ArrayRef<GetElementPtrInst *> GEPList(&Entry.second[BI], Len);
14973
14974 // Initialize a set a candidate getelementptrs. Note that we use a
14975 // SetVector here to preserve program order. If the index computations
14976 // are vectorizable and begin with loads, we want to minimize the chance
14977 // of having to reorder them later.
14978 SetVector<Value *> Candidates(GEPList.begin(), GEPList.end());
14979
14980 // Some of the candidates may have already been vectorized after we
14981 // initially collected them. If so, they are marked as deleted, so remove
14982 // them from the set of candidates.
14983 Candidates.remove_if(
14984 [&R](Value *I) { return R.isDeleted(cast<Instruction>(I)); });
14985
14986 // Remove from the set of candidates all pairs of getelementptrs with
14987 // constant differences. Such getelementptrs are likely not good
14988 // candidates for vectorization in a bottom-up phase since one can be
14989 // computed from the other. We also ensure all candidate getelementptr
14990 // indices are unique.
14991 for (int I = 0, E = GEPList.size(); I < E && Candidates.size() > 1; ++I) {
14992 auto *GEPI = GEPList[I];
14993 if (!Candidates.count(GEPI))
14994 continue;
14995 auto *SCEVI = SE->getSCEV(GEPList[I]);
14996 for (int J = I + 1; J < E && Candidates.size() > 1; ++J) {
14997 auto *GEPJ = GEPList[J];
14998 auto *SCEVJ = SE->getSCEV(GEPList[J]);
14999 if (isa<SCEVConstant>(SE->getMinusSCEV(SCEVI, SCEVJ))) {
15000 Candidates.remove(GEPI);
15001 Candidates.remove(GEPJ);
15002 } else if (GEPI->idx_begin()->get() == GEPJ->idx_begin()->get()) {
15003 Candidates.remove(GEPJ);
15004 }
15005 }
15006 }
15007
15008 // We break out of the above computation as soon as we know there are
15009 // fewer than two candidates remaining.
15010 if (Candidates.size() < 2)
15011 continue;
15012
15013 // Add the single, non-constant index of each candidate to the bundle. We
15014 // ensured the indices met these constraints when we originally collected
15015 // the getelementptrs.
15016 SmallVector<Value *, 16> Bundle(Candidates.size());
15017 auto BundleIndex = 0u;
15018 for (auto *V : Candidates) {
15019 auto *GEP = cast<GetElementPtrInst>(V);
15020 auto *GEPIdx = GEP->idx_begin()->get();
15021 assert(GEP->getNumIndices() == 1 || !isa<Constant>(GEPIdx));
15022 Bundle[BundleIndex++] = GEPIdx;
15023 }
15024
15025 // Try and vectorize the indices. We are currently only interested in
15026 // gather-like cases of the form:
15027 //
15028 // ... = g[a[0] - b[0]] + g[a[1] - b[1]] + ...
15029 //
15030 // where the loads of "a", the loads of "b", and the subtractions can be
15031 // performed in parallel. It's likely that detecting this pattern in a
15032 // bottom-up phase will be simpler and less costly than building a
15033 // full-blown top-down phase beginning at the consecutive loads.
15034 Changed |= tryToVectorizeList(Bundle, R);
15035 }
15036 }
15037 return Changed;
15038}
15039
15040bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeStoreChains(BoUpSLP &R) {
15041 bool Changed = false;
15042 // Sort by type, base pointers and values operand. Value operands must be
15043 // compatible (have the same opcode, same parent), otherwise it is
15044 // definitely not profitable to try to vectorize them.
15045 auto &&StoreSorter = [this](StoreInst *V, StoreInst *V2) {
15046 if (V->getPointerOperandType()->getTypeID() <
15047 V2->getPointerOperandType()->getTypeID())
15048 return true;
15049 if (V->getPointerOperandType()->getTypeID() >
15050 V2->getPointerOperandType()->getTypeID())
15051 return false;
15052 // UndefValues are compatible with all other values.
15053 if (isa<UndefValue>(V->getValueOperand()) ||
15054 isa<UndefValue>(V2->getValueOperand()))
15055 return false;
15056 if (auto *I1 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V->getValueOperand()))
15057 if (auto *I2 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V2->getValueOperand())) {
15058 DomTreeNodeBase<llvm::BasicBlock> *NodeI1 =
15059 DT->getNode(I1->getParent());
15060 DomTreeNodeBase<llvm::BasicBlock> *NodeI2 =
15061 DT->getNode(I2->getParent());
15062 assert(NodeI1 && "Should only process reachable instructions");
15063 assert(NodeI2 && "Should only process reachable instructions");
15064 assert((NodeI1 == NodeI2) ==
15065 (NodeI1->getDFSNumIn() == NodeI2->getDFSNumIn()) &&
15066 "Different nodes should have different DFS numbers");
15067 if (NodeI1 != NodeI2)
15068 return NodeI1->getDFSNumIn() < NodeI2->getDFSNumIn();
15069 InstructionsState S = getSameOpcode({I1, I2}, *TLI);
15070 if (S.getOpcode())
15071 return false;
15072 return I1->getOpcode() < I2->getOpcode();
15073 }
15074 if (isa<Constant>(V->getValueOperand()) &&
15075 isa<Constant>(V2->getValueOperand()))
15076 return false;
15077 return V->getValueOperand()->getValueID() <
15078 V2->getValueOperand()->getValueID();
15079 };
15080
15081 auto &&AreCompatibleStores = [this](StoreInst *V1, StoreInst *V2) {
15082 if (V1 == V2)
15083 return true;
15084 if (V1->getPointerOperandType() != V2->getPointerOperandType())
15085 return false;
15086 // Undefs are compatible with any other value.
15087 if (isa<UndefValue>(V1->getValueOperand()) ||
15088 isa<UndefValue>(V2->getValueOperand()))
15089 return true;
15090 if (auto *I1 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V1->getValueOperand()))
15091 if (auto *I2 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V2->getValueOperand())) {
15092 if (I1->getParent() != I2->getParent())
15093 return false;
15094 InstructionsState S = getSameOpcode({I1, I2}, *TLI);
15095 return S.getOpcode() > 0;
15096 }
15097 if (isa<Constant>(V1->getValueOperand()) &&
15098 isa<Constant>(V2->getValueOperand()))
15099 return true;
15100 return V1->getValueOperand()->getValueID() ==
15101 V2->getValueOperand()->getValueID();
15102 };
15103
15104 // Attempt to sort and vectorize each of the store-groups.
15105 for (auto &Pair : Stores) {
15106 if (Pair.second.size() < 2)
15107 continue;
15108
15109 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Analyzing a store chain of length "
15110 << Pair.second.size() << ".\n");
15111
15112 if (!isValidElementType(Pair.second.front()->getValueOperand()->getType()))
15113 continue;
15114
15115 Changed |= tryToVectorizeSequence<StoreInst>(
15116 Pair.second, StoreSorter, AreCompatibleStores,
15117 [this, &R](ArrayRef<StoreInst *> Candidates, bool) {
15118 return vectorizeStores(Candidates, R);
15119 },
15120 /*MaxVFOnly=*/false, R);
15121 }
15122 return Changed;
15123}
